title: pork chop bake
directions: In a large baking dish, arrange potatoes and carrots in layers with flour, butter and onion. Brown pork chops and lay on top of the other mixture. Pour soup over top and bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: moor casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions slowly until done.
Drain.
Boil spaghetti until done; drain.
Put tomatoes into meat and cook, then add corn.
Stir in the peas last.
Mix the meat and vegetable mix into the spaghetti.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture into a casserole dish. Add a layer of cheese, then pour the rest of the mixture into the casserole.
Top with another layer of cheese.
Warm until the cheese melts and serve.

title: southern barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Heat over low heat about 15 minutes. Pour over browned meat and cook in moderate oven for 1 hour or until meat is done.

title: easy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add sugar, shortening, egg and flour.
Mix well and put into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Pour into crust. Refrigerate.

title: sourdough bread
directions: For starter, combine potato flakes, sugar and 1 cup water. Leave 1 cup starter out all day.
That evening, put the cup of starter in a large bowl.
Add oil, 1 1/2 cups warm water and salt. Let set out all night.
The next morning, add bread flour and work up with hands; form round ball.
Let rise all day until double in size.
Pull apart to make two loaves. Put in greased pan and let rise one to two hours or until doubled.
Cook at 350° for one hour then let cool.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter.
Add sugars.
Beat egg slightly and add to mixture.
Sift dry ingredients together and add.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet. Press with fork.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: disappearing marshmallow brownies
directions: Grease bottom and sides of 9-inch square baking pan.
Melt butterscotch pieces and butter in heavy saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm.
Add flour, brown sugar, baking powder, salt, vanilla and 1 egg to butterscotch mixture.
Mix well.
Fold into butterscotch batter just until combined the marshmallows, chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Center will be jiggly but becomes firm upon cooling.
Makes 12 to 18 brownies.

title: grilled cheese sandwich
directions: Melt butter in a pan.
Put sandwich in the pan and put cheese in the middle and butter on the bread.
Flip sandwich over when it is brown.

title: chip dip
directions: While heating chili, add cream cheese and blend thoroughly. Top with shredded cheese and serve with your favorite chip.

title: olive-cheese tidbits
directions: Cut butter and cheese into flour. Add pepper. Form into small balls around olives and seal.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight. Bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes or until brown. Yields 4 dozen.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Put ground meat in buttered casserole; do not pack.
Sprinkle onion soup mix and chopped onion and cover with layer of sliced potatoes.
Sprinkle with brown seasoning.
Mix together canned soups and pour on top of potato layer.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: biscuit pizza
directions: Place biscuits on baking sheet separately.
Put a little sauce on each biscuit, then your favorite toppings and finally the cheese.
Bake in a 375° oven.
They are done when slightly brown on bottom and edges.

title: cheese herb bread
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, sugar, salt, yeast, oregano and basil. Heat milk and butter to 120° to 130°. Gradually add hot mixture to flour, beating 2 minutes with electric mixer. Add 1 cup flour, potatoes, eggs and cheese. Beat 2 more minutes. Stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough on a floured surface and knead 8 to 10 minutes.

Shape into a ball and place in greased bowl. Cover and let rise until almost doubled. Punch dough down and divide in half. Roll into 10 to 12 inch lengths and place on greased cookie sheet. Brush with melted butter. Let rise until almost double in size. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.

title: applesauce cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat the butter, margarine or shortening for 30 seconds. Add the sugars and egg. Beat until combined. Stir together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and spices. Add flour mixture alternately with applesauce to butter mixture. Stir in raisins and nuts. Turn batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, spreading evenly. Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean. Cool in pan on wire rack. Prepare the Cream Cheese Frosting. Spread over the cake. Serves 12.

title: one cup vegetarian soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine until almost tender, but not brown. Add celery and carrots and stir for 3 or 4 minutes over low heat. Add everything else except barley.
Bring to a boil and then turn to medium-low heat and cook until vegetables are almost tender. Add barley.
Bring to a boil and cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: st. joseph's cream puffs(sfinge di san giuseppe)
directions: Place butter, water, whiskey and orange rind in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Add flour and salt. Keep stirring until mixture leaves sides of pan. Remove from stove. Add 1 egg at a time, beating thoroughly. Drop by tablespoon into hot oil and fry in a deep saucepan. Do not overcrowd. Cook until golden brown. Drain on paper towels. Toss in large bowl with honey. Arrange on platter. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese in top of double boiler.
Add sausage and Bisquick.
Stir until completely mixed.
Roll into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 325 degrees for about 20 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add sugar, catsup, mustard, vinegar and Worcestershire sauce to the three cans of beans (undrained).
Mix all together.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: In a large bowl or dishpan, cream together first 4 ingredients.
Stir in soda, salt, baking powder and flour.
Add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes for soft cookies, 11 to 12 minutes for crisp cookies.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and add vanilla wafers.
Bake in well-greased tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown the ground beef and onions together, then drain.
Mix all together and bake at 300°, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: barbecue potatoes
directions: Cut each potato into wedges crosswise.
Place in a glass baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inches).
Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over potatoes making sure all are covered with sauce.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; toss lightly.
Serve immediately.
Yields 6 servings.

title: stew stroganoff
directions: Combine first four items; mix well.
Heat slowly to bubbling, not boiling.
Serve over noodles; garnish with parsley.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Cut beef into cubes, brown in Dutch oven in a small amount of oil; drain.
Add the seasoning mix then cover with enough water to cover the beef.
Simmer until tender.
Add enough water to cook the noodles, bring to a boil.
Add the noodles.
Cook until noodles are just done.
Mix beef mixture with noodles or serve over the noodles.
Can be increased for a large crowd.
Large pasta shells can be substituted for noodles.

title: hermit cookies
directions: Beat butter (oleo), sugar and egg for 30 seconds.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Combine flour, soda, spices and salt. Add to beaten ingredients.
Add raisins and nuts.
Grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: kahlua mousse
directions: Heat sugar in water until sugar dissolves; set aside.
Mix eggs, salt and chocolate chips in blender.
Add the sugar mixture slowly and blend until thick.
Cool.
Add cognac and Kahlua.
Fold half of the cream into chocolate mixture.
Chill several hours in small wine glasses.
Top with remaining whipped cream and slivered almonds before serving.
Serves 6.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook hamburger in skillet; drain off grease.
Add onions and celery; cook slightly.
Add all other ingredients and boil about five minutes.

title: custard mochi
directions: Mix dry ingredients first. Gradually add liquids to dry ingredients.
Add butter last.
Mix slowly from the bottom so that it won't be so lumpy.
Grease two 9 x 13-inch pans.
Use half of the recipe for one pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt; stir in next 3 ingredients. Cook and stir until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.
Stir in eggs and cook 2 minutes longer.
Pour into pie crust.
Top with whipped topping.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown chuck onions, and peppers in a large skillet; drain. Mix with pasta sauce and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add spaghetti parmesan, pepperoni, grated cheddar, and granulated garlic to skillet mixture.
Place in a casserole dish and bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes, until hot and bubbly.

title: fullmer's corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients; make a well in the middle.
Add wet ingredients; mix until well moistened.
Place bacon in bottom of large cast-iron skillet or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour mixture over bacon.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour in greased and lightly floured bundt pan or two loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: barbecued baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Drain kidney and butter beans in a colander and wash under cold water.
Cut meat off ham hocks into bite size pieces.
Melt butter in skillet and add bacon, ham and onion.
Saute for about 7 minutes or until onions are soft. Combine onion mixture with beans and all remaining ingredients, stirring gently to blend.
Bake, uncovered, for one hour and allow to sit for 20 minutes before serving so the juices will be reabsorbed.

title: quick banana bread
directions: Mash banana; sprinkle soda on banana and let stand 10 minutes. Add sugar and mayonnaise.
Add flour last.
Makes 6 muffins. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: almond crusted pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place generous 1/2 cup almonds in food processor with sugar. Process until very fine. Pour into large bowl. Add gingersnap crumbs and mix. Pour in butter and stir well to combine. Press into bottom and sides of 10-inch pie plate to form crust. Bake 10 minutes; cool.

title: diabetic - apple fritters
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and milk in small bowl, beating until smooth.
If batter is too stiff, add a little water. Dip apple slices into batter and fry until golden brown.
Yields 2 servings.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Stir into creamed mixture the eggs, vanilla and water.
Mix with the creamed mixture the sifted flour, salt and soda.
Last, add oats, nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: beef and noodle bake
directions: Saute onion with butter.
Add meat.
Cook until meat is done. Add tomato sauce, water, noodles and seasonings.
Cover pan
and cook
on low 15 minutes.
Add grated cheese and pour into casserole
dish (greased).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Serve with green salad and rolls.

title: crumbed julienne carrots
directions: Cook whole carrots in a small amount of water with honey until tender.
Drain.
Cut carrots lengthwise into strips and roll them in egg, then in cracker crumbs.
Saute lightly in hot butter.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Place uncooked rice in bottom
of
pan.
Pour onion soup and one can of water over rice.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Place chicken on rice.
Spread
cream
of
celery soup over chicken.
Bake uncovered in preheated oven at 300° to 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Add water as necessary.

title: out of this world eggplant
directions: Boil eggplant until tender; drain and mash. Add eggs, onion, salt, pepper, milk, crumbs and butter. Mix well and pour into buttered casserole. Sprinkle top with buttered crumbs and bake 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Mix corn, peanuts and gumdrops.
Melt together marshmallows, butter and vanilla.
Mix all together.
Grease Bundt pan and press into pan, then turn out on plate.

title: elephant stew(this one for fun)
directions: Cut elephant into bite size pieces.
This will take about 2 months.
Cover with gravy and cook over kerosene fire at 465° for about 4 weeks.
This will serve 3,800 people or the 32nd brigade. If more people come, then add the 2 rabbits.
Do this only if necessary, as most people do not like to find hare in their stew.

title: cucumber rounds
directions: Mix cream cheese with mayonnaise and grated onion until creamy consistency.
Take small glass to make bread rounds.
Place one cucumber slice on rounds.
Spread cream cheese mixture on cucumber slice.
Broil until brown on top.

title: baked breast of chicken in wine(low cholesterol)
directions: Arrange chicken in pan and season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Dot
with
1/4 cup margarine and bake in a preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: mixed vegetables
directions: Cook vegetables until tender and drain well.
Add celery, onion and cheese.
Place in greased baking dish.
Cover with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: one skillet breakfast
directions: In large fry pan, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain off some of drippings.
Add frozen potatoes, onions and pepper. Brown well and then cover for about 5 or 10 minutes.
Remove lid and move potatoes around to make 6 wells.
Drop egg in each hole and cover, just long enough to baste.
Add crumbled bacon and cheese over top of all.

title: honey apple muffins
directions: Combine oil, honey, sugar and egg.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients and alternate with milk. Stir in apples and nuts. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Sprinkle top with sugar and cinnamon before baking.

title: deviled onions and sweet peas
directions: Cook onions in boiling water until tender.
Drain.
Add peas. Heat oven to 350°.
Add peas in shallow baking dish.
Mix and add remaining ingredients.
Pour over peas and onions.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, baste occasionally.
Serves 4.

title: sheila's punch
directions: Mix; freeze for 3 hours.

title: pickled okra
directions: Pack okra,
whole, in jars.
Add hot pepper, garlic and dill seed or fresh dill.
Mix and boil hard for 10 minutes the water, vinegar
and salt.	Pour over the okra already in jars. Seal jars in hot water bath.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over the cooled crust.
Heat juice and dissolve jello until smooth.
Add berries and Cool Whip until mushy.
Spread over second layer. Refrigerate until set.
Absolutely divine!

title: pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add milk and flour (mixed with salt and baking powder) alternately.
Beat well after each addition.
Add one egg at a time.
Beat well each time, then add 1 teaspoon each of vanilla, lemon, orange and butter flavoring. Bake in greased and floured angel food pan at 315° to 325° for 1 hour.

title: ground meat dressing
directions: Chop vegetables.
In a large pot put in ground round and cook until brown, skimming off excess grease.
Add vegetables and cook for about 15 minutes.
Wet stale bread and wring almost dry.
Chop in small pieces and slowly add to dressing.
(Don't add so much bread that your dressing is dry.)
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook mixture for about 1 hour on a low fire.
After dressing is done, add 1 stick butter.
If dressing is too wet add Italian bread crumbs.
When cool, beat one egg and add to dressing before putting in bird or dish.

title: the best jello pie
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water, then add 1/2 cup more of cold water. Add strawberries. Let set in fridge until jelled.

title: "nine's" coconut pound cake
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder and salt; then set aside.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Have pork shoulder sliced 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 2-inch strips, removing bone.
Melt shortening in large frying pan.
Add meat; brown lightly.
Add Dr. Pepper, garlic, soy sauce, vinegar and ginger.
Cover and cook over low heat until meat is tender, about 1 hour.
Add celery and green peppers; cook 5 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with some of the juice from the pineapple.
Stir into meat mixture.
Add pineapple with rest of juice.
Cook until green peppers are barely tender.
Serves 6 to 8 over rice.

title: creamy potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a small pot, heat the soup, butter or margarine and sour cream over low heat. Combine potatoes, green onion and 1 c. cheese into a large mixing bowl. Mix in the heated soup mixture. Season with salt and pepper. Pour into a 9x13 inch dish. Sprinkle 1 c. of cheese over the top of the casserole. Bake 30 to 45 minutes. Serve warm.

title: gallo pinto(costa rican dish)
directions: The rice should already be cooked.
In a pan, heat oil and fry onion and garlic until heated through.
Add beans; cook for about 3 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, ketchup, pepper, chopped cilantro and rice.
Mix together and you have a "Gallo Pinto."

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: barbecue slaw
directions: Mix together.
Store in refrigerator.
Will keep for several days.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Mix ingredients together and beat with a mixer for 1 minute. Bake 55 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Saute sliced onion and bell pepper, then remove from pan.
Add chicken, cubed or sliced.
Sear in pan.
Add seasoning and 1/4 cup water.
Add vegetables.
Garnish with cheese, tomatoes and lettuce.
Add salsa.

title: dreamy spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Saute ground beef and drain.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add spaghetti sauce and water to meat and remove from heat.
Combine cottage cheese, sour cream, cream cheese, pepper and onion.
In a 9 x 13-inch casserole, spread 1/2 of the spaghetti and cover with cheese mixture.
Add the remaining spaghetti and pour melted butter over it.
Spread tomato and meat sauce on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be assembled a day ahead.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes or so before baking. Don't overcook, as it will be dry.
Serves 6.

title: chicken and dressing bake
directions: Combine water, celery flakes and salt in a large saucepan. Bring to a boil over high heat; reduce heat to medium. Add chicken and cook until tender, about 20 to 25 minutes. Drain chicken, reserving 2 1/2 cups broth. Cool chicken and coarsely chop.

title: egg noodles
directions: Mix 1 cup flour, whole egg, yolks, butter, water and salt in a bowl.
Stir.
Knead dough working in remaining 1/4 cup flour. Cover with cloth and let rest for 30 minutes.
Roll out dough 1/4 inch thick.
Cut into thin pieces.
Let dry for 30 minutes.
To cook, bring 2 quarts salted water to boil.
Add 1 Tbsp. butter and noodles.
Return to boil
15 - 20 minutes.
Drain and serve.

title: cream cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all the ingredients into a bowl and knead them with your fingers.
Shape dough into golf ball sizes and set them on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten tops enough to make them look like biscuits.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Thin soup with about 1/2 cup of liquid from asparagus. Crumble crackers into soup mixture and chopped eggs; mix.
Pour 1/2 of the soup mixture into a Pyrex dish.
Arrange asparagus over this layer.
Now, pour remainder of soup mixture over asparagus and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake in moderate oven for about 15 to 20 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: johnnycake (cornbread)
directions: Note:
If you use sweet milk, add 1 teaspoon soda and 2 teaspoons baking powder.

title: soy-oat waffles
directions: Soak soy beans several hours or overnight in sufficient water to keep covered.
Drain; discard water.

title: curried pecans
directions: Melt butter in a shallow, small roasting pan.
Stir in curry and salt.
Add pecans and stir until coated.
Bake in a 325° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool and put in jars.

title: party meat balls
directions: Beat egg in large mixing bowl.
Add milk and crumbled bread. Let stand 5 minutes; beat with fork until bread is in fine pieces. Add next 5 ingredients.
Blend well with fork.
Use a teaspoon to shape meat balls.
Brown in oil and place them in a baking dish. Arrange slightly browned onion slices on top.
Mix gravy mix according to package directions.
Pour gravy over meat balls. Bake at 350° covered for 1/2 hour.

title: german noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles in salted water.
Saute onion and celery in butter until golden.
Add pepper.
Blend into cooked noodles in 2-quart casserole.
Add sour cream, cottage cheese and 3/4 of shredded cheese.
Pour beaten eggs over all and blend gently. Sprinkle 1/4 cup of cheese over all and bake for 1 hour at 350°. Let stand a few minutes before serving.
May be made in flat pan and cut into squares.

title: brown sugar green beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan. Cook until most liquid is boiled away.

title: stuffed chicken quarters
directions: Melt butter
and cook zucchini until tender, 2 minutes. Stir frequently.
Remove from heat.
Into saucepan, tear bread into small pieces,
stir in
eggs, cheese, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Preheat
oven
to
On
each
quarter, with fingers, carefully
loosen
skin
from
meat to form a pocket. Spoon stuffing in
each
pocket.	Place chicken in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 50 minutes until fork-tender.
When ready to serve, brush with honey and sprinkle lightly with salt.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Mix together sugar, water, oil, vinegar and vanilla and add to flour mixture. Bake in greased and floured oblong pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: best pie crust
directions: This makes "flaky pie" crust.
Can freeze balls of this to use later.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Saute with celery and onions.
Boil frozen broccoli until thawed; place broccoli at bottom of casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with chicken and more Parmesan cheese.
Mix together the soup, mayo, curry, Cheddar cheese, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Pour over broccoli and chicken.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and paprika; dot with butter.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: congenial salad(mrs. newel nesmith's recipe)
directions: Heat pineapple, sugar and
gelatin
to	boiling
point. Remove from heat.	Break up
cream cheese in pineapple mixture and stir well to melt.
Add	lemon
juice
and milk, then sour cream (or Cool Whip).
Add nuts
and	cherries.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish or large
mold.
Congeal.
(Use
sour cream for salad or Cool Whip for dessert.)

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook the broken spaghetti just until done.
Chop the onion, green pepper, cucumbers and tomatoes.
Mix together with the cooked spaghetti.
Pour Italian salad dressing over all.
Sprinkle with Salad Supreme (about 1 tablespoon or to taste).
Mix well again and serve or let chill and serve.

title: soy peanut dipping sauce
directions: Mix soy sauce, water and vinegar; set aside.
Put peanut butter in bowl and mix in sesame oil thoroughly.
Then mix in chili paste and cayenne.
Add soy mixture and mix well.
Blend in mayonnaise.
Serve at room temperature.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Make cream sauce with oleo, flour, pepper, broth, and milk. Blend in salmon, onion, and parsley.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape into eight cones or cylinders.
Roll in crumbs.
Dip in egg substitute.
Roll again in crumbs.
Refrigerate another hour.
Fry in deep hot 374° corn oil until brown.
Draining on paper towels. Serve with sauce made with skin milk, such as curry or mushroom.

title: kevin costner's favorite mocha-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spoon out onto a pan and freeze for 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: salted nut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, 1 cup margarine and salt; blend well.
Press in ungreased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. In small saucepan, combine corn syrup, 2 tablespoons margarine, water
and butterscotch chips; boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Sprinkle nuts over partially baked crust.
Pour cooked mixture over nuts.
Return to oven and bake an additional 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into bars. Makes 48 bars.

title: italian bean and tomato salad
directions: Combine beans, tomatoes and dressing. Cover. Refrigerate at least 1 hour. Sprinkle with basil and cheese just before serving. Makes 6 (1 cup) servings.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat; add vegetables, cornstarch, water and soy sauce. Cook until veggies and meat are done.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cranberry sour cream coffee cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift together baking soda, powder, salt and flour.
Add alternately, the flour mixture and sour cream.
Add almond flavoring.
Pour 1/2 batter into tube pan. On top, place 1/2 the cranberry sauce.
Add remaining batter and top with cranberry sauce and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. When cool, drizzle with 1/2 cup confectioners sugar mixed with 2 tablespoons water and 1/2 teaspoon almond flavoring.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Gently stir salt into sliced cucumbers.
Cover with ice.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain.
Add onions.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Boil 10 minutes.
Strain.
Add onions and cucumbers and bring to boil.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Jar and seal.
Makes 3 pints.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Fry ground beef and onion together until done.
Drain off any grease.
Add taco seasoning mix and water to meat; stir until well blended.
Turn off heat and set aside.
Mix tomatoes and beans in a saucepan to heat.
Set aside.
Shred cheeses and mix together; set aside.
Cut tortillas into bite size pieces and set aside.
Spray a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or glass dish with Pam cooking spray.
Put a layer of tortillas on bottom of pan, over the tortillas put a layer of the taco meat.
Over the meat put a layer of tomatoes and beans. Sprinkle cheese on top of the beans.
Keep layering all ingredients until all used up.
End the top layer with cheese and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Sift flour into large bowl.
Add water and mix.
Roll out on floured surface real thin.
Cut in long strips, then cut across them.
Let dry about 24 hours.
Prepare chicken and broth.
Bring to a hard boil.
Add dry dumplings, four at a time, cook for 5 minutes.

title: grandma's st. louis sloppy joes
directions: Cook celery in water until tender; set aside.
Brown beef and onion.
Add tomato soup and mix well.
Add celery and enough reserved water to make mixture "sloppy" but not runny.
Heat to desired
temperature.
Serves 6 to 8 on hamburger buns.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: a twist on pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; rinse under cold water. Drain. In a large bowl, whisk together the broth, vinegar, oil, garlic, sugar, basil and salt. Add the pasta, broccoli, tomatoes, pepper and Parmesan and toss to coat. Yield: 8 servings.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Mix eggs and milk together with flour.
Layer meat, onion and 1 layer of cheese on bottom of dish.
Pour mixture of eggs, milk and flour over it.
Make another layer of cheese and mixture and cheese.
Repeat until all is used.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown on top.

title: peasagne
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Add peas and mash.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: baked zucchini and cheese
directions: Heat olive oil in saucepan; saute onions 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, basil and garlic.
Cook over low heat 45 minutes.
Taste for seasoning and puree in blender or use a sieve. Slice unpeeled zucchini, then shake in paper bag with flour.
Heat vegetable oil in skillet; cook squash until lightly browned.
In shallow baking dish, arrange as many successive layers as possible of squash, sauce and cheese, ending with sauce and cheese.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cracker 'n vegetable lasagna
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, cook and stir red pepper, onion, zucchini and oregano in margarine until tender.
In lightly greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, layer half each of the crackers, vegetable mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.

title: spring garden vegetable soup
directions: Combine and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry jelly
directions: Combine cranberry juice and powdered fruit pectin in a 6-quart saucepan.
Cook until mixture boils and stir in sugar.
Boil hard 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and skim foam from top; pour into hot glasses and seal.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Fix the Rice-A-Roni according to directions except omit butter. Cool. Chip the artichoke hearts. Mix juice with mayonnaise and curry powder. Chip green onions and olives. Mix all together.

title: hot pineapple casserole
directions: Combine pineapple and eggs.
Combine sugar, flour and salt; mix into pineapple.
Put in greased 1-quart casserole.
Melt margarine; toss bread cubes in melted margarine.
Top casserole with bread cubes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until casserole bubbles and bread cubes begin to brown.

title: lemon lush
directions: Crust: Mix flour with margarine. Press into 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: salmon balls
directions: Mix all together.
Have Crisco hot and drop by teaspoonful into Crisco; fry until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: pickled peaches
directions: Put everything, except peaches, in saucepan.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Add peach halves.
Bring to boil; take off heat and cool.
Pour into jars and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: italian chicken and rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Stir together water, rice, tomatoes, cheeses, onion and 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with chicken; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and remaining Italian seasoning.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until chicken is tender.
Let stand 4 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: overnight chicken divan
directions: Remove skin and bone chicken and coarsely chop.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Arrange in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine next 7 ingredients; spoon half of sauce over broccoli.
Arrange chicken over sauce; top with remaining sauce.
Refrigerate overnight.
Let stand at room temperature 30 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake an additional 5 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Simmer water, bouillon cubes, celery and onions for 20 minutes.
Add potatoes, carrots and frozen vegetables and simmer until all vegetables are tender.
Add Cream of Chicken soup and cheese.
Heat only until cheese is melted.

title: mary lee's eggplant parmigiana
directions: Peel and slice eggplant very thin.
Dip in flour and then egg and fry in safflower oil.
Layer sauce, eggplant, grated cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers.
Cook at 350° until sauce boils, then cook 20 more minutes.

title: best oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix butter, Crisco, brown sugar and sugar.
Add egg and mix. Add vanilla, flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet by rounded tablespoon.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes for chewy cookies or 10 to 11 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet before removing onto wire cooling rack.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix all of puddings with milk until well mixed. Add condensed milk and Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers, pudding mixture, bananas, etc.
Last layer on top vanilla wafers.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients over boiling water.
Cool completely and add Cool Whip, stirring to mix.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate.
Makes 2 pies.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine ground beef, sauce, tomatoes and onions.
Cook noodles as directed and drain.
In a baking dish, layer the noodles, beef mixture and each cheese. Repeat, ending with cheeses.
Microwave 5 to 7 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: sugarless fruit muffins
directions: Combine juice concentrate with mashed bananas and eggs and beat until fluffy.
Stir dry ingredients together and add to the first mixture.
Stir in raisins.
Spoon into 18 muffin cups lined with cupcake papers.
Bake in preheated 350° oven about 15 minutes or until a pick comes out clean.
About 75 calories each.

title: chinese cabbage salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate.
One can Chinese noodles to add at individual taste as they get soggy.

title: crabmeat royal street(stuffed mushrooms)
directions: Saute shallots in butter.
Do not brown.
Add snow crab and bring to boil.
Add sherry and cook 8 to 10 minutes.
Add cream sauce and thicken with 1 or 2 teaspoons of the bread crumbs. Season to taste with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Let stuffing cool then roll into balls.
Roll the balls in mixture of remaining bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Stuff mushroom caps that have been poached for 5 minutes in water and lemon.
Butter the mushroom caps and bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.
Makes 20 mushroom caps.

title: beef broccoli wellington
directions: Brown beef and drain well.
Add broccoli, onion, sour cream, salt, pepper and mix well.
Simmer for 10 minutes.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix in large container and add ice.
Serves 15.

title: crab quiche
directions: Drain and flake crabmeat.
Grate cheese and toss lightly with crab.
Put all other in large mixing bowl and beat well.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Take 2 pie crust bottoms; put cheese and crab in crust and pour custard over top.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Continue baking at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes until done.
Insert clean knife in center, if comes out clean it's done.
Cool about 10 minutes.
Can freeze for about 1 month.

title: cinnamon-apple toast
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Wash and cut apple into thin slices, removing seeds.
Spread butter or margarine onto bread slices. Put bread on cookie sheet, buttered side up.
Place apple slices on bread.
Sprinkle with 1 teaspoon sugar and ground cinnamon. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until bread is toasted.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and put in a pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Frost with icing.

title: orange butter(good with zucchini bread)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until all orange juice is absorbed.
Store in refrigerator.

title: ritz cracker ice cream dessert
directions: Mix butter
and
Ritz
crackers
and put 1/2 into bottom of pan. Whip 3/4
cup milk with 1 box pudding until thick.
Blend in 1/2 gallon ice
cream
with
pudding.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Keep in refrigerator or freezer.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package. Drain water. Add Velveeta (cut in cubes) and 1/4 stick of margarine to broccoli. Microwave until it melts. Pour into buttered casserole dish. Melt 1/4 stick of margarine. Pour over top of casserole. Bake at 350° or microwave until bubbly.

title: skillet supper
directions: Brown pork chops; add onion and bell pepper.
Sprinkle rice around chops, add tomatoes and season with salt and pepper.
Cover and bake 1 hour.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add flour and eggs and beat well. Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked shell and sprinkle nutmeg as desired on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Yield:
1 pie.

title: oven salmon cakes
directions: Combine 3/4 cup of the cracker crumbs, egg, parsley, onion, milk, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add salmon and cheese; mix thoroughly.
Shape into 4 patties.
Mix butter with remaining crumbs.
Coat patties with mixture.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Place tomatoes on cakes and bake for 5 minutes.
Makes 4.

title: justin's juicy steak
directions: Pick out the steak.
Cut all the fat off.
Put steak in the pan with oil.
Cook it.
Put soy sauce in the pan, too.
When it's done, you eat it with a fork and a knife.

title: camp stew
directions: Boil chicken and stew beef together.
Cut potatoes and chop onions and boil together.
Place in large boiler and add other ingredients.
(Put corn in last because it will scorch.)
Add enough water to make the consistency right and bring to boil. Simmer 15 minutes or longer if needed, and serve.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan.
Heat on top of stove and cook until mixture forms a ball in testing.

title: chow chow(delicious with meats and beans!)
directions: Chop cabbage; add 4 teaspoons salt.
Work with hands, mixing and squeezing until a bit of juice comes from cabbage.
Add cut up peppers and tomatoes.
Work a bit more; add chopped onions.
Make syrup of vinegar, water, salt and sugar.
Put chopped ingredients into cold syrup and bring to a boil (a good boil in the center of the pot).
Cook about 5 minutes after boil begins.
Begin to put into hot, sterile jars from center of the pot.
Do not let cook too long or syrup will cook away.
Seal.
Yield:
8 pints.

title: a good punch
directions: Use a large container. Mix all ingredients together. Stir well. Chill and serve.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; cool and debone.
Saute onion, bell pepper and celery.
Cook spaghetti in chicken liquid.
When done, add chicken, vegetables and soups; mix well.
(I do not throw liquid out.
I add all except cheese and mix well.)

title: chinese upside-down casserole
directions: Brown meat; add chopped celery, onions and sliced water chestnuts.
Stir and cook until crisp-tender.
Add onion soup mix and pepper.
Stir and add undiluted mushroom soup.
Remove from skillet and put into casserole dish.
Top with Chinese noodles. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, or until noodles are brown.
Serve with soy sauce.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions, drain.
Drain the chilies. If you buy whole chilies in the can, chop them up.
Start with
layer of 8 to 10 tortillas in pan.
Put thin layer of meat, next layer with soup mixture.
When finished, sprinkle with grated cheese.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix ingredients well and chill.
Serve over salad.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients, except potato chip crumbs.
Spoon into shallow 2-quart casserole dish.
(Spray dish with nonstick spray.) Crush chips to fine crumbs and sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly throughout. Makes 6 generous servings.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt Velveeta, Cheddar, margarine and milk.
Pour over potatoes.
Let stand one hour. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add salt, pepper and onion flakes as desired.
Serves 12.

title: ham stuffed chicken breast
directions: Pound breast between wax paper until thin.
Place 1 piece ham and cheese on each breast.
Roll and serve with toothpick. Chicken should completely cover cheese.
Place in baking dish. Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes until sauce is thick.
Good over rice (remove toothpicks).

title: southern banana pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir pudding mix and milk in saucepan. Add egg yolks.
Stirring constantly, cook over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Arrange layer of wafers on bottom and sides of dish.
Add 1 layer of banana slices; top with a layer of the cooked pudding mixture.
Repeat steps again, ending with pudding.
Beat egg whites and salt with electric mixer on high until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Spoon over pudding.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until meringue is light browned.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix dry
ingredients
and
add water.
Stir and drop by tablespoonful into	1/4-inch
deep	hot Crisco corn and canola oil.
Turn frequently and fry until golden.

title: cheese strips
directions: Remove crusts; cut bread into 4 strips.
Brush with melted butter.
Toast under broiler on both sides.
Mix other ingredients except Parmesan cheese.
Spread on buttered side of bread and roll in Parmesan cheese.
Freeze at this point.
To serve, toast under broiler.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
Add water to make 1 cup. Heat to boiling and add Jell-O; cool.
Add ginger ale and let set partially.
Mix cranberry jelly and pineapple and fold into Jell-O.
Let set until firm.

title: imes' walnut cake
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add milk and dry ingredients alternately.
Bake at 350° in a loaf pan, which has been greased and floured, for 40 minutes or until tests done with toothpick inserted into cake.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix butter and sugar; add sour cream, then egg, salt, flour, baking soda and vanilla.
Add raisins, roll in the flour until of a consistency to handle.
Roll to 1/8 inch thick.
Use cookie cutters and put in slightly greased pan.
Bake 10 minutes until light brown at 350°.

title: cocoa oats delight cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk in a saucepan.
Let it come to a boil for one minute.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, oats and vanilla; blend well.
Put one spoonful at a time onto wax paper (drop by teaspoonfuls), then let cool.

title: meat balls
directions: Roll in balls and bake or fry for 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower cheese soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter for 5 minutes.
Add water and seasoning.
Bring to boil.
Meanwhile, cook the cauliflower in pan or microwave.
Add milk and cheese to boiling mixture.
Reduce heat.
When cauliflower is done, drain and chop.
Add to soup. Heat and serve.
May be made with broccoli or California vegetables.
Makes approximately 6 to 8 servings.

title: pumpkin or white sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs, sugar, and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Mix pumpkin or white sweet potato with ginger, cinnamon, and cream or rich, sweet milk.
Pour mixtures into crust and top with second crust.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: sausage, green beans & potato skillet
directions: Cook sausage and onion in oil in skillet until onion is tender.

title: every day cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, margarine and eggs.
Add vanilla and oil and mix thoroughly.
Mix together flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Roll in balls about size of a walnut.
Flatten with a fork.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Boil cabbage until done and drain.
Put cabbage in bottom of casserole dish.
Brown hamburger meat; drain and put on top of cabbage.
Pour 1 jar spaghetti sauce over that.
Add 1 bag shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 325° until cheese is melted.

title: seven layer dinner
directions: Use all raw ingredients.
Place in layers, season each layer with salt and pepper to taste.
Bake, covered, at 350° until all vegetables are tender, approximately 2 hours.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Blend together sugar, butter, milk and vanilla.
Put in microwave-safe bowl.
Cook on High 3 minutes, stir, cook additional 3 minutes.
Stir again and cook 3 minutes longer. Remove from oven and add chips and marshmallow.
Stir in well. Cook on High 45 seconds.
Remove; stir in vanilla.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: 6 weeks muffins
directions: Mix Raisin Bran, sugar, soda, salt and flour.
Add beaten eggs, Crisco and buttermilk.
Mix and store, covered.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: In a pan on stove, boil water and butter (or margarine) together.
Add flour all at once; stir hard and blend well.
Stir until mixture cleans side of pan.
Set aside to cool.
Put in mixer bowl and add 1 egg at a time, beating well after each egg. Spread in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake supreme
directions: Grease three - 9 inch round cake pans; line with wax paper. Lightly grease and flour wax paper. Set aside.

title: bishop asbury pound cake
directions: Preheat
oven
Grease and flour a 12 cup tube pan. Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add
lemon juice and vanilla.
Finally, add the flour a little
at a	time.
Pour
thoroughly mixed batter in pan and bake at
325° for 1 1/2 hours or until a straw test shows that it is done.
Cool a bit; then turn out.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and spices and beat well.
Blend in pumpkin.
Add milk and beat well.
Turn into pie pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 40 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan; set aside.
Beat sugar, molasses, butter and eggs in large mixer bowl until smooth.
Mix in flour, spices and salt, alternately stirring in boiling water.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix the eggs, oil, zucchini, pineapple, sugar and vanilla together; beat well.
Add the flour, salt, soda, baking powder, cinnamon and walnuts; mix well.
Finally, add the walnuts and wheat germ, mix and place in 2 greased 9 x 5 x 2-inch bread pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pesto macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni noodles.
Chill, then add onion, olives and pesto and mix together.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together including juice in pineapple. Whip and stir.
If you prefer add crushed pecans and sprinkle coconut on it.

title: oat wheat bread
directions: Combine oats and margarine in bowl.
Pour boiling water over them and set aside to cool.

title: artichoke salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to package directions; cool.
Drain artichokes; reserve liquid.
Add artichokes, thinly sliced green onions, olives and mayonnaise to rice.
Add marinade liquid as needed.

title: vegetable sandwiches
directions: Grate all the vegetables.
Squeeze the vegetables to remove as much water as possible.
Mix 2 tablespoons of the juice with 1 envelope of gelatin.
Put in small container and melt over hot water.
Add drained vegetables to gelatin mixture.
Fold in mayonnaise and salt to taste.
Refrigerate mixture overnight. This filling becomes stiff.
You may want to add more mayonnaise when making sandwiches.
Makes about 3 dozen finger sandwiches.

title: bar cheese
directions: Melt Velveeta cheese in double boiler; stir often.
Be sure it is melted.
Remove from stove.
Stir in horseradish and mayonnaise, also Worcestershire sauce.
Have dish ready as it sets fast.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, mix shortening, sugar, lemon rind, eggs and bananas.
Combine both mixes; stir until smooth.
Pour batter into a greased bread pan.
Bake 1 hour or until done.
Cool before you slice.

title: fudge pudding cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients in 1 1/2-quart casserole bowl with whisk until blended.
In separate bowl, mix brown sugar, white sugar and 1/2 cup cocoa.
Spread over top of previous mix.
Then pour hot water over top of all the ingredients.
Cook at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Test for doneness with knife to see if bottom is gooey and top is set.

title: peanut butter crisscross cookies
directions: Cream shortening, vanilla and sugar.
Add eggs; beat thoroughly.
Stir in peanut butter, then add flour, salt and baking soda that you have mixed together.
Form into the size of balls you want.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Press with back of fork both ways.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: red strawberry punch
directions: About 10 minutes before serving, in blender, crush strawberries and lemonade.
Mix all ingredients in punch bowl. Float mold and orange slices on top.

title: german cucumbers
directions: Slice cucumber (peeled).
Salt slices and place in a deep bowl. Weigh it down with a saucer to draw out the juice.
Leave overnight.
Squeeze out all juice from cucumbers.
Then place in brine of vinegar, sugar, milk, salt and pepper.
Let stand several hours.

title: luscious lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, 1 tablespoon lemon rind, butter, lemon juice and egg yolks in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until smooth and thickened, stirring constantly.
Cover and cool.
Pour sour cream into filling and pour into pie shell. Chill 2 hours before serving.
Top with whipped cream; garnish with lemon rind, if desired.

title: peanut butter custard pie
directions: Cream the powdered sugar and peanut butter together until crumbly; set aside.
Stir the next 7 ingredients together in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Bring to just below boiling point and cook a few minutes more.
Sprinkle 2/3 of peanut butter mixture in bottom of baked pie shell.
Pour custard over this; save remainder of peanut butter mixture for top.

title: frozen cranberry mold
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze in the Tupperware Jel-Ring mold, which prevents frostbite.

title: crunchy chicken cheese bake
directions: * If desired, omit tomato; combine soup with 1/4 cup milk.

title: overnight cinnamon rolls
directions: Starting at 5 p.m., dissolve yeast in 1 cup of warm water to which 1 tablespoon sugar has been added.
Put 2 cups water, one cup sugar, salt and melted shortening in large bowl.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add yeast mixture.
Work in flour to make a dough that is workable (fairly soft).
Do not let dough get stiff.
Cover and let rise.
Work dough down each hour.
At 10 p.m., roll out dough on buttered surface into 2 rectangles.
Brush on butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Cut into slices about 1-inch in width and roll.
Place in greased pans (any size and shape; rolls can touch).
Cover pans with towel and let set overnight.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 15 to 25 minutes.
Frost with powdered sugar icing.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish (8-inch square).
Mix flour, 1/2 cup granulated sugar, baking powder and milk until smooth. Spread over margarine in baking dish.
Add sliced peaches, undrained (or any fruit desired).
Do not stir.
Sprinkle with vanilla and brown sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle crust with remaining 1/2 cup granulated sugar and return to oven and bake until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Fry hamburger with onions.
Drain meat.
Add soups, taco sauce and chilies.
Heat until hot.
Place a layer of tortillas in casserole dish.
Pour part of mixture on top.
Layer cheese, tortillas, meat mixture and cheese until everything is used.
End with cheese.
Place in 350° oven.
Bake until cheese is melted good.

title: cheeseburger loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except cheese.
Spray loaf pan. Press half of meat mixture into pan.
Spread grated cheese.
Add the rest of the meat mixture and shape top.
Decorate with catsup. Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper; drain.
Add all remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer and serve.

title: fruit ice tea
directions: Bring 2 cups of water and tea bags to boil.
Remove from heat; let stand about 20 minutes.
Add sugar, Five Alive and tea, mixing well.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: rhubarb torte
directions: Blend the 1 cup flour, powdered sugar and butter.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: fluffy berry pie
directions: Blend cream cheese, sugar and eggs until smooth. Add vanilla and blend.
Pour into pie shell and bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Remove from oven and spread with sour cream. Chill 1 hour.
Mix berries and cornstarch in saucepan.
Cook until thickened and cool. Whip the cream and fold into cooled berries.
Spoon on top of cream cheese in pie shell.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut peeled eggs lengthwise and slip out yolks.
Mash yolks with fork.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Fill egg whites, heaping slightly.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: marzetti
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° in casserole dish for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken and debone; chop in small pieces.
Add all ingredients with enough mayonnaise to hold together.
Place on lettuce leaves to serve.

title: squash casserole(from the files of kay merritt)
directions: In a saucepan, steam squash and onion until tender.
Drain well and mash.
Set aside.
Combine sour cream and soup and stir in carrots.
Fold in squash and cheese.
Melt margarine and combine with stuffing mix and seasonings.
Spread half of stuffing mixture in bottom of 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Add vegetable mixture as next layer.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing on top and add pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Freezes well. Serves 8 to 20!

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar, salt, cornstarch and water.
Cook until thick.
Add juice of lemon, rind and orange juice.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks.
First, add a little hot mixture to egg yolk; mix.
Add a little more hot mixture to egg yolks to warm eggs, then add all eggs to mixture.
Cook one or two minutes.

title: stromboli
directions: Let bread dough rise overnight in refrigerator.
Roll out to 9 x 12-inch rectangle 1/2-inch thick.
Place pepperoni, Mozzarella cheese and jar of Progresso pepper salad in center of dough.
Top with 6 pepperoncini.
Fold and seal edges and ends of dough.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with pepper.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: spoon tacos
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; add salt, pepper, garlic powder and taco seasoning.
Add red beans, chilies, corn chips and tomato sauce.
Lastly, add cheese and stir well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: parsleyed potatoes(no fat)
directions: Peel and pare potatoes into small cubes.
Cook until tender and drain.
Add all the ingredients, stirring just until mixed well.

title: cheesecake bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs, margarine and pecans.
Spray pan with PAM.
Spread into 9 X 12 cake pan.
Batter will be thick.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and egg.
Spread on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350 for 30 -45 minutes until golden brown.

title: delicious omelet
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add yolks and continue to beat.
Add flour, milk, salt and pepper.
Beat well and fry.

title: never fail caramel icing
directions: Cook until dissolved.
Cover pan 2 or 3 minutes.
Cook to soft ball stage, then beat.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix cheese and cracker crumbs.
Add liquid to mushroom soup. Layer cheese and cracker crumbs in bottom of dish and layer broccoli.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cover with soup.
Repeat until all ingredients are used, ending with crumbs and cheese; sprinkle with nuts.
Pour melted margarine over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Freeze cookie dough for 1 hour.
Slice into thin slices 1/8-inch thick.
Lay slices overlapping on foil lined pizza pan (covering pan).
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes or until brown. Cool.

title: cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Using a No. 9 cast-iron skillet, melt 1 tablespoon shortening as oven heats.
Cream remaining 1 tablespoon shortening; add sugar.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add beaten egg yolk.
Sift cornmeal, flour, soda, baking powder and salt together and add to egg mixture alternately with sour milk.
Last fold in egg white beaten stiff.
Turn into hot cast-iron skillet and bake for 20 minutes, or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, beaten eggs, cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Stir in broccoli and put in buttered casserole.
In saucepan, melt 1/2 stick butter and stir in crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk candy
directions: Boil the ingredients until forms soft ball in water.
Beat until creamy.
Pour onto greased plate.
Drop by a spoon in water until the ball forms on water.
It is ready.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers; cut into 1-inch pieces, enough to fill 4-quart jars.
Now to each jar, add 3 to 4 slices onion, 2 pieces of celery and 2 heads of dill.
Dissolve sugar and salt in vinegar water. Bring to boil.
Pour while still hot over cucumbers.
Use in 30 days.

title: honey chicken
directions: In mixing bowl, combine honey, mustard, margarine and curry powder. Set aside. Dip each piece of chicken in sauce and place in a large greased pan.
Pour remaining sauce over chicken. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pot roast meat loaf
directions: Shape first 7 ingredients into a loaf in center of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Peel and slice 1/4-inch thick potatoes and onions.
Peel and quarter lengthwise the carrots.
Mix 2 teaspoons dried parsley flakes, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Place vegetables in layers around meat.
Sprinkle each layer with part of salt mixture.
Cover lightly with foil.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more to brown meat.
Serves 4.

title: highland toffee bars
directions: Combine shortening and oatmeal.
Add sugar, corn syrup, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Press into well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.
When cool, loosen edges and remove from pan.
Coat with melted chocolate; sprinkle with nuts.
Cut into squares when chilled.
Makes about 36 squares.

title: chili dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill.
Use as a seafood dip or surrounded by chips.
Yields 1 cup.

title: home canned rotel
directions: *For hot, use 10; for medium, use 7 and for mild, use 4.

title: candy-crust mint pie
directions: Combine chocolate morsels and butter in a saucepan; cook over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat; gradually add to cereal; stir well.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with aluminum foil; place a circle of wax paper over foil in bottom of pie plate.
Press cereal mixture evenly into pie plate.
Cool.
Invert crust on the back of another 9-inch pie plate; remove foil and wax paper. Return crust to original pie plate.

title: dump cake
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch square baking pan, layer the ingredients as follows: pineapple, cherry pie filling, cake mix and melted butter and scatter pecans on top if you like nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: turkey crunch casserole
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Stir soup into mayonnaise; toss with turkey mixture.
Turn into 2-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes, then sprinkle with noodles and bake another 15 minutes or until mixture is bubbling. Serves 6.

title: dressed eggs
directions: Cut eggs in halves and put yellow in bowl.
Chop yellows or mash with fork.
Add salad dressing, sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into halves, chill and serve.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Mix everything together.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: texas crab grass
directions: Melt butter and add garlic and onion. Saute until soft.
Add spinach. Cook about 5 minutes. Add crab and cheese.
Heat through. Serve hot with crackers.

title: *six week bran muffins
directions: Mix together all ingredients well in a large mixing bowl. Store in covered containers in the refrigerator.
Keeps 6 to 8 weeks.
To bake, fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes total of 6 dozen or more.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli until almost tender.
Place broccoli in ungreased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole dish.
Heat oven to 400°. Beat soup and milk with hand beater until smooth.
Pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix bisquick and margarine with fork until crumbly.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake until top is light brown, about 20 minutes.

title: spam ring
directions: Grind or chop very fine the Spam, onion and olives.
Mix well with cream cheese.
Add Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Put in a greased gelatin mold and chill for 6 to 8 hours.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Place meat back in pan over moderate heat. Add onions, garlic cloves, chili powder, salt and water.
Cook until onions and garlic cloves become tender, then stir in catsup. Serve on hot dogs.

title: mexican chili casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
In casserole dish add beans, salsa, tomato sauce, onion, 1 cup cheese, and hamburger.
Mix together well.
Bake at 375° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: meat balls with buttermilk sauce
directions: Add
enough buttermilk to mix.	Make into meatballs and brown in	a
frying
pan.
Put
in
a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Make sauce of 1 package of Lipton's beef and mushroom soup and buttermilk.
Pour
this
over
meatballs.
Bake
at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Mix together.
Line dish with vanilla wafers.
Cover with mix and repeat for 2 layers of vanilla wafers and mix.

title: russian banana nut bread(wonderfully moist and easy!)
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar. Add eggs and cream well.
Sift flour and soda together. Fold flour and bananas into above mixture. Add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: frank 'n chili manicotti ole
directions: Cook manicotti according to directions, drain and set aside. Shred 2/3 of cheese, cut remaining cheese into strips and insert strips into slit frankfurters.
Place one cheese-stuffed frank into each manicotti shell.
Combine chili and tomatoes in bowl; spoon 2 cups of mixture in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Arrange 10 stuffed shells on top of mixture and pour remaining mixture over.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove and uncover; sprinkle the shredded cheese on top.
Bake 10 more minutes, until cheese has melted.

title: blueberry banana pie
directions: Beat together cream cheese and sugar.
Spread into pie crust. Layer sliced bananas over cream cheese filling.
Spread Cool Whip over bananas.
Top with blueberry filling.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: chili for an army
directions: Cook hamburg and linguica until done; drain off most of fat. Put meat into a 5-quart pan.
Saute onions and peppers, then add to meat.
Add kidney beans, maple syrup, crushed red pepper and crushed tomatoes.
Heat on low-medium, covered, until hot.
Add chili to taste.
Stir often.
Taste often.
Be careful with the chili powder unless you are a fire breathing dragon!

title: raspberry salad
directions: Allow berries to partially thaw.
Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Stir in berries and then applesauce.
Chill until firm. Make topping of sour cream and marshmallows; combine and let stand 1 hour.
Spread over Jell-O mixture.

title: margaret's squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add soup, cheese, sour cream, water chestnuts, margarine, and almonds; then set aside.

title: betty lou's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with the skins on.
Cool before peeling.
Boil eggs.
Chop bacon small; brown until crisp, reserving 1 tablespoon of drippings.
Drain on paper towel.
In a large mixing bowl, cut potatoes into bite size pieces.
Add eggs, onion, bacon and at least 1 cup of mayonnaise (more may be added to reach desired consistency).
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: easy red velvet cake
directions: Mix cake mix with cocoa.
Add vanilla, buttermilk, coloring, melted margarine and eggs.
Blend until moistened.
Add soda and vinegar; mix well.
Bake in 3 greased and floured layer pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, being careful not to overbake.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion and saute.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and soup; stir constantly. Gradually add broth and then broccoli.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Add milk; simmer until broccoli is tender.
Best when broccoli has been chopped in food processor or blender.

title: hawaiian delight
directions: Cut up pieces of cake; spread pieces in bottom of cake pan. Prepare instant pudding as directed on box; pour on top of cake and spread out.
Cut bananas into slices; place on top of pudding. Sprinkle coconut over sliced bananas.
Drain crushed pineapple and spread over coconut.
Spread Cool Whip over pineapple as topping. Let cake stand in refrigerator overnight for best results.
Makes one 9 x 12-inch cake.
Serves 24.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, margarine and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, and beat 1/2 minute after each egg.
Add flour, salt and baking powder, using about half of the flour; add cream cheese and milk. Add other half of flour.
When this is mixed well add flavoring. Pour in tube pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325° or until brown and pulls away from edges.

title: dreamsicles
directions: In blender whip cottage cheese.
Add a little lemon juice together until smooth.
Add pepper and salt to taste.
Only 10 to 15 calories per tablespoon.

title: quick chicken dinner
directions: Brown chicken and cut up onion in skillet with cooking spray. Add a dash of Worcestershire sauce, vegetables and ingredients from rice and sauce package.
Add to that mixture the margarine and water according to directions on rice and sauce package.
Cook according to package directions.
Serve hot.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Beat eggs very well with medium speed mixer.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Beat with hand mixer for 1/2 minute; pour into molds.
Freeze.
Makes 10 to 12 fudgsicles.

title: orange-yogurt shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender; process until smooth.
Pour into 5 glasses.

title: boiled cookies
directions: Cook sugar, milk, butter and cocoa for 2 minutes.
Start counting when mixture comes to a full rolling boil.
Remove from heat and add oats, nuts (optional), peanut butter and vanilla. Beat well until blended.
Spoon onto waxed paper.

title: gansitos
directions: Let dough rise till double. Put on cookie sheet in small oval shapes.
Let rise and bake.
Put vanilla pudding (instant or cooked) into each end of bun and strawberry glaze in the middle. Dip in chocolate.

title: ravioli chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken according to package directions; cut into small pieces and set aside.

title: garden burgers
directions: In a large bowl, combine egg white and bread crumbs.
(If using veal or beef, stir in 2 tablespoons water.)
Stir in carrot, onion, green pepper, salt and pepper.
Add Parmesan cheese and ground meat; mix well.
Shape meat mixture into 4 (3/4-inch) thick patties.
Spray a cold grill rack with nonstick spray. Grill burgers on an uncovered grill directly over medium coals for 7 minutes.
Turn and grill 8 to 11 minutes more or until no pink remains.

title: easter lamb cake
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, cream shortening with sugar until fluffy.
Beat in flavorings.
Add sifted ingredients alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in egg whites.
Turn batter into front half of a well-greased and lightly floured lamb cake mold. Tightly cover with second half.
Place mold on a baking sheet.
For light aluminum molds, bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Remove to a cake rack and let stand, unopened, for 10 minutes.
Remove from mold and cool completely.
Frost with buttercream icing; sprinkle with coconut.
Use gumdrops or chocolate bits for eyes and nose.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Beat well and frost cake.

title: chicken for grill
directions: Put all in heavy foil.
Cook 1 1/4 hours, turning often.

title: bavarian cream pie
directions: Roll cookies into crumbs with rolling pin, saving 3 cookies. Mix crumbs with butter and press into a 9 or 10-inch pie plate, saving a few buttered crumbs to add to 3 crushed cookies for topping.

title: chinese pickled beets
directions: Drain
liquid from beets.
Mix all ingredients in a pan and cook
for about 5 minutes or until mixture thickens.
When cool, store in fridge.
Delicious!
May eat as vegetable dish. Add to salads or spoon over cottage cheese.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook ground beef and drain.
Cover the bottom of the dish with biscuits.
Put half of the spaghetti sauce over biscuits.
Then add meat and the rest of the sauce.
Cover with cheese and cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue steak fingers
directions: Cut round steak into finger-size strips.
Salt and pepper. Flour both sides of strips and brown good on both sides in skillet. After all strips have been browned, drain grease from skillet and wipe clean with paper towel.
Place strips back in skillet and cover with barbecue sauce.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Fill pepper halves with filling and place in casserole dish or pan.
Pour over the tomato sauce.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Fry in hot skillet.
Serve hot with butter.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix soup, sour cream, green onions and cheese together.
Add potatoes and put into greased casserole.
Mix corn flakes and butter.
Spread on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Boil ingredients, then add to cucumbers and cook.
Soak pickles overnight.

title: 5 can casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased baking dish. Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until well heated.

title: tea
directions: Place peel and tea bags in the bottom of tea pot.
Bring cold water to a full boil, pour over tea and peel when water first comes to a boil.
Let steep for 3 to 5 minutes.
Rub sugar cubes over mandarin peels to release oils.
Place 1 cube sugar in each cup, cover with hot tea.
Serves 4.

title: swedish cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order.
Roll balls about the size of golf balls; put on ungreased cookie sheet, 8 balls to each sheet, 4 on each side.
Place far enough away that you can flatten them with a fork that has been dipped in flour.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
I always make a double batch.

title: pork chops in chive cream
directions: Sprinkle pork chops with salt and pepper.
In frying pan just large enough to hold the chops, melt butter and oil over medium heat.
Add chops to the pan.
Brown on both sides.
Remove chops. Add mushrooms to the pan.
Saute for a few minutes.
Add wine, broth and chives to the pan.
Bring to a boil.
Add chops.
Cover. Reduce heat.
Simmer until chops are tender, 35 to 40 minutes. Remove chops to a warm serving dish.
Keep warm.
Skim and discard fat from cooking liquid.
Add cream and mustard.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Cook until reduced and slightly thickened.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour sauce over chops.

title: cheddar garlic biscuits
directions: Combine together Biscuit mix, cheese and onion.
Stir in milk until a soft dough forms.
Stir 30 seconds longer.
Drop by a tablespoon, 2-inches apart onto an ungreased baking sheet.

title: italian chicken
directions: In a frying pan, heat oil and add seasoned chicken breast (salt and pepper). Brown chicken on both sides (10 to 15 minutes). Add 1/2 to 3/4 of the jar of spaghetti sauce. Cover and heat through for additional 15 minutes. Cook pasta according to package directions. Drain pasta. Put cheese on top of chicken breast and let melt. Put pasta on plate and serve chicken and sauce on top. Makes 2 servings.

title: santa snacks
directions: Combine melted butter, graham cracker crumbs and coconut in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press lightly.
Cover with layer of semi-sweet bits.
Sprinkle with layer of chopped nuts and drizzle condensed milk over surface.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: pizza canapes
directions: Mix everything together.
Will keep in refrigerator.
Slice French bread into small thin slices and spread with mixture. Broil 10 minutes.
Also good on English muffins.

title: macaroni and cheese supreme
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour.
Stir milk in slowly.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Remove sauce from heat.
Add 2 cups Cheddar cheese and stir to blend.
Add Worcestershire sauce. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Place macaroni in 2-quart baking dish.
Add cheese sauce and mix.
Spread drained tomatoes across top of macaroni mixture.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and Mozzarella cheese over tomatoes.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Melt shortening and oleo in saucepan.
Add cocoa and water. Bring to a rapid boil.
Sift together flour and sugar in large bowl.
Add boiling mixture to flour and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour on greased cookie sheet (one with rim on it).
Cook 20 minutes at 350°.
Ice while warm.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Combine
cherries
and almond extract; place in greased 8-inch square
baking
pan.
Combine
dry
ingredients;
add melted butter, mixing until crumbly.
Sprinkle over cherries. Bake in a preheated 375° oven 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with your favorite whipped topping.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift together first four ingredients.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into large pan.
Bake at 300°F for 1 hr.

title: sweet chicken
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients into a saucepan over stove.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour over chicken and marinate overnight in refrigerator.
Place chicken and sauce in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until chicken is well done.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add potatoes.
Sift together all dry ingredients.
Blend into potato mixture.
Mix 1/4 cup flour with 1 cup nuts and 1 cup raisins. Add to other mixture.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes in 2 bread pans (greased and floured).
Let cool for 15 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Wrap and store in refrigerator.
May bake less time.

title: punch
directions: Mix Jell-O, Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Bring to a boil and stir well.
Add juices.
Chill.
Add ginger ale at serving time.

title: oysters homestead
directions: Saute bacon, onion and garlic in olive oil until glossy.
Add chopped spinach; heat for 10 minutes.
Add cream; heat for 5 more minutes.
Open oysters and loosen meat in shell.
Sprinkle oysters with white wine and add spinach mixture.
Heat in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove and dust oysters and spinach with Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Put oysters under broiler 2 or 3 minutes until brown and serve.

title: velveeta cheese fudge
directions: Heat the cheese, margarine and vanilla until melted in microwave.
Meanwhile, combine powdered sugar, cocoa and pecans. Combine the two mixtures (use your hands).
When completely mixed, spread in two 13 x 9 x 2-inch buttered dishes.
Chill 1 hour and slice.
Freezes well.

title: goldie's pecan pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into pre-made pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Mix lightly.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients; place in a buttered dish.
For the topping, combine the remaining ingredients in a bowl and chop fine.
Sprinkle over sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: apricot topping
directions: Puree apricots until smooth.
Combine apricots and next 5 ingredients in medium saucepan; simmer over low flame until sugar dissolves.
Cool slightly.
Stir in orange juice.
Chill before serving mixture.
Can be stored up to 2 weeks in refrigerator. Makes 2 cups.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Place alternating layers of vegetables in pan.
Spread mayonnaise on top.
Cover with grated cheese and bacon.
Garnish with olives if desired.

title: melt-in-your-mouth chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove meat from bones; place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In saucepan, mix and bring to boil the reserved broth and soup.
In another bowl, combine margarine, pepper, salt, flour and buttermilk; mix thoroughly to form batter.
Sprinkle cooked peas and carrots and rice over the chicken.
Pour broth mixture over this.
Spoon batter over top.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(I use a little less salt and pepper.)

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut 15 minutes in a colander.
Cut with scissors into one-inch pieces.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Cover and store in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Yields 10 servings.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown meat with onions and peppers.
Add sauce, stewed tomatoes and soup.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook spaghetti as directed on box (break spaghetti into 3 or 4 pieces).
Add spaghetti into mixture.
Pour in baking dish 13 x 9-inch and sprinkle on cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: apple casserole
directions: Place apples in greased casserole dish.
Cover with water. Mix butter, sugar, flour and cinnamon together and spread on top of apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: prune cake
directions: Grease and flour 2 (8 or 9-inch) layer cake pans.
Heat oven to 375°.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add whole eggs, chopped prunes.
Add flour with salt and soda alternately with prune juice.
Add walnuts last.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple (reserving syrup).
Add water to make 1/2 cup of pineapple syrup.
Add beaten eggs, sugar, salt and lemon juice. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thick.

title: quick taco chip dip
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and onions.
Sprinkle shredded Cheddar cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.
Done when cheese is near bubbly stage.
Serve with taco chips.

title: squash dressing
directions: Cook and debone 1 chicken.
Cook cornbread.
Cook squash, bell peppers, chopped onion and celery.
Drain well.
Mix cornbread and squash mixture with chicken soup and chicken broth (sage - optional).
Add chicken and bake until lightly brown.

title: sorry cake
directions: Mix well and pour in 13 x 9-inch greased pan and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: kielbasi bean stew
directions: Bring sausage and water to a boil over medium heat in a 6-quart saucepan.
Reduce heat to low and simmer for 10 minutes or until sausage is brown.
Remove sausage and set aside.
In same pan, cook onions, potatoes, carrots and green pepper until all are brown, stirring occasionally.
Stir in juice cocktail and sausage; reduce heat to low.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in pork and beans until heated.

title: potato candy(a 100 year-old canadian recipe)
