directions: It is preferable to cook potatoes a day ahead and refrigerate.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Mix wafer crumbs, 1 Tbsp of the sugar and butter; press firmly onto bottom of 9 inch spring foam pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Saute pork chops, then place in long Pyrex dish.
Add salt and pepper, sliced onion and potatoes on top of pork chops.
Pour cream of mushroom soup over this.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Mix and boil 2 minutes.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Mix Crisco, oleo and flour like pie crust.
In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients with beaters and pour into bowl with other ingredients; stir well.
Dough will be sticky; sprinkle with a little flour.
Make large balls and roll out (not too thin). Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Frost when cool with can of vanilla frosting or confectioners sugar and food coloring.

title: bisquick chew bars
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased pan and bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: grandma's date cookies
directions: Cook dates in a little water; cool.
Drop a small teaspoon of the cookie dough onto a cookie sheet and flatten.
Then drop a little of the date mixture.
Then put a little of the dough over the date mixture.
Bake about 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute onion in butter for 4 minutes.
Mix all ingredients together except cheese and Doritos.
Place Doritos in pan and pour mixture over; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: krumel forte(scandinavian)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla and baking powder; mix.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased square pan. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Wrap in aluminum foil to store.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Mince 4 to 5 mushrooms until you have 1/2 cup.
Mince green onion to make 1 tablespoon. Saute minced mushrooms and onion in 1 tablespoon butter until all liquid evaporates. Add a pinch of salt and parsley; mix well.
Cool.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat eggs, one at a time, and pour into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add melted oleo.
Blend in flour, onion, sugar, salt, pepper and milk.
Add both corns.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Serves 6.

title: no cook play dough
directions: Mix ingredients listed together in a large bowl.
After mixing, knead well.
Add food coloring as desired.
Store in an airtight container or heavy plastic bag for up to 6 months.

title: spokane sausage
directions: Mix ingredients with hands until well combined.
Cover tightly and chill in refrigerator (34° to 38°) for 3 days.
Each day, remove mixture from container and knead lightly for 5 minutes.
On fourth day, knead lightly and then shape into 4 equal rolls, each 3 inches in diameter (add 2/3 tablespoon of water if too dry). Wrap each roll in foil.
Chill overnight.
Next day, remove foil. Place on rack in broiler pan.
Bake 4 hours at 225°.
Turn several times.
Chill slightly.
Wrap in foil and refrigerate (3 weeks or freeze 2 months).
Serve alone or with cheese and crackers.

title: different pineapple salad
directions: Heat crushed pineapple. Add lemon juice and sugar. Stir well until sugar is dissolved. Dissolve Jell-O in 1/4 cup cold water. Add to pineapple mixture. Stir well. Set in refrigerator until practically set, then fold in grated cheese and Cool Whip. Pour into a mold and put into refrigerator until set.

title: methodist carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots crosswise. Cook in salted water until just tender. Drain. While carrots are cooking, saut onion in butter until transparent. Do NOT brown!
Add sugar.

title: venison salisbury steak
directions: Salt and brown minute steak in skillet and place in baking dish.
Saute pepper and onion in skillet and add brown sugar, soup and water.
Heat together and pour over steak.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients together over casserole dish.
Top with 1 cup crumbled potato chips and 1/2 cup grated cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: amazing easy coconut pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 1 (9-inch) pie plate.
In blender, mix milk, eggs, butter, sugar, Bisquick and vanilla. Blend 3 to 5 minutes.
Pour into pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes. Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: thousand and one dressing
directions: Make in advance to season (thin down with vinegar).

title: potpourri
directions: In crock-pot put water orange slices, lemon slices, bay leaves, cloves and cinnamon sticks. In about 10 minutes your home should be smelling great!

title: emma hawkins' chicken casserole
directions: Boil fryer.
Debone and cut into chunks.
Reserve broth.
Cook noodles in broth for 4 to 6 minutes.
Chop and saute celery and carrot.
Heat together all soups.
Mix all ingredients together. Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes or microwave on High for 4 to 8 minutes.

title: cereal - popcorn snack
directions: Combine in a large roaster the popcorn, peanuts and cereals. Combine and bring to a boil the margarine, Karo and sugar.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Do not stir while it boils.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and baking soda.
Stir quickly.
Drizzle mixture over popcorn, etc.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: 5 minute carnation fudge
directions: Combine and boil for 5 minutes the evaporated milk, butter and sugar.
Remove from heat and add the marshmallows, nuts, chips and vanilla.
Stir until marshmallows and chips are melted.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch buttered, square pan.
When cooled, cut into squares and serve.

title: mint ice cream dessert
directions: Sprinkle vanilla wafer crumbs evenly in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Set aside.

Melt chocolate and butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat. Remove from heat. Stir in powdered sugar, egg yolks, 1/2 cup pecans and vanilla. Beat egg whites (at room temperature) at high speed of an electric mixer until soft peaks form.
Fold into chocolate mixture.
Pour evenly over crumbs. Cover and chill 1 hour or until firm.
Spread ice cream over chocolate layer.
Cover and freeze 8 hours or until ice cream is firm.
Cut into squares.
Drizzle each piece with chocolate syrup and sprinkle with toasted pecans, if desired, not necessary. Yields 15 to 18 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored. Add milk and lime juice; blend well. Spoon filling into graham cracker pie crust. Combine egg whites (at room temperature) and cream of tartar. Beat until foamy. Gradually add sugar, one tablespoon at a time. Beat until stiff peaks form. Spread meringue over filling; seal to edge of pie crust. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes (until meringue is golden brown). Cool to room temperature. Chill in the refrigerator.

title: barbecue beef or pork
directions: Place beef or pork in crock-pot with 1 to 2 packets onion soup mix. Cook on high until tender. Use enough water to cover. Remove from crock-pot, saving approximately 2 cups of broth.

title: balloon buns
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease muffin pan for six.
Place muffin pan on baking sheet to catch spills.

title: father swiatek's punch
directions: Stir well liquor and sugar.
Add 7-Up and fruit.
Excellent party punch.
Watch out for the "punch" from the fruit.

title: cherry angel dessert
directions: Place half the cake pieces in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.
Save 1/3 cup cherry pie filling for garnish.
Spoon remainder of filling over cake in pan.
Top with remaining cake.
Combine pudding mix, milk and sour cream.
Beat until smooth, then spoon over cake.
Chill in refrigerator 5 hours.
Top with remaining pie filling before serving.

title: ah la
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain off excess fat.
In a large pot, combine meat, potatoes, tomatoes, celery, tomato sauce and Veg-All; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and let simmer until potatoes and celery are done.
A can of whole corn may be added, if desired.
Also, you may add water if a little dry.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and remaining ingredients.
Roll into small balls.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 minutes.
Roll into powdered sugar when hot and then again when cool.

title: gingerbread cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously spray a 10-inch tube pan with nonstick vegetable coating; set aside.
Beat sugar, molasses, egg substitute, buttermilk and margarine in large mixer bowl until smooth.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Turn oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients. Roll into balls and then roll balls in granulated sugar.
Place balls on ungreased baking sheets and bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: low fat chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Cream brown sugar, sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Beat in egg whites.
Gradually beat in dry ingredients.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Lightly grease sheets and bake for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies with 4 grams fat vs. 7 grams of fat.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Place it and rest of ingredients in crock-pot and cook until cheese is melted.
Serve hot in crock-pot.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes. Add salt, pepper, sugar, sour cream and margarine. Add just enough milk to bring to proper consistency. Add remaining ingredients (except cheese). Place in greased casserole and top with grated cheese. Bake 20 min. at 400° or microwave.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together the potatoes, 1/2 the melted margarine, sour cream, onion, salt, pepper, chicken soup and cheese.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Mix together dressing mix and the rest of the melted margarine; place on top of mixture.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, carrot, sweet pepper and salt together and let stand for 1 hour.
Boil the sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard for 3 minutes and then pour over the first mixture.
Let stand until cool.
Then put in containers and freeze.

title: corn bread bake
directions: Brown beef with onions; drain.
Prepare Jiffy mix according to the package.
Place 1/2 of the corn bread mixture on the bottom of the 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer ground beef, chilies, creamed corn and grated cheese.
Top with remaining corn bread mixture and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test by inserting a knife in center.
If clean when removed, it's done.

title: dill pickles
directions: Bring mixture to a boil.
Select about thumb sized or smaller cucumbers and wash thoroughly.
Pack into sterilized quart jars with three or four cloves of garlic and three or four dried red peppers (for hot), less for milder pickles.
Also add three or four heads of washed dill.
Add a pinch (whatever can be held between thumb and index finger) of alum to each jar.
Pour hot liquid to neck of jar.
Wipe mouth rim of jar with lint free wet cloth.
Put on sterilized lids and screw rings tight.
Place jars in cold pack canner half full of hot water.
Add boiling water to cover tops of jars.
Boil five minutes.
Remove to towels, out of draft, let sit overnight.
Liquid can be saved and reheated later.

title: sugar-free lemon pie
directions: Combine water, Sweet 'N Low and cornstarch.
Cook until thickened.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla, lemon juice and jello. Fill pie crust. Refrigerate.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple with juice.
Stir well.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.
Pour into oblong dish and chill until set.
Cut into squares and serve.
Equally as good as a salad or dessert.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and mix.
Next add buttermilk.
Add vanilla, baking soda and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in flour until mixed well.

title: spicy noodles and pork
directions: *If you can't find ginger root, use 1/4 to 1/2 teaspoon ground ginger.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare and slice apples.
Sift dry ingredients together and mix with apples.
Pour in unbaked pie shell, dot with butter and cover with top crust.
Flute edges using thumb and index fingers.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce temperature to 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.
Serve warm or cold.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add to the creamed mixture.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add a No. 2 can of fruit cocktail, undrained, to the mix and blend well.
Pour in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Take 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup chopped pecans and mix.
Sprinkle over top of the uncooked batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin tea bread with orange cheese spread
directions: Preheat oven to moderate 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Set aside.

title: barbecue
directions: Fry hamburger with onions until brown, then drain off the grease.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour this over browned hamburger and onions and simmer 20 minutes.
Spoon on warm buns.

title: red velvet cake
directions: You will need 3 round cake pans.

title: sweet and sour cucumbers
directions: Peel and thinly slice cucumbers and onions.
Mix together and pour over vinegar and milk.
Add sugar.
Add salt and pepper to taste and chill overnight.

title: salmon patties
directions: Heat shortening or cooking oil in a medium skillet.
Combine all ingredients in a medium mixing bowl.
Place one tablespoon salmon mixture in the skillet of hot oil.
Be sure to brown both sides.

title: italiano meat pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Brown beef in large skillet. Drain.
Add green pepper.
Cook for 2 minutes.
Add spaghetti sauce. Cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Sprinkle half of the Parmesan cheese over bottom of frozen pie shell.
Spread half meat mixture in pie shell. Sprinkle 1 cup of the Mozzarella cheese over meat. Layer remaining meat and Parmesan cheese. Bake on cookie sheet for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle top with remaining Mozzarella cheese. Return to oven until cheese melts.
Serves 6.
tags: Pet-Ritz deep dish pie crust shell

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all together, eggs last.

title: cheesy grits casserole
directions: Cook grits according to directions, cooking until thick.
Cool slightly.
Beat eggs; measure and add enough milk to make 3/4 cup liquid.
Combine all ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup cheese.
Place in greased casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with reserved cheese just before removing from oven.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mexican chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine first 4 ingredients in a saucepan and heat until chocolate is melted.
Combine all the rest in a large bowl. then
mix with the first mixture.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13 inch cake pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: easy olive-bacon appetizers
directions: Roll half strips of bacon around large stuffed green olives. Broil 5 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: diane's pasta sauce
directions: In a large Dutch oven, put beef, onion, garlic and green pepper; saute on medium heat until beef is done.
Add nutmeg, oregano and basil; cook 2 minutes.
Add the canned tomatoes and the next 7 ingredients; simmer for about 20 minutes.
Add tomato paste to thicken sauce; taste to see if any salt and pepper are needed.
Simmer another 10 minutes or so; taste again for any seasoning adjustments.
If a little bitter, you can add more sugar or squeeze a little orange juice into the sauce.
Surprisingly, this mellows the flavors.
Serves 8 with 1 pound of pasta (ziti, spirals or shells).

title: jello fruit salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water and marshmallows.
Let set until it starts to gel; then mix in other ingredients.
Chill.

title: chocolate marshmallow nut fudge
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt chips with milk and salt. Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla and nuts. Spread into 9 x 9-inch foil-lined pan. Carefully push marshmallows into fudge evenly. Cool. When firm, turn out fudge. Remove foil and cut into squares.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Have cheese and margarine at room temperature.
Blend them together, then add flour and Rice Krispies.
Work all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls and pat on greased cookie sheet. Cook for 15 minutes at 325°.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cook shrimp according to directions.
Soften cream cheese. Add rest of ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: onion pie
directions: Combine crackers and melted butter and press mixture around sides and bottom of 10-inch pie plate or 9-inch square pan to form crust.
Saute the onions in 1/2 cup butter.
Add scalded milk, eggs and salt.
Add the cheese last and mix thoroughly.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Add mushrooms, seasonings and pizza sauce.
Cool.

title: chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in order given and stir only enough to mix thoroughly.
Do not beat.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour in 350° preheated oven.
This pie freezes well.

title: gelatin banana splits
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and pour into a deep, narrow dish.
Chill until firm.
Just before serving, cut bananas in half lengthwise.
Brush with lemon juice and arrange in banana split dishes.
Scoop gelatin onto banana.
Garnish with whipped topping, cherries and nuts.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix oleo and sugar; cream well.
Add mashed bananas, lemon juice, eggs, salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add milk, vanilla and flour, a little at a time.
Mix well.
Add nuts; mix well.
Spoon into a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chicken and crouton casserole
directions: Line casserole with chicken breasts.
Cover with Swiss cheese. Dilute soup with enough water to thin slightly (approximately 1/2 can to each can of soup).
Pour over chicken and cheese.
Cover with croutons.
Pour melted butter over the top.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Let set 5 to 10 minutes.

title: salmon burgers
directions: Drain the canned salmon, reserving 2 tablespoons of the liquid.
In a medium mixing bowl, stir together reserved liquid, egg, bread crumbs, cheese, onion and thyme.
Add drained salmon; mix well.
Shape into 1/2-inch thick patties.
Cook in hot oil over medium heat until each side is brown.

title: sweet and sour turkey meatballs
directions: In medium bowl, combine ground turkey, onion, bread crumbs, 2 tablespoons sweet and sour sauce, egg white and ground pepper; blend well.
Form into 15 meatballs, each about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Coat bottom of large nonstick skillet generously with cooking spray.
Place skillet over medium-high heat and heat about 30 seconds.
Add meatballs; cook 6 to 7 minutes, or until browned on all sides, turning frequently.
Reduce heat to low; stir in remaining sweet and sour sauce.
Place bean sprouts, bell pepper and snow peas over meatballs.
Cover and cook 8 to 10 minutes, or until meatballs are no longer pink in center.
Stir mixture; serve over rice.

title: pound cake(moist, whipped margarine and crisco)
directions: Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and milk alternately, then vanilla.
Save 1/2 cup of the batter for the icing.
Bake at 300° for approximately 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: potato pancakes-luchow's style
directions: Wash, peel and grate potatoes.
Cover with cold water; drain and press out water.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Stir until mixed.
Heat oil in a heavy frypan.
Drop by full tablespoons into the hot oil and gently flatten each pancake as it begins to fry. Turn as soon as cake begins to cook golden.
Remove with a slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
These cook very quickly.
Serve with applesauce, sour cream or just plain as a side dish.
These freeze very well and may be reheated in the microwave.

title: cabbage(no so far east)
directions: Heat oil and garlic.
Add cabbage and spices.
Stir-fry until done.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Put in large casserole dish.
Cover with cornflakes.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed french toast
directions: Cube all bread. Put half in bottom of greased 9 x 12-inch glass baking dish.
Put broken up cream cheese on top of bread. Put rest of bread on top of that.
Put mixture of eggs, milk and maple syrup over bread.
Put plastic wrap on top and refrigerate overnight.
The next morning, bake in
a 375° oven for 45 minutes. Serves 8.

title: sausage soup(yield: 12 to 16 servings)
directions: Remove the casings from the sausage and discard.
Brown sausage in a heavy Dutch oven or large saucepan, mashing it with the back of a spoon until the meat is no longer pink and has rendered most of the fat.
Spoon out most of the fat from the cooked sausage and discard.
Add the onion and garlic and cook, stirring until soft, but not browned.
Add carrots, zucchini, peppers, wine chicken broth, tomatoes, basil and oregano and bring to a boil.
When the soup is boiling, add the orzo and cook for 20 minutes.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serve in heavy soup bowls.
If desired, sprinkle Parmesan cheese over each serving.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in baking pan or casserole dish covered tightly.
Bake for 2 hours.
Serve over cooked noodles or rice.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix vanilla pudding and cold milk; add ice cream.
Pour mixture over torn bits of angel food cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup of boiling water and add strawberries. Chill and then pour over cake-ice cream mixture.
Keep refrigerated.

title: seed cake for birds
directions: Pour hot, melted suet over the mixture until it is covered and put aside to set.
Stir when it begins to harden and the seeds will be nicely distributed.
Peanut butter can be stirred into the fat before pouring over the seeds.
Turn out onto a tray when ready to use.
This can also be prepared in half a coconut shell and hung from a tree.
Several of these cakes can be made at one time and kept refrigerated or frozen until used.
Seed eating birds (which includes most small birds around during the winter) will be attracted to this.
Insect and fruit eaters, such as mockingbirds, like a cake made only with raisins and suet.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until smooth.
Form into 1-inch balls. Melt chocolate chips and shortening together in double boiler. Dip balls into chocolate mix 1/2 way.
Place on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Fry ground meat until brown.
Add onion and garlic.
Put in enchilada and taco sauces.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.

title: pasta and salmon
directions: Cook rotini with water and chicken bouillon cubes.
Drain 9/10 of water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together.

title: taco bean soup
directions: Mix together and cook in crock-pot all day.
Serve with Fritos and garnish with cheese.
Can be served with oven baked potatoes. Also with corn bread.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots
1/2 hour.
Drain and chop or cut up with scissors.
Beat egg until
light;
stir in sugar and mix well. Stir in butter.
Sift
flour
with rest of dry ingredients and add alternately with orange
juice
and
water.
Add
nuts and apricots and mix well.
Pour batter into well greased loaf pan ( 9 x 5-inches) and bake
for
hour
and 15 minutes in 350° oven. (Also makes 3 small loaves, baked about 1 hour.)

title: eclair pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Put water and margarine in sauce pan. Bring to boil and lower heat. Add flour and salt. Stir over low heat until dough leaves side of pan; remove from heat. Beat in eggs one at a time until smooth. Place spoonfuls of dough on a cookie sheet and spread to form a 7-inch circle. Bake at 400° for 40 minutes; turn off oven and let pie shell stay in oven for 15 minutes. Combine pudding and milk in a mixing bowl. Place pudding in refrigerator for 15 minutes. Blend whipped cream, sugar and vanilla into chilled pudding. Slice the pie shell in half horizontally to
form two layers. Remove the top half and spoon pudding mixture on the bottom half; replace the top half. Frost with chocolate frosting.

title: easter ring(makes 6 rings)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a large bowl or on a clean surface.
Form a well in the middle and add butter, eggs and vanilla.
Mix.
(Mixture will be crumbly.)
Slowly add milk until mixture is a tacky dough.
Sprinkle table with flour and knead dough until even texture when cut with a knife.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter and pour over dressing. Combine and heat evaporated milk, cream of celery soup and chopped onion.
Put half of mixture in casserole dish.
Add chicken to soup mixture over dressing.
Put remaining dressing evenly over casserole.
Pour 1 1/2 cups chicken broth over casserole.
Put in oven uncovered at 450° until bubbling, approximately 45 minutes.

title: crab "pizza"
directions: Mix together the first 5 ingredients.
Spread on flat glass serving plate to resemble pizza crust.
Cover with chili sauce, leaving 1/4 to 1/2-inch uncovered around the edge.
Gently flake crab meat with fork; sprinkle over chili sauce.
Sprinkle parsley over all.
Serve with crackers and spreader.

title: hawaiian delight cake
directions: Bake cake mix as per directions on box in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool.
Spread undrained pineapple on top of cake.
Combine pudding mix, milk, cream cheese and Cool Whip.
Blend well.
Spread over cake.
Chill well, preferably overnight.

title: herbed butter
directions: In a small bowl, whip butter with a fork.
Blend in the other ingredients.
On a sheet of waxed paper, shake into a log.
Wrap in plastic and refrigerate until chilled.
Makes about 1 cup.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients and roll into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crabwiches
directions: Mix and spread on muffins.
Quarter and freeze.
Broil until bubbly.

title: fresh peach cookie cobbler
directions: Thoroughly mix peaches, sugar, tapioca and nutmeg; set aside. Slice cookie dough into 1/4-inch slices.
Line bottom and sides of 9-inch square baking dish with dough.
Pour peach mixture over the slices and top with remaining slices of dough.
Ice cream can be served on top.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: barbecue stuffed onions
directions: Quarter onions but do not slice through.
Spread open like a flower, stuff with butter and seasoning.
Wrap with foil.
Put on barbecue until soft, approximately 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes or until brown and firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package instructions; drain well. Make a white sauce of the margarine, flour and milk.
Season with salt and pepper; set aside.
Place broccoli in casserole.
Crumble Blue cheese over it.
Then top with white sauce.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Melt 1 tablespoon margarine.
Top casserole with cracker crumbs and drizzle the margarine over the crumbs.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: grandma's oatmeal cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter and sugars.

Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine the oats, flour, dry pudding mix and the baking soda; gradually add to the creamed mixture. Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls 2-inches apart onto lightly greased baking sheets. Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown. Remove to wire racks to cool. Yield: 7 dozen.

title: santa fe chicken hero
directions: Pound chicken breasts slightly to flatten evenly.
Brush both sides with oil.
Combine seasonings; sprinkle on both sides of chicken.
Grill over medium heat for 6 to 8 minutes.
Turn and grill 4 to 6 minutes more (until tender and no longer pink).
Top with cheese; allow to melt, about 2 minutes.
Brush rolls with margarine; grill until toasted.
Place lettuce, tomatoes and chicken on rolls; top with picante.
Serves 6.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Fry onions in butter; add the flour and sour cream.
(Have asparagus in baking dish.)
Pour sauce over in baking dish. Sprinkle with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven.

title: festive layered salad(makes 8 servings)
directions: Cook macaroni shells following package directions. Drain well in a colander. Cool to room temperature.
Place lettuce in an even layer in the bottom of a 3-quart clear glass bowl. Arrange the carrot sticks in an even layer over the lettuce.
Cover with a layer of macaroni, then the peas, onion and ham. Sprinkle top with Swiss cheese.
Combine the mayonnaise and dill in a small bowl. Mound the dressing.
Cover with plastic wrap. Chill several hours. Just before serving, toss well to coat.

title: chicken wings
directions: Cut off and discard tips.
Cut each wing in half.
Mix water, soy sauce, sugar, pineapple juice, oil, garlic and ginger.
Pour this mixture over the wings in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Place wings in flat shallow baking pan (about 15 x 10 x 1-inch).
Bake uncovered in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes or until brown.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: blueberry clusters
directions: You will also need 1 1/2-inch paper candy liners.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add strawberries and spoon over cream cheese.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Then add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and oats.
Add nuts, raisins and chips.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Fry sausage until brown.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until cheese is all melted.
Serve with chips.

title: dutch upwaterford, michigan
directions: Boil potatoes and let cool.
Chop into 1/2-inch pieces when cool.
Cut ham into 1/4-inch pieces.
Cut green onions into small pieces.

title: carnation banana wafer pudding
directions: Heat milk and add salt and sugar.
Beat 3 egg yolks and stir in hot mixture.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.

title: sicilian meatball soup
directions: Combine beef, egg, onion, garlic, parsley, bread crumbs, 1/3 cup cheese, salt and pepper in bowl.
Shape into little 1-inch meatballs.
Set aside.
Bring broth to boil.
Drop meatballs in, then add the noodles.
Simmer until meatballs are cooked (about 8 to 10 minutes).
Ladle into bowls and sprinkle generously with grated cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except water.
Add the cold water; mix well.
Bake at 250° for 30 to 35 minutes in cupcake pan.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and pineapple, then nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy caramel cake
directions: Bake cake mix per directions on box in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Poke holes in cake with handle of wooden spoon while still hot. Pour jar of topping over hot cake.
Follow with can of sweetened, condensed milk.
Cover and refrigerate.
Next day, frost with Cool Whip.

title: basic four fudge
directions: In medium bowl, mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Press into pan.
Cut in slices.
Serve.

title: tomato quiche
directions: In a skillet, saute onion in butter until tender. Add tomatoes, salt and pepper. Cook over medium-high heat until liquid is almost evaporated, about 10 to 15 minutes. Remove from heat. Sprinkle 1 cup of cheese into bottom of pie shell. Cover with tomato mixture. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. In a mixing bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Stir in cream; mix well. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325°. Bake for 40 minutes or more until top begins to brown and knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Let stand for 10 minutes before cutting.

title: pineapple bavarian pie
directions: Combine milk and lemon juice in large bowl; mix well.
Stir in pineapple and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crusts.
Chill until set.

title: sparkling burgundy bowl
directions: Combine all ingredients except wine and stir until sugar is dissolved and raspberries slightly thawed.
Put in punch bowl over small chunk of ice or ice cubes.
When ready to serve, add sparkling Burgundy.
Makes about 40 servings.

title: mildred fortner's pork barbecue
directions: Salt to taste.
Cook until onions are done.
Cut up about 2 pounds lean pork.
Combine with sauce and cook slow about 30 minutes.
Makes about 20 sandwiches.

title: tomato relish
directions: Peel and mash tomatoes.
Chop peppers and onions.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Put in jars and seal.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Drain juice from sweet potatoes.
To juice, add sugar, oleo, orange juice and cinnamon.
Cook until slightly thickened.
Add sweet potatoes.
Continue to cook until slightly candied.

title: my favorite lemon pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan.
Combine egg yolks, water and lemon juice in small bowl.
Then stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly until mixture boils and thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine.
Pour into baked 9-inch pastry shell.
Spread meringue over hot filling. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: mama's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Heat together next four ingredients until melted, then cool until about 110°.
Add yeast and egg to water, sugar and shortening mixture.
Mix in flour, half at a time.
Knead until the dough handles well.
Let rise until double in size.
Roll out and cut into desired size.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 375°.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Mix together eggs, oleo and sugar.
Add flour and soda.
Mix cocoa in boiling water.
Add to batter.
Add sour cream and nuts. Pour into a greased and floured 15 1/2 x 11 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: tomato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Peel and seed the tomatoes and slice 3/4-inch thick.
Put enough tomatoes in the crust to fill, but don't overflow.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together the mayonnaise, cheese, chives and basil, seasoning with salt and pepper to taste; spread over the tomatoes.
Bake for about 20 minutes or until the topping turns golden brown and pie is bubbling.
Cool slightly before serving.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place browned meat in the bottom of a casserole dish sprayed with cooking spray. Add Tater Tots over meat. Cover this with the soup (a 1/2 can of milk or water added to dilute soup first). Top with cheese and cover with foil. Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°. This is easy, quick and good.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom soup

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and oil together.
Add sugar and beat well. Add egg yolks and beat.
Combine flour and soda.
Add to egg yolk mixture.
Add buttermilk, vanilla, coconut and pecans.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 3 (8-inch) cake pans.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350° or until done; cool.

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: Put cereal in a large bowl and set aside.
Melt chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine until smooth.
Stir in vanilla. Pour mixture over cereal and stir until all pieces are coated. Put cereal mixture in plastic bag with the powdered sugar.
Shake until all pieces are covered.
Spread on wax paper to cool.
Store in airtight containers.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In large mixer bowl, combine all ingredients, except pastry shell; mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Place coconut and nuts in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix German chocolate cake according to package and pour over coconut and nuts.
Mix powdered sugar, oleo and cream cheese. Microwave until thin.
Pour over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Check after 30 minutes.

title: maple cheese and fruit
directions: About 15
minutes
before
serving, in a small bowl use spoon to stir cottage cheese, mayonnaise, maple flavored syrup and salt until blended.
With knife, slice bananas and apples into bite size
chunks.
Peel
and
cut orange crosswise into thin slices. Drain pear halves.
Chill large platter and line with lettuce. Arrange
fruit
in
separate
piles on lettuce. Spoon dressing over top.

title: pepperoni sticks
directions: These are simple and kids love them.
Remove biscuits from can and gently flatten them with fingers.
Spread with a spoonful of pizza sauce.
Top with 2 or 3 pepperoni slices and a small slice of cheese.
Roll up and put on an ungreased cookie sheet seam down.
Bake according to time and temperature on biscuit can. (These can be varied with other pizza toppings for the filling.)

title: cheese puffs
directions: Separate biscuits; cut each into thirds.
Wrap dough around cheese cubes.
Drop into hot oil for 3 to 4 minutes until brown. Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 30 appetizers.

title: corn pudding
directions: Drain corn; mix sugar and flour.
Add salt and pepper.
Beat in eggs and milk.
Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch dish; pour mixture in and bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until set.

title: chicken and bean soup with parsley
directions: Heat water, beans, sage and soup mix (dry) to boiling in a 4-quart Dutch oven.
Boil 2 minutes; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for about 2 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Stir in chicken and parsley.
Cover and cook about 15 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: easy rolls
directions: Pour water into large bowl. Spread yeast over water and add sugar and salt; stir to dissolve. Add egg, soft oleo and 3 cups flour. Beat with spoon and continue adding flour with hands until all flour is worked in. Place dough in greased bowl and brush top with melted oleo. Cover with greased wax paper and let rise until double. Punch down and make rolls. Bake at 400°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Pick off bones and cut up.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Cook stuffing according to directions on package.
In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, alternate chicken and broccoli.
Top with cheese slices.
Then top with soup.
Spread stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: quick skillet squash medley
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, melt butter.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except zucchini.
Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 5 minutes.
Stir in zucchini.
Continue cooking until squash are crispy-tender (4 to 5 minutes).	Makes 6 servings.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Pour water over dried beef and let stand for 15 minutes and drain.
Combine peas, soups, celery, garlic salt and pepper.
Add drained cut up beef to mixture.
Line bottom of casserole with 1/2 can of Chinese noodles, pouring mixture over them.
Sprinkle rest of noodles on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rosy rhubarb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Make cake mix according to package directions; do not bake.
Add rhubarb, sprinkle sugar and jello on top of cake batter, then carefully pour milk on top.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes.
Top with ice cream or Cool Whip when serving.

title: raisin and pecan pie
directions: Cook in saucepan all ingredients, except egg whites, 5 tablespoons sugar and vanilla, until thick and caramel colored. Pour in a baked pie shell.
Make meringue with egg whites, adding remaining sugar a little at a time.
Add vanilla.
Brown.
Serves 8.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening together.
Add sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well after each egg.
Add milk and flour alternately.
Mix well.
Add vanilla.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: simple apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Blend well.
Stir in apples and raisins.
Pour in crust with oleo.
Cut other in strips.
Crisscross strips over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or more.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Add cream or milk, sugar, vanilla and cinnamon; cream altogether.
Beat eggs; add them and sour cream to the mixture.
Put into pie shell.
Cook and cool, then put on glaze.

title: chicken long rice
directions: Soak mushrooms in warm water for 20 minutes, then cut off the stems.
Remove skin from chicken and cube.
Crush ginger root.

title: fast and easy lazy man's cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/4 pound of margarine in a casserole.
Make a batter of flour, sugar, milk, salt and baking powder.
Pour batter in center of casserole; do not stir!
Pour sweetened fruit in center of casserole (use berries, cherries, peaches, etc.).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican style cornbread muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix flour, meal, sugar, shortening and egg together.
Then add corn, peppers, onion, cheese and hot peppers. Mix well.
Put it in muffin pan.
Cook at 375° until golden brown.

title: grilled vegetable salad
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, set aside.
Cut carrots and remaining vegetables into large pieces.
Add to vinegar mixture, toss to coat.
Let stand 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Drain, reserving vinegar mixture.
Cook, covered with grill lid, over medium hot coals, turning occasionally.
Return vegetables to vinegar mixture, tossing gently.
Cover and refrigerator overnight.
Serves 6.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Heat green beans thoroughly and drain.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
In a small saucepan, melt butter.
Add Swiss cheese slices and stir to melt over low heat.
Be careful not to scorch. Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.
Pour over green beans and mix well.
Put into casserole dish and top with French fried onions.
Bake at 400° until bubbly.

title: quick and easy fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave 20-40 seconds. In a large bowl, blend cream cheese, marshmallow creme and cherry juice until well mixed and dip consistency.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; mix with sour cream.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill for about 3 hours.
Flavor intensifies after chilling.
Best if made day before.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place first three ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine flour and mustard; sprinkle over bread mixture.
Beat eggs, butter and milk.
Pour over bread mixture.
Refrigerate for at least 8 hours.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli by package directions.
Mix together remaining ingredients (except crackers and butter) with broccoli.
Top with crackers and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot and cook 5 to 6 hours, until tender.

title: chew bread
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add well beaten eggs.
Work with hands.
Add flour, nuts, coconut and vanilla.
Have pan already greased well and floured.
Pour in pan and mash out over pan. Cook 30 to 45 minutes in a 300° oven.
Add raisins, if wanted.

title: hot macaroni salad
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Cover with crushed cheese and Ritz crackers.
Dot with butter.
Heat about 30 minutes at 325° until bubbly.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Saute mushrooms in butter, remove from pan and set aside. Fry bacon until crisp; remove and set aside.
Add meat to dripping and brown well.
Blend in flour.
Add garlic, tomato paste, wine and seasoning.
Cover and simmer 2 hours.
Add onions, mushrooms and bacon; simmer 1 hour longer.
Garnish with cherry tomatoes and serve over noodles or rice.
Serves 8.

title: monkfish, crab style
directions: Cut fish into one-inch chunks.
Coat fish lightly in seasoned flour.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter in large skillet.
Add oil and garlic
and saute one minute.
Add floured fish.
Cook over high heat until lightly browned, about 2 to 4 minutes.
Add remaining butter.
Add 1 tablespoon lemon zest.
Squeeze half of lemon over fish and add parsley, salt and cayenne.
Stir to blend ingredients.
Serve fish with pan juices over top.

title: green tomato jam
directions: Put tomatoes in blender and discard liquid.
Add sugar and bring to a boil; hard-boil 15 minutes.
Remove and add jello. Pour into jars and seal.

title: brunch enchiladas
directions: In a bowl, combine ground ham, onions and green pepper.
Place 1/3 cup of the mixture and 3 tablespoons shredded cheese at one end of each tortilla. Roll up. Arrange tortillas, seam side down, in a greased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine first four ingredients and set aside.
Mix 6 cups of water and margarine and bring to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients and stir well.

title: cheese flan
directions: Mix all ingredients except sugar and water in a blender. Note:
To keep blender from overflowing, divide this mixture into 2 blendings; set aside.
Mix in saucepan 1 cup of sugar and 2 tablespoons of water.
Place saucepan over medium-hot burner and stir gently until evenly browned.
Spread glaze over bottom and side of an 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan.
Pour flan mixture over the glaze. Place pan in a large pan containing water.
Bake 1 hour in a 250° oven.
Let cool completely.
Cut into squares and place on serving plate.
Drizzle remaining glaze over top.
Keep refrigerated until time to serve.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: In stock pot saute beef in 1/4 pound butter.
Add water, salt, pepper, garlic powder, bouillon cubes, poultry seasoning, and worcestershire sauce.

title: pineapple and rice mold
directions: Mix rice, milk, sugar and salt in double boiler and cook 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle gelatin over pineapple and let stand 15 minutes.
Put into rice mixture.
Stir in coconut and flavorings.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Fold in Cool Whip and refrigerate overnight.
Delicious.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cut squash and cook until tender.
Drain.
Thoroughly mix all ingredients, reserving half of crumbs for topping.
Sprinkle a few seasoned crumbs over the top.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: apple crisp
directions: Prepare enough apples to fill 13 x 9-inch baking pan 3/4 full. Finely chop graham crackers.
Stir together crumbs, sugar, oats, flour and spices.
Add butter.
Mix well.
Spoon mixture over apple slices.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes or can be microwaved on High for 12 to 15 minutes, turning dish 1/4 turn after 6 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Great served with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: crab quiche
directions: In mixing bowl, beat eggs until frothy.
Add sour cream, milk, salt, mustard, cayenne and blend well. Drain crabmeat, break up and remove all cartilage.
Add to egg mixture.
Add cheese, chives and lemon juice and mix well.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell and bake at 425°
for 15 minutes.
Turn heat down to 350°
and bake another 30 to 40 minutes until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Serves 6.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain oranges and chunk pineapple juice.
Mix juice with vanilla pudding.
Cook until thickens.

title: country peach tart
directions: Roll pastry on floured surface into 12 inch circle; transfer to ungreased cookie sheet.
Combine flour and Equal; sprinkle over peaches and toss.
Arrange peaches on pastry, leaving 2 inch border around edge of pastry.
Sprinkle peaches lightly with nutmeg.
Bring pastry edge toward center, overlapping as necessary.

title: carrot cake
directions: In a large
bowl
mix
dry ingredients.
Add oil, eggs, carrots, pineapple, raisins,
nuts and vanilla.
Mix until all ingredients are moistened.	Then
stir
for
5 minutes longer. Bake in 9 x 9-inch	cake
pan
at 355° for 40 to 50 minutes or until cake leaves the side of pan.

title: ham and cabbage soup
directions: Season as you like.
Put in crock-pot until done.
The next day it's great!

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Whip the cream cheese and sour cream with mixer; add rest of ingredients. Roll into ball and chill.

title: fruited pot roast
directions: Brown meat on all sides in a Dutch oven.
Add onions, cloves, salt, pepper, brown sugar and 1 cup of cider.
Bring to a boil. Simmer for 3 hours.
Soak prunes and apricots in cold water to cover for 2 hours.
Drain fruits; add to meat with remaining cider. Simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove meat to platter and slice. Arrange prunes on one side and apricots on other side of meat. Gravy may be thickened slightly and poured over meat.

title: goulash
directions: Mix all ingredients; cook until onion and bell pepper are done.
The recipe can be doubled.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate four hours before serving.
Makes a large portion. This is good with all raw vegetables or any kind of chips.

title: corn salad
directions: Put all ingredients together in a large kettle.
Mix well. Heat just to boiling.
Do not boil because the corn will shrivel. Stir real good and, when hot, put in heated jars and lids and seal.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, flour and syrup, then add butter, vanilla and peanut butter.
Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then turn oven down to 350° and bake for 25 minutes.

title: pea casserole
directions: Place peas in small casserole dish.
Pour soup over peas. Mix crackers with melted margarine.
Cover peas with mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until top is browned.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine together in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken massimino
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Remove skin from chicken, if desired. Arrange in a baking dish and place in oven.
Combine remaining ingredients in a bowl. Add about 1 1/2 to 2 cups of hot water to mixture.
Let stand while chicken cooks, stirring once or twice to combine flavors.
After 1 hour pour mixture over chicken and continue cooking for 15 minutes.
Put chicken on platter and serve sauce in a bowl.

title: broccoli and cheese cornbread
directions: Add the corn muffin mix after mixing the other ingredients. Put in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: In very large deep pan crumble breads.
(I use the food processor for making
bread
crumbs.)
Add
onion,
celery and butter.
Heat squash
and
liquid almost to boiling.
Add eggs to first mixture and gradually add squash and liquid until you get "dressing" consistency
and
stir until butter melts.
Add pepper. This really makes
a
lot.
I
usually
cook
1/2 and freeze the other half.
Cook
in
Pyrex dish at 350° for about an hour.
My mom
created
this
recipe
and out family really likes it.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple.
Drain oranges.
Combine pineapple, oranges, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and walnuts.
Mix sour cream and sugar.
Stir into fruit mixture.
Chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cream of garlic soup
directions: Blend garlic in processor to coarse paste, stopping occasionally to scrape down side of bowl.
Heat oil in large heavy saucepan over low heat.
Add garlic paste and cook until just beginning to color, stirring frequently, about 12 minutes.
Add stock, wine and potato and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Puree soup in blender in batches.
Return to saucepan, add milk and cream and bring to simmer.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serves 16.
If soup is very thin, simmer until thickened to desired consistency.
Ladle into bowls and serve.

title: fancy egg scramble
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon or sausage and onion in 3 tablespoons butter or margarine until onion is tender, but not brown.
Add eggs and scramble just until set.
Fold mushrooms and cooked eggs into Cheese Sauce.
Turn into a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine remaining melted butter, crumbs and paprika; sprinkle atop eggs.
Cover; chill until 30 minutes before serving (can refrigerate overnight).
Bake, uncovered in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Makes 10 servings.

title: easy pickles
directions: Drain juice from pickles and discard. Put pickles in a bowl. Heat together remaining ingredients until sugar dissolves. Pour over pickles and stir with wooden spoon. Leave at room temperature until cool. Pack in jar and refrigerate for several days. Delicious!

title: apple crisp
directions: Put together in bowl, oatmeal, sugar, flour and cinnamon. Pour melted butter over this and mix well.
Spread over apples or applesauce which has been placed in pan or casserole dish.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Beat eggs, mix sugar and flour together to keep down lumps. Add sugar and flour mixture to well beaten eggs.
Add pineapple juice and butter.
In a saucepan cook to a cream sauce.
Pour over pineapple and bake at 300° for about 20-25 minutes or until slightly brown on top.

title: potato cheese puffs
directions: Combine ingredients except oil.
Mix well.
Pour 2 inches of salad oil into saucepan or frying pan.
Heat to 375°.
Drop batter by tablespoons 4 or 5 at a time into the hot oil.
Fry 3 or 4 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve immediately.
Makes 24 puffs.

title: strawberry angel torte
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix as directed on package for 10 x 4-inch tube pan.
Cool and remove from pan as directed.
Cut cake horizontally into 3 layers.
Stir strawberries and milk into 1 1/2 cups of the whipped topping in large bowl.
Place 1 cake layer on serving plate.
Spread with 1/2 of the strawberry mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with top of cake.
Frost top and sides of cake with remaining whipped topping.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Garnish top and sides of cake with strawberries.

title: ribs and marinade
directions: Generously season ribs with Cavender's seasoning.
Spray ribs with apple juice and pineapple juice.
Grill each side of ribs for 10 to 15 minutes.
Put ribs in oven, pouring remaining liquid over ribs.
Bake at 400° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt together.
Mix oleo and chocolate.
Mix all together and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and beat thoroughly.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together and alternate, adding to the creamed mixture, the buttermilk, bananas and dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Grease and flour Number 303 cans; fill 2/3 full and bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: benedictives
directions: With cream cheese at room temperature, add prepared cucumber, onion, salt and about 1/4 cup mayonnaise.
Mix very well, adding more mayonnaise, if needed.
Prepare bread; flatten each slice of bread with a rolling pin.
Spread each slice with a moderate amount of filling.
Roll up like a jellyroll.
Roll each in melted oleo, then in ground peanuts.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: meat loaf
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain off fat.
Stir in with other ingredients in a 3-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Combine 1 cup of the strawberries, 3/4 cup of the sugar and 1 cup of water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes on medium heat.
Remove from heat and mash strawberry mixture along with remaining 1/4 cup of sugar and the salt.
Return to heat and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add food coloring and stir.
Cool.
Slice remaining strawberries and place in the cooled pie shell.
Pour cooled strawberry filling over the fresh berries. Refrigerate until serving time, the top with whipped cream.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese until smooth. Add flour; mix until a soft dough forms. Cover; chill at least 1 hour or overnight. Shape dough into 1 inch balls. Place balls into cups of ungreased deluxe mini-muffin pan. Dip mini-tart shaper in flour; pressing into dough to form tart shell.

title: congealed salad
directions: Dissolve jello and cool.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and pineapple. Add to jello and nuts.
Mix. Whip Dream Whip according to directions and fold into mixture. Refrigerate to set.

title: no name salad
directions: Mix all together in a large bowl. Chill.
Coconut or nuts may be added.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in a casserole dish.
Melt margarine and mix the crumbled bread to coat.
Spread bread on top of pineapple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: breakfast bites
directions: Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, salt and nutmeg in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine milk, oil and egg; add to dry ingredients, stirring until just moistened.

title: drumstick treat
directions: Mix vanilla wafers, 2/3 cup peanuts and melted butter.
Pat in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: pistachio dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
So simple and so good.

title: candied carrots
directions: Drain carrots and place in heavy pan. Pour melted butter over them. Sprinkle sugar on top. Cover, bring to boil and simmer until sauce is syrupy.

title: baked "apple doughnut" muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg and 1/2 cup sugar. Cut in shortening until mix is fine.
Mix egg, milk and apple; add to dry ingredients at once.
Mix quickly and thoroughly.
Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.
Mix 1/3 cup sugar and cinnamon. Roll muffins in mixture.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: minnesota crab cakes
directions: Combine artificial crab meat, bread crumbs,
onion
and parsley.
Stir in milk, egg, Worcestershire
sauce	and
lemon juice.
Mix well.
Shape into 8 patties and pan-fry.

title: wonderful fruit dip
directions: Mix with beater.
Refrigerate for 1 hour or so.
Serve with fresh fruit (honeydew melon, watermelon, cantaloupe, grapes or strawberries).

title: pickled beets
directions: Boil juice, vinegar and sugar for 2 to 3 minutes.
Pour over beets.
Cool and put in refrigerator to chill.

title: linguine salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and let marinate 6 hours in refrigerator before serving.

title: dill string beans
directions: Stem green beans;
pack
uniformly
in
hot, sterilized jars (wide mouth).
To
each pint add 1/8 teaspoon red pepper, 1 clove garlic and 1 head dill.
Heat together water, salt and vinegar. Pour over beans
in jars.
Seal at once.
Process in boiling water bath (212°) 5 minutes.
Makes 4 pints.

title: persimmon cream candy
directions: In saucepan, mix together the sugar, syrup, half and half and salt; let rest about 20 minutes to dissolve sugar.
Place on heat; quickly bring to a boil.
Boil to almost the soft ball stage, about 230° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pulp and butter or margarine.
Return to heat; boil, stirring constantly, until the soft ball stage or 240°.
Set aside until partially set. Beat until mixture shows signs of hardening.
Pour into buttered dish.
Mark into squares when cool.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Add combined dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Put on floured board and work in additional flour until dough can be rolled out easily.
Divide dough and roll out to 1/8 inch thick. Cut with cutter, place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.
Yields: 3 dozen.

title: best brownies
directions: Melt chocolate.
Beat 4 eggs, 1 cup sugar and 2/3 cup oleo together.
Combine with chocolate.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together with nuts.
Combine with above ingredients.
Bake in 11 x 13-inch pan 33 minutes at 350°.
May frost with chocolate icing.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix Jell-O and lemon yogurt together; stir until mixed well, then add Cool Whip and mix well.
Put in pie shell and chill.

title: rolled spiced christmas cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, allspice and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse meal. Stir in eggs and water, mixing well. Dough will be stiff.
Chill until you can handle dough, about 1 hour.
Roll onto lightly floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut out with desired cookie cutters.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for 7 to 8 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Cool.
Decorate as desired with confectioners sugar icing, colored sugar or candied fruits.
Makes about 9 dozen cookies.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Use enough water and salt in proportion given to cook the zucchini, about 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Cool slightly. Cut each in half lengthwise.
Spoon out
pulp and chop coarsely. Place cut side up in ungreased baking dish.
Cook and stir onion in margarine until tender.
Add chopped pulp, green pepper, pimento and stuffing mix.
Fill the zucchini with the mix. Sprinkle each with 1 tablespoon cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until hot and cheese is melted, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: green bean-sour cream casserole
directions: Mix butter in saucepan over low heat.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Return to heat and stir until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream and onion.
Put beans in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Pour sauce over them, stirring to mix.
Top with Swiss cheese, then crumbs.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix and bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: tuna balls
directions: Bake at 500° for 5 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Cook and stir for 1 minute over medium heat.
Gradually add milk.
Cook and stir until thick and smooth.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Stir in onion, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes.
Grease rectangular Pyrex/glass casserole pan.
Layer half of the sliced potatoes in the pan. Pour half of the sauce over the potatoes.
Layer remaining potatoes over sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over potatoes.
Cook for 50 to 70 minutes in 400° oven.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: currant bread
directions: Cream together the flour, salt and margarine. Stir in the baking powder and currants.
Add eggs and milk. Turn into an oiled 8 x 4-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: dinosaur eggs for children
directions: Gently crack the hard-boiled eggs.
Put the cracked eggs in a small bowl or cup of Kool-Aid.
Cover bowl with Saran Wrap and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Take eggs out of bowl and remove egg shells.
The eggs will have a marbled look and taste like Kool-Aid.

title: chicken supreme
directions: In skillet, in 1 Tablespoon hot oil, cook chicken for 10 minutes or until browned.
Remove.
Pour off fat.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Add 1/3 to 1/2 c. of lemon juice to the condensed milk, depending on taste and desired tartness.
Mix together with a spoon until well blended and pour into pie crust. Chill in refrigerator to set and top with whipped cream.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Unroll dough and press seams together on 15 x 11 inch baking pan.
Bake 350 degrees for 8 - 12 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, sour cream, mayo, dry dressing.
Mix in onion.
Spread onto cooked crust.
Sprinkle vegetables over cream mixture.
Top with shredded cheese.

title: wheat germ zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs to blend. Add oil, sugars and maple flavoring. Continue beating until light and foamy.
Using spoon, lightly stir in zucchini. Combine flour, wheat germ, soda, salt and powder together.
Stir in gently. Add walnuts.
Stir once more gently. Put in greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: veal dogs
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly.
Shape into oblong patties.
Grill 8 to 10 minutes on each side or until cooked thoroughly.
Serve in hot dog rolls.
This is a delicious alternative to hot dogs.
Makes about 8 veal dogs.

title: crock-pot port wine ham
directions: Trim ham and place in crock-pot.
Add remaining ingredients. Cover and cook on high for 1 hour, then on low for 6 hours.

title: beef crunch
directions: Mix all ingredients except Chinese noodles.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 400° about 25 minutes.
Sprinkle noodles on top of casserole and bake 5 more minutes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Put all ingredients into a blender bowl in the order listed. Blend on low speed until a rough texture is acquired and ingredients are mixed or mash ingredients together with the tines of a fork until you achieve the coarse texture you may prefer.

title: inch salad
directions: Layer items in a 9 x 13-inch pan in order given.
Ice with mayonnaise.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese (optional). Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.
Stir before serving.

title: swiss chard
directions: Wash Swiss chard well. Let 3 cups of water with 1 tablespoon of salt come to a boil. Put Swiss chard into boiling water. Cover and let cook until tender. Remove and let drain. Saute garlic, onion and oil. Add Swiss chard and add salt to taste. Let simmer for 5 minutes, then add kidney beans. Also add about 1/2 cup water. Sprinkle Romano cheese. Let simmer for another 5 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread(serving size:  8.  preparation time:  0:30)
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat together milk and eggs. Beat in melted butter.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into a greased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: polish nut balls
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add flour, vanilla and nuts.
Roll into balls.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° on ungreased cookie sheet. Roll in powdered sugar before completely cooled.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Mix together well pineapple with juice and jello.
Put in microwave for 2 minutes to blend.
Let cool, then add buttermilk. Place in refrigerator until it starts to set.
Blend in Cool Whip and pecans.
Pour into large Pyrex dish.
Leave in refrigerator until set.

title: confetti bites
directions: Press crescent rolls into a 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking sheet to form a crust.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Place all dry ingredients in cake pan and mix with fork. Make "wells" throughout. Add oil, vinegar and vanilla into "wells." Mix with fork.
Add cold water and mix.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
DO NOT OVERBAKE AND MIX WITH A FORK, DO NOT USE A SPOON.

title: chili con queso
directions: Mix and cook over low heat until cheese melts and is blended.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Shape and chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Heat until cheese melts.
Add remaining ingredients and place in casserole dish.
Put in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl; make well in center.
Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Add blueberries.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes. Yields 12 muffins.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: coconut, macadamia nut chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 minutes.

title: eggplant
directions: Brown bacon pieces.
Drain all but 1 tablespoon of grease off bacon.
Add all of the other ingredients.
Saute until done.
Done when eggplant turns transparent.

title: mild mexican dip
directions: Using a food processor, chop tomatoes until juicy, with a few chunks.
Chop onion slightly and add to tomatoes.
Chop bell pepper slightly and add to tomato and onion mixture.
Add garlic salt and oregano; stir.
Use to top tacos or any dish you'd like to spice up!

title: mexican cornbread salad
directions: Bake Mexican cornbread.
Cool; crumble.
Blend Ranch dressing mix and mayo in separate bowl and then add to crumbled cornbread. Toss in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 3 hours and serve cool.

title: boston style beans
directions: Wash beans and leave in water to soak 8 hours or overnight. Bring to boil and cook until tender.
Mix mustard, salt, pepper, sugar, molasses, vinegar and chili sauce.
Add to beans; add onion.
Cut salt pork into slices; scald with hot water.
Drain and add to beans.
Bake at 375° for approximately 4 hours.
Add more boiling water during cooking if beans seem dry.

title: italian salad dressing
directions: Put in jar and shake well.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Bring to a boil 2 cups of water to melt jello.
Mix all ingredients together.
Blend strawberries and bananas in blender; pour over the other mixture and stir well.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Oil iron Pyrex. Combine the corn meal and flour in a large bowl. Mix the milk, butter and eggs in medium-size bowl. Stir the milk mixture into the corn meal mixture just until moistened. Pour batter into the prepared pan. Bake until golden brown, 35 to 40 minutes or until firm. Let cool, then turn out on plate.

title: old time pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Sift together sifted flour, salt and baking powder; add alternately with milk.
Add lemon extract and lemon rind.
Last, fold in the stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake at 350° in loaf pan for 45 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Place 2/3 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon in plastic bag. Cut each biscuit in quarters.
Place a few at a time into sugar mixture, coat well.
Place biscuits in Bundt pan.
Melt the oleo, brown sugar and cinnamon together.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes and turn upside down on plate and enjoy!

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into paper cupcake liners in 2 1/4-inch muffin tins.
Freeze.
After frozen, store in a plastic Ziploc bag.

title: eudene's spaghetti sauce
directions: Simmer everything together for approximately 30 minutes.
Add cooked spaghetti and serve.

title: chili con queso
directions: Drain tomatoes and chilies and place in a colander over a bowl. Reserve 1/3 cup liquid. Set both tomatoes and liquid aside. Heat oil in a medium saucepan over medium heat. Add onion and garlic; saut 4 minutes. Add cream cheese; cook until cheese melts, stirring constantly. Add tomatoes, reserved liquid and chili powder; bring to a boil. Add processed cheese, reduce heat and simmer for 3 minutes or until cheese melts, stirring constantly. Garnish with cilantro, if desired. Serve warm with baked tortilla chips. Makes 14 servings.

title: potato skins supreme
directions: Cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Scoop out some of the center and put shells.
Bake in for about 15 minutes more.
Brown the ground beef.
Drain excess oil and add taco seasoning mix according to package directions.
Add the chopped onions.
Put beef mixture into potato shells.
Top with favorite shredded cheese and put back in oven long enough to melt cheese.
Serve with sour cream, taco sauce, etc., as desired.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Add cloves, apple and orange slices to juice mixture and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand about 5 minutes.
Yields 2 quarts.
This is great when you have a cold or the flu.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients, then add the rest.
Mix together until smooth.
Pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch or 2 cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Frost.

title: black bean soup
directions: Rinse beans in running cold water; discard any stones or shriveled beans.
In 6-quart saucepan over high heat, heat beans and salt in 8 cups water to boiling.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Remove saucepan from heat; cover and let stand 1 hour.
Add ham bone and remaining ingredients.
Over high heat, heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer for 1 hour, or until tender, stirring occasionally.
Discard bay leaves.
Remove ham bone from soup to cutting board.
Cut meat from bone into bite size pieces. Return cut up meat to soup; discard bone.
With slotted spoon, remove 1 cup beans to small bowl.
With fork, mash beans.
Return to soup; mix well.
Makes 8 main dish servings.

title: coconut cake
directions: Grease and flour 1 (8-inch) square Pyrex dish.
Can double recipe and use an extra large rectangular glass Pyrex dish.
Bake cake per instructions on box.
While cake is baking, mix in a 4-cup measuring cup the Eagle Brand milk with Coco Lopez cream of coconut milk.

title: lichety split cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° until it tests done.

title: potato salad with cooked dressing
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until done.
Cool, peel and dice.
Dice onion and mix.
Add celery seed and salt to taste.
Beat eggs in top of a double boiler.
Mix flour, sugar and salt and add to eggs, stir often.
Gradually add vinegar to this mixture.
Cook over slow boiling water, stirring constantly to avoid lumps.
Cook until thickened and remove from heat; add milk and butter.
Mix well.
Pour over diced potatoes and chill for a few hours.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix together 1 stick of butter and cracker crumbs.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix together sugar, eggs and 2 sticks of butter for 10 minutes.
Spread on crust.
Layer bananas, pineapple, then Cool Whip.
Sprinkle on nuts and place cherries on top.

title: south dakota salmon
directions: Into hot sterilized pint jars, pack cut Northern pike. Combine ingredients for each pint.
Pour over Northern pike. Process for 90 minutes at 10 pounds pressure in pressure cooker or 3 1/2 hours in hot bath.

title: golden glow cake
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken pot-au-feu (soup)
directions: In 5-quart Dutch oven, over medium-high heat in hot salad oil, cook chicken (a few pieces at a time) until browned.
Remove to a plate.
Discard fat from Dutch oven.

title: waffles ala colleen
directions: Place waffle in toaster.
Heat according to package.
Spread with butter.
Cover with desired amount of maple syrup and sprinkle with sprinkles.

title: cheesecake pie
directions: Beat cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, about 4 hours. Before serving, arrange fruit on filling.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sugar, oil, eggs and sour cream.
Beat for 2 minutes. In a separate bowl mix brown sugar and cinnamon (and nuts if you like).
Pour half of batter in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with half of sugar mix.
Cover with remaining batter but not with remaining sugar mix.
Swirl with a knife.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Top with glaze.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together margarine, chocolate chips and peanut butter. Pour over Crispix (coat each piece well). Empty powdered sugar in a large brown bag, then pour in Crispix mixture and shake well. Great for youth group party treats.

title: rum pecans
directions: Combine all ingredients in small pan.
Cook over medium heat. Stir constantly for 15 minutes or until sugar is melted and nuts are well covered.
Pour out on oiled waxed paper.
Separate halves as they cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat altogether until well mixed except the last 3 ingredients.
In separate bowl, mix 5 tablespoons of sugar and 2 tablespoons of cinnamon.
Add apples.
Mix and set aside.
Alternate batter and apples in well-greased 10-inch tube pan, ending with apples on top.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours.
Cool 10 minutes.
Turn upside down on plate.
Tap bottom of pan with knife to loosen.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Add alternately with dry mix.
Fold in stiff egg whites and fruit. Bake in Bundt or angel food cake pan for 1 hour and 10 minutes at 325°.
Glaze.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° in a Bundt pan or oblong cake pan for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.
Can be iced with a glaze of your favorite icing.

title: venison stew
directions: Dust stew meat with flour and pepper.
Brown meat in bacon drippings.
Place browned meat in crock-pot.
Add onion and other vegetables.
Blend soup with milk and beef broth; pour over ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Add sliced mushrooms and bacon bits about 1 hour prior to serving.

title: southwestern snack mix
directions: Pour cereal into a large mixing bowl. Combine oleo, catsup, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and onion salt.
Drizzle over cereal, tossing lightly to thoroughly coat.
Sprinkle with chili powder until thoroughly coated. Spread in ungreased jelly roll pan and bake about 25 minutes at 300°.
Stir occasionally. Spread on foil to cool. Store in tightly covered container.

title: cabbage ramen salad
directions: For dressing, combine seasoning packet from Ramen noodles, oil, vinegar and sugar in small bowl. Mix well.

title: father's sauerkraut
directions: Cover the sauerkraut with water. Add the diced apple, 1 diced onion, sugar and vinegar. Cook about 45 minutes. Then add the remaining onion which has been browned in butter. Serve immediately.

title: texas chili dip
directions: Turn chili, cottage cheese and peppers into mixer bowl; beat together at low speed until blended, adding lemon juice.
If you use hot sauce, omit chopped peppers and add sauce with lemon juice.
Chill about 4 hours.
Serve as a dip for cucumber slices, cauliflower, celery and carrot sticks or with toasted wedges of cornmeal tortillas.
Makes about 2 2/3 cups.

title: chocolate picnic cake
directions: Mix first 6
ingredients together and beat 3 or 4 minutes on medium speed.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: meat and potatoes casserole
directions: Mix beef, hash browns, tomato sauce, paste and water; pour 1/2 into 3-quart dish.
Top with 1/2 of cheese.
Add remaining beef mixture.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Top with rest of cheese while hot.

title: portuguese red bean soup
directions: Boil the ham shanks and sausage in enough water to cover for about 20 minutes. Add beans and cook until beans are tender.
Add tomato sauce, chopped onion, parsley, potatoes and cabbage.
Cook until vegetables are clear.

title: french fried fish batter
directions: Batter:
Sift flour, paprika, baking powder and salt.
Combine egg and milk.
Blend milk mixture into flour just until smooth. Add juice.
This should be thick enough to just glaze or run off. Fry in deep fat or fry in pan.

title: puff pancakes
directions: Beat eggs in bowl. Add all remaining ingredients. Pour batter from 1/4 cup measuring cup. Brown on both sides.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix oil with seasoning and pour over crackers.
Stir occasionally until moisture is absorbed.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground meat and drain excess fat.
Add spaghetti sauce, water, salt, seasoning and sugar.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.

title: provincial liver paste(foies gras)
directions: Boil liver in water until tender.
Remove skin and fibers. Grind in food chopper with onion and celery.
Blend to a smooth paste and season to taste with lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Form into a large mound; chill.
