Before serving, sprinkle with minced eggs; serve on lettuce accompanied by cocktail crackers and spreaders.
This paste may be stored in earthenware crocks with melted butter poured on top.
Truffles may be added.
The same proportion of pork or chicken livers may be substituted for the calf's liver.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat margarine, sugars, egg, water and vanilla together until creamy.
Sift together flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture and blend well.
Stir in oats and nutmeg.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 10 to 14 minutes.

title: annette's blueberry torte
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add crumbs.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with this mixture.
Beat cream cheese.
Add sugar and beaten eggs and vanilla.
Spread over crumb mixture and bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Spread pie filling over top and chill well. Cover with whipped cream before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: karla's pot roast
directions: Soak the meat in the refrigerator for about 24 hours before cooking. Drain off meat and save the juice. Put the roast in a roasting pan in the oven about 1/2 hour uncovered on 350°. Add the drained juice to the roast and cook uncovered an additional 1 hour.
Put 6 ginger snaps in the juice (It makes a nice thick gravy). Put a cover on the roasting pan and cook about 1 hour covered or until meat is tender and done.

title: cranberry fruit punch
directions: Mix well, serve over ice cubes.

title: preserved children
directions: Mix the children and the dogs well together; put them on the field, stirring constantly.

title: orange gelatin salad
directions: Combine jello, hot water and orange juice; let this jell.
Then add pineapple, oranges and cherries (if desired).
Let this set. Mix Cool Whip with pudding and spread on top of jello.

title: crunch torte
directions: Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Beat in vanilla.
Fold in cracker crumbs that have been mixed with sugar and nuts.
Put in greased 9-inch pan, round or square.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Serve with fresh berries, peaches, ice cream, or whipped cream.
Serve small servings.
It is rich.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat vigorously with fork. Grease bottom (only) of loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes.

title: savory stuffed shrimp
directions: In small skillet, saute celery, onion and green peppers (about 4 minutes).

In 1 teaspoon olive oil, toss with celery, onion, peppers, breadcrumbs and add egg, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Combine remaining oil, thyme and paprika and brush on shrimp. Stuff bread mixture into sliced back of shrimp allowing it to spill over in baking dish and bake 10 to 15 minutes or until shrimp are cooked through.
Garnish with black olives.

title: sweet and sour meat balls
directions: Drain pineapple reserving juice.
Set pineapple aside.
Add water to juice if needed to measure 1 cup.
Pour into a large skillet.
Add water, vinegar, soy sauce, brown sugar and cornstarch.
Stir until smooth.
Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Add pineapple, meatballs, and green pepper.
Simmer uncovered for 20 minutes or until heated through. Serve over rice.
Yields 6 servings.

title: applesauce-spice cake
directions: Cut waxed paper to fit 9-inch tube pan.
Grease pan and paper. Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Fold in applesauce and spices.
Add soda to sifted flour.
Fold flour into butter mixture.
Add raisins and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pan.
Bake 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours at 325°.
Use toothpick test for doneness.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat together all ingredients for 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: church window candy
directions: In a large saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips and butter.
Remove from heat and cool.
Stir in marshmallows and 1/4 cup nuts.
Divide mixture in half.
Shape each half into a log 1 1/2-inches in diameter 6 inches long.
Roll each log in remaining 1/2 cup nuts and chill.
Slice log in 1/2-inch slices.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat, add onion and garlic; stir until mixture becomes brown.
Add water.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder, salt, cumin and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours until meat is tender and mixture has thickened.

title: fruit pizza pie
directions: Spread dough over pizza pan.
Bake until brown; cool.
Mix cream cheese, vanilla and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Spread on cookie base.
Place fruit in circles on cream cheese mixture.
In bowl, mix the remaining 1 cup sugar with salt, cornstarch, juices and water.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Cool; pour sauce over fruit.
Let set.
Eat while warm.
Sauce is optional.

title: hamburger main dish
directions: Cook ground beef.
Drain.
Place in dish and mix in onion. Pour soup over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Take from oven.
Add Tater Tots to top.
Bake an additional 20 minutes until golden brown.

title: old fashioned apple pie
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Prepare pastry; roll out half and line a 9-inch Redi-Pan deep dish pie pan.
Combine sugar, flour and
cinnamon in medium size bowl.	Stir in water.	Add apples. Mix
to coat thoroughly.
Pour into pastry lined pan. Dot
with butter.
Roll
out	second	half
of pastry for top crust.	Cut design in center to allow steam to escape.	Place on
pie, pressing around edge to seal.
Brush pastry with milk and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes or until crust is browned. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: low-fat diet seasoning
directions: Cook chicken, hen, turkey or beef.
Put broth in refrigerator overnight.
Lift off congealed fat; throw away.
Use broth in pinto beans, butter beans, green beans or peas.
Also you can use bought chicken and beef cubes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat in shortening.
Season with salt and pepper.
Then add the next 5 ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat for 2 hours, then add 1 teaspoon of Worcestershire sauce and 1 teaspoon Kitchen Bouquet.
Thicken with 4 tablespoons of flour mixed with a bit of water.
Just before serving, add 1/2 cup sour cream.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, soup and one-half can of water in casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.
Remove; spread french fried onions over top and bake until browned.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Combine filling ingredients thoroughly and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° about 1 hour.

title: simple fruit dip
directions: Mix well; serve with fruit.

title: english trifle
directions: Bake yellow cake in an oblong pan as directed. Cut in half. Freeze half for something later. Cut other half in 8 or 9 pieces (split each piece). Arrange half the pieces in a 1-quart glass serving dish; top with 1/2 of strawberries. Spread on half of pudding; repeat. Chill 8 hours.

title: cherry delight
directions: Mix crumbs of crackers, melted butter and sugar. Put mixture in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 8 minutes; let cool.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg; beat well, then add nuts, raisins and applesauce.
Mix into dry ingredients, leaving a little flour to add last.
Add 2 tablespoons hot water and remainder of flour.
Bake in a 325° oven in loaf pans or 9 x 13-inch greased pan for approximately 35 to 45 minutes.

title: party punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in cranberry juice on low heat.
Add to other juices and chill.
pour over ice in punch bowl.
Add 7-up just before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine beaten eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil; beat.
Add alternately, zucchini and flour mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake at 325° approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour, either in 2 loaf pans or an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Test for doneness with a toothpick.

title: chicken and stove top casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook chicken and set aside to cool. Prepare Stove Top dressing as package says.
Mix soup and milk together and set aside.
Cut chicken in cubes.
Put in casserole dish.
Pour soup mixture on top of chicken.
Spoon Stove Top dressing on top of casserole.
Mix into casserole some.
Bake in oven 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbly.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add eggs.
Fold in pineapple and bread.
Top with cinnamon.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: bart's clam chowder
directions: Put water in large pot.
Add onions, carrots, celery, potatoes, parsley and tomatoes.
Fry bacon until browned; add to water mixture with the drippings.
Add clams, salt and pepper. Cook 1 hour or more.

title: mom's potato soup
directions: Cook together potatoes and onion in sauce pan covered with water until potatoes are mushy.
Add milk and salt and pepper to taste.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix and pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: basic vinaigrette
directions: Combine mustard and vinegar in small bowl.
Add oil slowly, while whisking.
You may add your favorite herbs to enhance, also salt and pepper as desired.

title: apple cranberry casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix apples, cranberries and sugar and put into greased 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix oatmeal, brown sugar, flour and pecans and pour over fruit and sugar mixture. Cut the margarine or butter into pieces and place on top of the casserole.
Bake for 50 minutes covered, then remove cover and bake for 10 more minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
Great for breakfast.

title: crescent roll cheese danish
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Use 1 package rolls to line bottom of pan.
Cream sugar, egg yolk, cream cheese and vanilla; pour over rolls.
Cover with second package of rolls.
Beat egg white slightly and brush on top of rolls.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cook and drain carrots.
Mix remaining ingredients; cook until thick while stirring.
Pour over carrots and let stand for a short time.
Serve hot.

title: clyds chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until cooked off bone.
Cut into pieces.
Dilute soup with milk.
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing with butter and chicken broth.
Pour over chicken and soup mixture.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: star spangled cherry pie
directions: Use medium bowl.
Beat cream cheese until light and fluffy. Add sweetened condensed milk. Blend thoroughly.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Pour into pie crust. Chill 2 to 3 hours. Top with cherry pie filling before serving.

title: chilaquiles con pollo
directions: Place chicken in a Dutch oven; add water and salt.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, 1 1/2 hours or until tender. Remove chicken from broth.
Cool, bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Strain broth and set aside 1 1/3 cups.

title: impossibly easy taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Grease 9 x 13 pan. Cook beef and onion in skillet over medium heat until brown; drain. Stir in seasoning mix. Spread in pan. Sprinkle with chilies. Stir Bisquick, milk and eggs until blended. Pour into pan. Bake 35 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 15 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: german coleslaw
directions: Mix cabbage, bell peppers and onions in bowl.
Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Chill for 24 hours or longer.
Yield: 12 cups.

title: corn pudding
directions: Put eggs in bowl and mix on medium speed.
Reduce to low speed and add flour, sugar, milk, butter, salt, pepper and corn. Mix all until blended.
Pour into a buttered 1-quart casserole and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Slice banana on bias and dip into pineapple syrup.
Put all fruit in bowl.
Add 1/2 cup coconut and mix.
Pour pineapple syrup over all and chill.
At serving time, top with remaining coconut.

title: six in one cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add
eggs
and beat well.
Mix in flour, salt, soda and vanilla.
Divide dough into as many parts as desired and add
one of the following:
approximately
cup coconut,
cup raisins, 1/2 cup nuts and 1/4 to 1/2 cup chocolate or caramel chips.

title: party turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium skillet, combine onion soup mix and meat; brown well.
Blend in cheese.
Separate or spread crescent dough according to package directions, then cut triangles in half.
Place spoonful of meat mixture in center of each triangle.
Fold over and seal edges.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 48 turnovers.

title: mother's squash supreme
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and place in a greased casserole dish.
Cover mixture with crumbs and melted butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix together the night before you plan to serve.

title: microwave corn on cob
directions: Place corn in a Ziploc bag, with a hole punched in it.
Cook on High for 2 minutes.
Turn and cook 3 more minutes.
Be very careful of steam.

title: veal parmigiana fanfare
directions: Saute onion and garlic in 2 tablespoons of olive oil until soft; stir in tomato paste and sugar.
Simmer 45 minutes, stirring often.
Stir in oregano and simmer 15 minutes longer.
Meanwhile, beat eggs and salt slightly.
Dip veal cutlets into egg mixture and then into cracker crumbs to coat well.
Brown cutlets, a few at a time, in part of remaining olive oil, adding oil as needed; drain. Pour about 1 cup of the tomato sauce into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with 1/2 of the cutlets; spread with 1 cup of sauce. Sprinkle with 1/2 portion each of the Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Repeat to make another layer.
Bake for 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serve with cooked spaghetti.
Serves 8.

title: dump cake
directions: If you don't have enough fruit of one kind, you may add apples or pears.

title: barbecued kielbasa bites
directions: In a saucepan, pour 8 ounces of barbecue sauce and meat. Simmer slowly for about 1 hour.
If serving for a party, a small slow cooker or fondue may be used.
Use party picks to eat with.

title: strawberry fruit dip
directions: Mix strawberries in a blender, then add to Cool Whip and Equal.
Very good with apples, bananas and grapes.

title: seafoam candy
directions: Boil sugar and water together until a little dropped in cold water forms a soft ball (238°).
Slowly pour the hot mixture over stiffly beaten white of the egg, beating while pouring.
Add nuts and extract and beat vigorously until candy stiffens.
When nearly set drop by spoonfuls on paper.
When cold the seafoam will harden so that it can easily be taken from the paper.

title: snickers pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix crushed cookies, peanuts and melted butter in a 9-inch deep pie dish and press firmly over bottom and sides.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool completely before filling.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion, mushroom and butter in skillet. Add broccoli and soup mixing well. Reduce heat and add cheeses. Cook over low heat until cheese melts, stirring constantly. Add almonds and mix. Serve with crackers.

title: danish bagel
directions: Preheat broiler.
Spread bagel halves with ricotta.
Sprinkle each bagel with 2 tsp. cinnamon sugar.
Arrange peach slices over cheese.
Sprinkle with remaining cinnamon sugar.
Place bagel halves on baking sheet.
Broil 6 inches from heat about 4 minutes, until sugar is bubbly and mixture is hot.
Serve warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add rest of ingredients.
Put in greased casserole for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook peppers and onion in oil.
Mix with the remaining ingredients in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle 1/4 c. Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes until bubbly.

title: planters punch
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Fill punch bowl.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon on buttered baking sheet.
Dip fork in water and press down.
Bake in a 325° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.	Cool completely on cookie sheet.
When cool, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: jello cream cheese salad
directions: Cream the cheese with a little milk.
Fold into stiffly whipped cream.
After lemon jello has chilled, fold it into the cream cheese mixture.
Fold the fruit cocktail into the chilled strawberry jello.
For this, use about 1 cup hot water and 3/4 cup cold water or juice from fruit cocktail.
When finished, the light mixture should be on top.
These mixtures have been poured into a mold and then chilled.
Unmold onto plate for serving.

title: raisin pie
directions: Wash raisins carefully and cook in boiling water until tender. Mix flour and sugar and add to cooked raisins, stirring until it thickens.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake in a double crust at 400° until done.
Add nuts.
(Nuts are optional.)

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and Crisco; add 1 egg at a time, beating slowly.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Alternate milk and flour.
Beat well.
Preheat oven to 325° and bake for 1 1/2 hours. Cool for 10 to 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: pickled mango
directions: Peel and cut mangoes into strips.
Add Hawaiian salt and leave overnight.
Drain and dry in a screen until very dry.
Place in pot and cover with water.
Boil for 20 to 30 minutes.
Drain in colander.
Place in pot; add in rest of ingredients and stir using low heat until hardens.

title: chocolate millionaires
directions: Pleasant words are as a "honey-comb," sweet to the soul and health to the bones.
Proverbs 16:24.

title: dilly beans
directions: Slightly immature beans are the best.
Stem and wash beans. Leave whole.
Prepare pint jars for canning.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Crumble sausage into skillet.
Brown and drain. Melt cheese in microwave and add to sausage.
Place by spoonfuls onto sliced bread on cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 minutes.

title: jalapeno corn bread casserole
directions: Cook
ground
beef in skillet;	drain well.
Set aside. Mix cornmeal,
salt, bacon drippings, corn and eggs together. Pour half of corn bread mixture in greased baking dish.	Layer meat, onion,
peppers
and cheese.
Cover with remaining corn bread mixture.
Bake
45	to
50	minutes
at
Serves 6 people.

title: french coconut and pineapple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour into unbaked pastry shell. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until set.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients together.
Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: turkey vegetable pie
directions: Cook frozen vegetables and drain.
In saucepan, cook onion, celery and thyme until tender.
Add soup and milk and stir until smooth.
In a 12 x 8-inch baking dish, combine turkey, cooked vegetables and pepper.
Add soup mixture and stir gently to mix.

title: blueberry butter
directions: *To make honey butter, substitute 1/4 cup honey for blueberries.
Makes 1 cup.

title: blender chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend liquids in blender first.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Beat egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour over pies and bake until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, drain.
Add all ingredients and place in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: brown edge sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine until fluffy.
Beat in sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add flour, mixed with salt and baking powder.
Mix well. Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes or until edges are brown.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: crawfish stew
directions: By using all-purpose flour and oil, make a roux (dark brown). Add all chopped vegetables and let vegetables wilt in roux. Add tomato sauce and about 4 to 6 cups water. Stir occasionally. Let simmer for 1 to 2 hours, adding Tony's seasoning and dash of salt and red pepper while simmering.
Add crawfish tails and let simmer (low heat) approximately 1 1/2 to 2 hours more. Serve over rice.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Hard-boil eggs; set aside to cool. Cook macaroni according to package directions (or taste). Rinse with cool water; drain. Dice celery. Shell eggs, cut in two directions (small pieces).
Combine macaroni, celery and eggs in larger bowl. Mix salad dressing, mustard, sugar and salt together.
Add to macaroni mixture. Continue to season to taste.
For better taste, refrigerate before serving.

title: spaghetti confetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain and season.
Mix all together, then add Italian dressing.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: macaroni salad
directions: In a large bowl put onion, celery, eggs and macaroni.
In a small bowl, mix Miracle Whip, vinegar, sugar, milk, salt, pepper and garlic until well blended.
Pour over macaroni mixture.
Mix together.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Mix in order given.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until done.

title: pineapple pudding
directions: In heavy saucepan, mix thoroughly the sugar, flour and salt. Add eggs and pineapple; mix well.
Add water and butter.
Cook until thick.
Remove from heat.
Crumble 6 cookies into a 1 or 1 1/2-quart dish.
Top with half the pudding.
Cover with the other 6 cookies.
Add remaining pudding.
Chill.
When cold, spread whipped topping over top.
Refrigerate.

title: three bean salad
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl that will seal.
Shake bowl to mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight to marinate.
This keeps for several days.
(A fourth can of beans, possibly green limas may be added also.
If so, slightly increase vinegar, oil and sugar.)

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: Cook celery, green peppers and onions in half the butter, until tender.
Add garlic and ham; cook 5 minutes longer.
Add remaining butter, shrimp, salt, hot pepper sauce, chili powder and sugar.
Cook, tossing often until shrimp are pink.
Add tomatoes and heat.
Serve over rice.
Makes 8 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix
ingredients and pour into crust.
Refrigerate 1 or 2 hours before serving.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar and flour.
Add rhubarb and toss lightly until rhubarb is coated with sugar mixture.
Spoon into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In the same bowl combine flour, oatmeal, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add butter.
Cut in with pastry blender until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle crumbs over rhubarb.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 minutes or until topping is brown and rhubarb is tender.
Serve warm.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: white fluffy frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick. Take off heat and cool to lukewarm. In another bowl, cream butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla. Add to cooked flour and milk mixture. Beat with mixer at high speed until fluffy. Spread on first layer and sprinkle coconut on. Spread on second layer and sprinkle top and side of layers. Makes enough for 2 (9-inch) layers.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream the oil, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, slowly. Add all at once with buttermilk and vanilla to mixture.
Stir in apples and walnuts.
Add to greased and floured pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Add sugar gradually.
Add vanilla, nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto a foil covered cookie sheet.
Place in oven; turn oven off.
Let stay for 6 to 7 hours.
Do not open oven door!
Makes 35 to 40 cookies.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Mix 2 cups flour, sugar, shortening, salt and yeast in 2 1/2-quart bowl.
Add water, milk and egg.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead 5 minutes. Place in bowl, cover and let rise for 1 hour.

title: quick and easy clam sauce
directions: Prepare 2 (9-inch) pie crusts.
Line a pie plate with one.

title: summer vegetable pasta salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add noodles and vegetables, mix lightly.
Season to taste.
Chill.

title: cranberry-glazed turkey loaf
directions: Cook sausage in a heavy skillet until browned, stirring to crumble.
Add onion and celery; cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Drain well.
Combine sausage mixture, turkey and next 6 ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix well.
Shape mixture into a loaf; place in a lightly greased 8 x 4 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until done.
Pour off excess liquid.
Transfer loaf to serving platter; spoon 1/2 cup Cranberry Glaze over top. Serve remaining glaze with loaf.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Whip cream, but don't add any sugar.
Mix in lemon pie filling.
Drain fruits and add to mixture.
(Can save tablespoon or so of pineapple liquid to add to mixture.) Chill.
Serve on lettuce.

title: banana muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Combine yogurt, milk, banana and vanilla; blend together just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill greased muffin cups 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order given, pour into pie crust or crusts.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes then 350° until knife comes out clean when inserted at center of filling, usually 30 minutes for small pie or 50 minutes for deep pie.

title: lemon ice
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat at low speed 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover.
Freeze until firm (about 4 hours).
Spoon into larger mixer bowl.
Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy but not thawed (2 to 3 minutes). Return to pan and refreeze at least 4 hours or until firm.

title: batter for deep fry
directions: Mix all together and stir as using.
Mixture tends to thicken at bottom.

title: 4 flavor salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.
Set out 1/2 hour before serving.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Stir butter into hot spaghetti.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs. Form spaghetti into crust in a 10-inch pie pan.
Spread cottage cheese over bottom of crust.
In skillet, cook beef and onion until tender and meat is brown.
Drain fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt.
Heat through.
Turn meat mixture into spaghetti crust.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix jello and gelatin together. pour boiling water over mixture and stir until mixture is dissolved. pour into a 9x13 inch pan and chill. Cut into shapes after mixture is well chilled.

title: four bean casserole
directions: In a large skillet, fry bacon until lightly browned.
Remove from skillet; drain.
In the same skillet, brown ground beef and onions; drain.

title: cranberry chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking dish.
In a bowl, combine Catalina dressing, onion soup mix and cranberry sauce.
Mix well and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until sauce bubbles.
Serve with rice or noodles. Very easy!
Ryan's favorite.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Cook beef nearly done.
Then add other ingredients.
Cook 5 or 6 hours.
Cook on high heat until bubbly and then lower heat and cook until done.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix together with fork, turn into loaf pan and put into cold oven. DO NOT PREHEAT OVEN.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Take from oven and brush with melted butter.
Turn at once into aluminum foil and wrap.

title: homestyle turkey pot pie
directions: Line 9-inch pie pan with 1 crust; set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Pour filling in pie pan.
Top with second crust.
Seal and crimp edges. Slit top of crust to vent and bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 servings.
Preparation: 10 minutes.
Bake time:
45 to 50 minutes.

title: egg dye
directions: Mix in plastic bowls.

title: chocolate chip cookies(eggless)
directions: Mix ingredients, adding chips last.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake in 350° oven.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: deer jerky
directions: Marinate overnight; bake at 150° for 6 to 8 hours by hanging from oven rack.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Add salt and mustard and mix well.
Add all other ingredients and toss well.
Pour into well-greased 8 x 10-inch casserole and refrigerate for 12 hours or overnight.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Let sit 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: fresh cucumber slices
directions: Layer sliced cucumbers and onion in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Pour marinade over cucumbers and onion.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.

title: creme brulee(texas governor ann richards' mansion recipe)
directions: Beat egg yolks in a large bowl.
Set aside.
Scald remaining ingredients in a heavy saucepan (nonaluminum).
Do not boil. Slowly add hot cream mixture to yolks while mixing, being careful not to beat air into it.
Set up cheesecloth to strain mix.
Pour into ovenproof custard cups (about 4 ounces).

title: finger jello
directions: Mix together all ingredients; chill until firm.

title: 60 minute cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat eggs.
Combine dissolved yeast, milk, eggs, sugar, melted butter and salt in this order and mix well.
Add flour to make sticky dough.
Allow to stand in warm place 15 minutes.
Shape into cinnamon rolls.
Let rise 15 minutes. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: daddy's buttermilk corn bread
directions: Sift flour; stir in cornmeal.
Combine egg and buttermilk; add shortening.
Pour into dry ingredients; stir just until mixed. Turn into hot 8-inch square pan (greased).
Bake in 400° oven for about 30 minutes.

title: lemon chicken(serves 1)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Combine seasonings and remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken and bake for 30 minutes.

title: coconut and pineapple pie
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Mix in egg and mix remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs longwise.
Set aside.
Mix mayonnaise, salt, pepper and mustard (to taste, if desired).
Mix in yolks from eggs.
Mix well, then spoon into holes in egg whites.
When filled, sprinkle with paprika.

title: old fashioned stack cake
directions: Combine sugar, shortening and molasses.
Beat until smooth. Add buttermilk, eggs, soda, ginger and salt.
Beat until blended (do not overbeat).
Fold in flour.
Pat into a 10-inch circle.
Put on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Repeat with another 10-inch circle, etc. until batter is used up.
Spread applesauce or dried apples between layers.
Serve.

title: green rice
directions: Butter a 2-quart (9 x 9-inch) baking dish.
Mix all ingredients.
Place into buttered dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Enjoy hot.

title: golden cream soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine first 9 ingredients; mix well. Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Gradually add milk to flour, then mix into soup.
Add cheese until melted.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring water and butter to boiling point in a large pan.
Add sifted flour and beat quickly until smooth and won't stick to the spoon or pan.
Cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly.
Drop on buttered cookie sheet at 400° until puffed, then reduce heat to 350° and finish baking.
They should be brown and slightly dry.
When cold, fill with custard or whipped cream and sprinkle powdered sugar over them.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Strain and serve.
Makes about 20 (6 ounce) glasses.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix sauerkraut, onion, carrot, celery and green pepper together. Mix sugar, salt, oil and vinegar together. Add to vegetables. Let stand overnight or longer. Refrigerate.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter and mix with cracker crumbs.
Spread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat 2 eggs, 1 stick of butter and powdered sugar for 15 minutes; spread this over cracker crumbs. Cover with layer of banana slices, then layer of drained pineapple.
Cover all of this with layer of Cool Whip.
Top with nuts and cherries.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before serving.

title: ellen's chocolate cake(no milk)
directions: Mix dry ingredients together and then add liquids and blend. Put in a 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: corn pone
directions: Makes 2 pie tins full.
Bake in 350° oven for about 25 minutes.
As good cold as hot.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling water until tender; drain and mash.
Add carrots, 1/2 of the stuffing mix, sour cream and milk; mix well.
More milk may be added if mixture is too thick.
Season with salt and pepper.
Mix remaining stuffing mix with margarine. Line rectangular casserole with stuffing mixture, reserving 1 cup to sprinkle on top.
Add squash mixture to casserole.
Sprinkle with reserved stuffing mixture.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes or until heated through and brown.

title: mexican rice
directions: Saute rice in oil until lightly browned; place stock and 1/3 cup tomato sauce in water with teaspoon salt.
Add rice.
Bring to boil; cover and reduce heat.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes until liquid has evaporated.
Serve topped with remaining tomato sauce.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook soupettes, rinse and cool.
Bring pineapple juice, orange juice, sugar, flour, eggs, cornstarch, salt and lemon juice to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook until thick.
Mix with soupettes.
Cool well overnight.
Next morning (or when well cooled), mix in fruit and Cool Whip.
Refrigerate several hours and serve.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add pineapple and flour.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake for 1 hour in a 300° oven.

title: sanders fudge cake
directions: Bake cake in 13 x 9-inch pan per directions.
Cool.
Using wooden spoon, poke holes with long end all over cake, going to bottom of cake.
Remove lid from fudge and heat in microwave until liquid.
Fill all holes with fudge and spread any remaining on top of cake.
Cool.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: dirt cups for kids
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Put 1 package of Oreo cookies in food processor and crunch up.
Layer Cool Whip mixture and Oreos.
Put gummy worms on top and push into mixture.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, combine flour, cream of tartar, baking soda, cinnamon and allspice; mix well.
Set aside. In separate bowl, combine banana, sweet potato puree, egg whites, evaporated milk, maple syrup and vanilla; stir into flour mixture. Stir in dates.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove from skillet and crumble.
Add celery and onion to bacon drippings and saute. Add vinegar and sugar. Drain green beans and add to sauce.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with crumbled bacon before serving.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then raisins and nuts.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well.
Spray 4 one pound coffee cans.
Fill 1/2 full. Put cans on cookie sheet or foil to bake.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
When done remove from cans.
Freezes well.

title: chicken cordon bleu in mushroom sauce
directions: Flatten chicken breast with meat mallet.
Place a piece of swiss cheese and ham in the center of the chicken.
Roll up lengthwise and secure with toothpick and tuck edges inside. Combine seasoned coating mix, parmesan cheese, and parsley flakes. Dredge chicken in flour and dip in egg and milk mixture.
Roll in coating mix.
Grease a 9-inch baking dish with oleo.
Bake chicken in pan and top with mushroom sauce.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: vinegar pie roll
directions: Mix dough as for pie crust.
Roll dough out and put sugar and butter on it.
Pour in baking dish.
Make like a cobbler pie.
Pour hot vinegar, sugar and water over and bake at 375° until brown.

title: baked stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini lengthwise; scoop out seeds and pulp, leaving 1/4-inch shell.
Put shells in a large saucepan with boiling salted water to cover.
Gently boil for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Line pan with foil.
Combine next 8 ingredients in a small bowl.
Mix well.
Spoon into shells.
Place zucchini on foil.
Sprinkle with cheese and seal foil.
Cook at 400° for 1 hour.
Garnish with parsley.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Add onion, celery, bouillon, Season-All and garlic powder to broth and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add broken spaghetti and cook until just tender.
Add both soups, undiluted, stirring to dissolve.
Heat thoroughly.
Place in casserole dish and top with grated cheese and small dash of paprika.
Bake until cheese melts at 350° and serve.
(Yields 9 x 13-inch casserole.)

title: corn off the cob
directions: Bake in oven 1 hour at 250°.
Set cool.
Bag and freeze.

title: banana salad
directions: Mix brown sugar and cornstarch, then add egg and vinegar.
Add coffee cream mix and cook until thick.
Refrigerate until used. Layer with bananas and dressing.
Put Spanish peanuts on top. Dressing can be kept in refrigerator for up to a week.

title: hildegarde aiken's cry baby cookies 1
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar. Add eggs, molasses and flour.
Mix well. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
(The raisins represent the eyes and the coconut the tears.)

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix together and then add 1/4 cup poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: creamed enchiladas
directions: Open cans.
T. C. loves to do this.
Drain chicken and chillies.
Saute onion in 1 teaspoon butter.
Empty all cans in a large bowl, mix and add onion.
Crush Doritos.

title: custardy bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Break buttered bread in pan.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and milk.
Mix.
Pour over bread.
Sprinkle with raisins.
Set baking pan into a larger pan containing at least 1 inch of hot water.
Bake 55 to 60 minutes until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: fast and easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook, rinse and drain well the pasta.
Chop and add the onion, sweet green pepper, tomatoes and the cucumber.
Mix the Italian dressing and the Good Seasons salad dressing mix together.
Stir all these ingredients well and let set in the refrigerator overnight.
The longer it sets the better it is.

title: chocolate almond torte
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bake cake in 2 round pans (9 x 1 1/2-inch).
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Split cake to make 4 layers.
Cook almonds and sugar over low heat, stirring constantly until sugar is melted and almonds are coated.
Spread on waxed paper.
Cool and break apart. Mix pudding, milk and almond extract.
Fold in whipped cream. Spread 1/4 of pudding mix and 1/4 nuts between layers and on top of torte.
Refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil; add baking powder, flour, salt and soda.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: skillet cookies
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Mix sugar with eggs and add to melted butter, also dates.
Cook this mixture until it thickens and browns, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cool; form into rolls and roll in coconut, powdered sugar or chopped nuts.
Wrap roll and refrigerate.
Slice as needed.

title: old fashion chocolate pies
directions: Cook in double boiler until thicken then add 1 tablespoon vanilla and 2 tablespoons margarine and mix well.
Pour in pie shells.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then add 1/3 cup sugar and pinch of tartar.
Pour over pies.

title: grilled teriyaki marinade
directions: Remove fat and outside membrane from meat.
Score on both sides.
Combine remaining ingredients and marinate steak in mixture 1 to 8 hours, covered.
Place steak on rack of grill. Broil/grill for 4 minutes on each side for medium.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: candied fruit cake
directions: Mix well with hands; pack and press tightly in a pan with a hole in middle.
Cook at 275° for 1 hour.
Don't overcook.
Turn out; wrap loosely in foil.
Store in cool place.
Will keep indefinitely in freezer.

title: homemade pierogi
directions: Mound the flour on a bread board and make a hole in the center of it.
Drop the eggs into the hole and work into the flour.
Add salt and water and knead mixture until it is firm.
Let rest 10 minutes covered with a damp cloth.
Divide the dough into halves and roll out thin.
Cut into circles with a large biscuit cutter. Place a small amount of filling on one side of each of the dough rounds.
Moisten edge of round with water and then fold edges together to form a pocket and press firmly.
Be sure the edges are well sealed to prevent the filling from running out.
Drop the pierogi into salted boiling water.
Cook gently for 3 to 5 minutes.
Lift out of the water carefully with slotted spoon. Drain.

title: stuffing balls
directions: Mix the preceding ingredients and brown in butter on stove. Mix another can of cream of chicken soup and 1 can water.
Pour over top of balls.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick buttermilk biscuits
directions: Cut Crisco into flour with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add buttermilk, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly, 3 or 4 times.
Roll dough to 3/4-inch thickness; cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Brush biscuits with melted butter.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: kentucky corn pudding
directions: Mix flour, butter, sugar and salt.
Add eggs that have been slightly beaten.
Add corn.
Pour in a buttered casserole. Bake for 45 minutes at 325°
Stir once after the mixture is heated through and before it becomes set.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar gradually and cream until fluffy. Blend in egg yolk and mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg together.
Add to creamed mixture, alternating with milk.
Fold in beaten egg white.
Pour into greased muffin pans, filling half-full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 12 muffins.

title: french cinnamon puffs
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add the rest of the ingredients (except melted butter, cinnamon and sugar mixture) and mix well.
Put heaping teaspoonful in each well-greased miniature muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
They do not brown.
When baked, turn
out muffins and dip in melted butter and cinnamon/sugar mixture.
I start with 1/2 cup melted butter and 1/2 cup sugar, but I always need more.
Serve warm or cold.
Store in Tupperware-type container.

title: jim's barbecued shrimp
directions: Put butter in shallow pan, about 7 x 9-inch.
Add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, barbecue sauce, and Tabasco; heat until butter is melted and mixture covers bottom of pan.
Place shrimp in pan, adding garlic salt and lots of black pepper.
Place in oven under broiler and broil for 10 to 12 minutes actual broiling time.
Shrimp should be basted at least twice, with basting time not counted.
Keep warm and serve with toothpicks or on pieces of French bread.

title: banana punch
directions: Stir all together and freeze in quart container.
About 2 hours before serving, take out of freezer.
Just before serving, add 1 bottle ginger ale to each quart.
Use potato masher to break up frozen chunks.
(I use the blender to mash the bananas and it works great.)

title: blueberry french toast casserole
directions: Slice bread diagonally into 10 to 14 slices about 3/4-inch thick.
Place on a rimmed baking sheet.
In medium bowl, whisk together eggs, milk, baking powder and vanilla.
Slowly pour over bread, turning to coat.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.
Before serving, preheat oven to 450°.
Use butter to grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and cornstarch in dish.
Gently stir in blueberries until coated.
Place bread, wettest side up, on berries.
Wedge slices in tightly, cutting some pieces to fit, if necessary.
Brush tops of bread with melted butter.

title: vermicelli and shrimp salad
directions: Break the vermicelli into small pieces, about 2 inches long. Cook in boiling, salted water for about 10 minutes.
Rinse in cold water; drain thoroughly.
Combine with remaining ingredients Chill at least 3 hours before serving.

title: sausage grits
directions: Drain cooked sausage and spoon into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine grits, cheese and butter, stirring until cheese melts.
Combine eggs and milk; stir into grits.
Pour over sausage.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Garnish with parsley and pimento strips, if desired.
Serves 15.

title: cheesy salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together and make into patties.
Fry in hot oil.
Drain well.

title: creamed spinach
directions: Melt butter in skillet. Add spinach. Let set until thawed. Add seasoned salt and onion. Cover and cook on medium heat until heated. Sprinkle flour over spinach. Blend in and cook 1 minute. Add sour cream. Heat
until hot. Do not boil.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Rub strawberries through a nylon sieve using a wooden spoon. Stir in lemon juice.
Gradually add sugar, stirring well between each addition. Whip the cream until peaks form and fold into mixture.
Pour into freezer container and freeze.
Beat after 1 hour. Cover, then seal and freeze.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put 1/2 of corn bread dressing in bottom of 9 x 9-inch square dish.
Add half of the melted margarine and 1 cup chicken broth. Layer pieces of chicken on top.
Mix sour cream and soup together. Spoon over top of chicken.
Add remaining dressing, margarine and broth.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: frosted oatmeal cake
directions: Cut butter in small pieces in large mixing bowl.
Add oats and pour in boiling water.
Let stand 20 minutes.
Add sugars and eggs.
Mix well.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to mixture and beat well.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Pour into large cake pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: praline-taffy-apple pie
directions: Prepare crust.
On lightly floured surface, roll out half of the pastry to form a 12-inch circle.
Mix into a 9-inch pie plate. Trim even with rim or pie plate.
For top crust roll our remaining dough.
Set aside.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll dough into rectangle.
Place shaved ham in center.
Cover with 1/2 Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 Monterey Jack cheese.
Sprinkle with Italian seasonings.
Take bottom part of dough, fold over ham.
Repeat procedure, ham, cheeses and seasoning.
Take top and fold over ham.
Seal seams by wetting and pressing together.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.
Dip in spaghetti sauce or pizza sauce.

title: sugar pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pastry pan with dough.
Spread with butter (quite a bit).
Add sugar and flour.
Stir in, with finger, milk. Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: snickers bar pie
directions: Whip the cream cheese and confectioners sugar together.
Add everything else and combine well.
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pimento chicken noodles
directions: To give chicken noodles a different taste, add the carrot, pepper, celery and potato to chicken broth when you put your noodles on to cook.
Very tasty.

title: golden angel cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and water until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating.
Sift flour before measuring and then sift flour, baking powder and salt 3 times and fold into the egg mixture.
Beat egg whites until foamy, then add cream of tartar and continue beating until stiff.
Gradually fold in egg whites.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: jambalaya
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper. Add chicken, sausage and shrimp. Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt stick of butter.
Add sugar and egg; beat well.
Stir in pecans, coconut, raisins and vinegar.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 275° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: oatmeal a b c's
directions: In a large mixer bowl, cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Mix well.
Stir in oats, raisins and pecans.
Dough will be stiff. Refrigerate dough, covered, until chilled or as long as overnight. Reheat oven to 350°.
Shape rounded tablespoonfuls of dough into letters.
Place on lightly buttered baking sheets about 1-inch apart.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove; let cookies stand on baking sheets for 2 minutes. Transfer to wire racks to cool completely.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: peach-berry punch
directions: Sieve raspberries; discard seeds.
In a punch bowl, stir together sieved raspberries, pineapple juice, peach or apricot nectar, lemon juice and carbonated water.
Float frozen peach slices in bowl.
Makes 12 (4 ounce) servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: stuffed chicken breasts in wine sauce
directions: Combine the wheat germ, onions, sun-dried tomatoes, basil and garlic powder.
Add 1/4 cup melted margarine.
Set aside.

title: sweet potato orange casserole
directions: In large bowl, beat potatoes with electric mixer at medium speed until well blended with sugar, margarine, salt and nutmeg. Fold 1/2 of the orange sections into potato mixture.
Pile into 2-quart casserole.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into muffin tins.
Bake at 350° to 400° until golden brown.

title: hamburger bean pies
directions: Scramble hamburger meat with chopped onion until done.
Drain meat, then add mustard, ketchup and beans.
Flatten biscuits on baking sheet; add meat and bean mix on top of biscuits.
Bake at 425° until biscuits are done.
Add cheese halfway through baking.

title: pecan crispies cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Beat in egg and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients and blend into creamed mixture. Stir in nuts.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: toasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Mix ingredients in a shallow pan.
Bake at 350 for 15 minutes, stirring every five minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla together.
Add milk and bread cubes and stir.
If too dry, add 1/2 cup milk.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake at 325°
about 1 hour.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Drop mixture by tablespoon into hot oil.
Fry until golden brown, turning once. Yields 6 servings.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter and brown celery, onion and bell pepper. Saute seasonings until wilted, then add crawfish. Add garlic, salt and pepper. Cook for about 15 minutes on low. Add all soups to the pot.
May want to add 1 can of water. Simmer until ready to serve.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix pretzels, melted butter and sugar and press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 6 to 10 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: spaghetti(easy, beginners)
directions: In a saucepan add the butter, mushrooms, sugar, tomato sauce, sugar and oregano. Over low heat, stirring occasionally, bring mixture to a boil. Lower heat to medium low and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes. Serve over spaghetti noodles.

title: chicken imperial
directions: About 1 hour and 15 minutes ahead:
with sharp knife, remove skin from chicken breasts.
On waxed paper, coat chicken breasts with 1/4 cup flour.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat in hot butter or margarine, cook chicken, a few pieces at a time, until lightly browned on all sides.
Set chicken aside.
In drippings in skillet over medium heat, cook mushrooms and onion 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in cream, sherry, salt and pepper and stir to blend well.
Return chicken to skillet.
Reduce heat to low; cover skillet and simmer 20 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender.
Remove chicken to warm platter.
In cup, blend 1 tablespoon flour with 2 tablespoons water.
Gradually add to pan liquids, stirring consistency and cook until thick.
Serve sauce over chicken.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat first 3 ingredients together.
Then add the next 5 ingredients.
Mix the next 4 ingredients together and add to other.
Put mixture in 2 large greased loaf pans or 4 small ones. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Stand 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: cherry cranberry salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine gelatin and sugar.
Add water; stir until sugar and gelatin are dissolved.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart serving bowl.
Chill until firm, 3 to 4 hours.
Yield:
12 to 16 servings.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: In a bowl, combine Ro-Tel tomatoes and the 2 cans soup; set aside.

title: zucchini lasagna pie
directions: Cook and crumble ground meat in skillet.
Add onion and brown. Grease 13 x 9-inch casserole.
Put cottage cheese in bottom, then layer with 1/2 of each cheese.
Add herbs, paste, water and tomatoes to meat and heat.
Spoon over cheese.
Sprinkle half of remaining Mozzarella cheese, then top with zucchini.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add pumpkin, evaporated milk, spices, salt and sugar.
Pour mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle most of cake mix over pumpkin mixture.
Sprinkle nuts over cake, then sprinkle remaining dry mix over nuts.
Drizzle melted butter or margarine over cake mix and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Refrigerate when cool.

title: chicken liver stroganoff
directions: Clean chicken livers.
Saute onions and mushrooms (if using fresh) in oil until wilted.
Add chicken livers and saute until light brown outside and pink on inside.
Add cream of mushroom soup, soy sauce, salt and pepper and thyme.
Simmer until hot and bubbly.
Stir in milk.
Heat through and serve over hot cooked rice or noodles.

title: speedy doughnuts
directions: In deep fryer or heavy saucepan, heat about 1 quart oil to 350°.
Separate 1 can Pillsbury biscuits into 10 biscuits.
Cut hole in center of each one.
Fry in oil about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes on each side.
Cover with regular sugar or powdered sugar.
Serve warm.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together until completely blended.
Add sugar; add eggs.
Cream until smooth.
Add flour, 1 cup at a time.
Add vanilla.
Blend until smooth.
Pour into tube or Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together; drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Do not drain the stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, corn, kidney beans and olives.
Add all to hamburger and onion.
Heat together.
Top with chips, avocado, cheese and sour cream, if desired.

title: old fashioned gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Cover and chill one hour.
Shape into round balls; dip into sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: old fashion egg pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Place filled pie shell in an iron skillet.
Place in oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until firm to touch.

title: smothered steak
directions: Put steak, flour, salt and pepper in crock-pot.
Stir well to coat steak.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on high 1 hour, then turn to low for 8 hours (high 5 hours).
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and sour cream together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
(After each egg is added, beat well.)
Sift flour and soda together and add to creamed mixture.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Bake in 325° to 350° oven until cake tests done by inserting toothpick.

title: cocoa pound cake
directions: Stir together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
In a large mixer bowl, cream butter, sugar and vanilla; beat in eggs, one at a time, then coffee solution, just until blended after each addition.
Gently beat in flour mixture in several additions, alternately with buttermilk, only until smooth after each addition.
Bake in a well-greased and floured 10-inch angel cake pan in a 325° oven until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean, 1 hour and 20 to 25 minutes.
Let stand on rack for 20 minutes.
Loosen around tube and edges; turn out on rack; turn right side up.
Cool completely.
Wrap tightly and let stand at room temperature overnight before slicing fairly thin.
Serve with ice cream and chocolate sauce.
Makes one 10-inch angel cake.

title: petit fours
directions: Line 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with waxed paper. Prepare
cake
as directed on package.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
At
once,
turn
cake out onto towel and peel off paper. When
cool, cut cake into 1-inch squares.	Place cakes on cooling rack with waxed paper underneath.	For glaze, heat frosting slightly until
thin
enough
to be poured.
Add food coloring to a portion of frosting if desired.
Pour icing over cakes.

title: pink cloud salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar in pan.
Heat to boiling point. Remove from heat.
Add jello.
Mix well. Let set and cool to room temperature.
Stir in cottage cheese and fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into dish and refrigerate until chilled for several hours.

title: shoepeg corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and chill for several hours.
Excellent served with meat, poultry or fish.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: fry bread for navaho tacos
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; add water slowly.
Knead for 5 minutes.
Break off pieces the size of a small lemon.
Roll flat to 6 to 8 inches round.
Fry in hot oil in frying pan.
Top with refried beans or chili, lettuce, tomatoes, cheese, hot sauce or salsa.
Makes 6 servings.

title: diabetic barbecued beans
directions: Cut bacon into 1-inch pieces.
Cook 3 or 4 minutes.
Add onion; cook until onion is tender.
Combine next 7 ingredients and add to bacon mixture.
Stir in beans.
Simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat; add Equal and serve.

title: easy beef roast
directions: Salt and pepper roast.
Place in roaster pan or wrap in foil. Cook approximately 1 to 2 hours, depending on the size of roast. Remove from stove; add soups and Coca-Cola.
Return to oven; cook 1 to 2 hours more.
There will be a thick brown gravy.
Serve over mashed potatoes or rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: italian cheese cake
directions: Beat egg whites and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients.
Using mixer, beat Crisco and margarine together.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add egg yokes and vanilla and mix. Add flour and buttermilk alternately, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Mix well. Add pecans and coconut and fold into batter.
Fold in beaten egg whites until white is gone.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 9 inch pans at 350° until done.

title: baked french toast
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, butter, vanilla and cinnamon.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in milk.
Put bread sliced 1 1/2-inches thick in large bowl and pour mixture over it; let soak 15 minutes. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan, then arrange bread in it.
Pour the mixture over the bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or powdered sugar.

title: great cream cheese dip(for crackers and vegetables)
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill at least 2 to 3 hours.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix eggs, bread, dressing and seasonings.
Stir in crabmeat. Fry in oil in skillet until brown.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bring to boil in heavy saucepan.
Add the cup of reserved batter.
Cook until thickened, as in cream gravy.
Pour over warm cake.

title: poor man's jambalaya
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients in oil until soft.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer 40 minutes.

title: no fail pecan pie
directions: Stir syrup, sugar, and butter until thoroughly mixed.
Add eggs and continue to stir.	Add vanilla and pecans and mix well. Pour into deep dish unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes until firm.

title: meatballs in green pepper gravy
directions: Combine ground beef, salt, celery salt, oregano, pepper and garlic; mix by hand.
Shape into balls about diameter of a quarter.
Roll balls in flour; save remaining flour.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix together soup, sour cream and tomatoes.
Pour chicken broth into large pan or skillet.
Dip tortillas in chicken broth to moisten.
Place chicken mixture on tortilla and roll up tortilla.
Place in casserole dish.
When finished rolling tortillas, drizzle remaining sauce over all tortillas.
Sprinkle cheddar cheese over top.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Put pie crust in 9-inch pan.
Mix ingredients and put in pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes, then 300° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: buttermilk coconut pie
directions: Bake at 350° until brown, about 45 minutes or 1 hour.
Double this pie for two.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Work in butter with finger tips.
Add milk.
Mix lightly and quickly.
Drop by teaspoons on well-greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: pastry for double pie crust
directions: Stir together flour and salt. Cut in the shortening until pieces are the size of a pea. Sprinkle 1 tablespoon water over part of the mixture. Gently toss with a fork.
Push to side of bowl.
Repeat until all is moistened.
Divide dough in half.
Use immediately or cover and chill until needed.

title: spiced tea
directions: Steep tea in the boiling water.
Remove tea bags.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat until hot.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Cut up chicken into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together, saving 1/2 the fried onions.
Sprinkle remaining fried onions on top.
Microwave on #8 setting for 10 minutes.

title: sourdough bread from herman
directions: Combine milk, 1 cup water and cooking oil; bring to a boil, then cool to lukewarm.
Take 1/4 cup warm water and dissolve yeast in it; add sugar and salt and add this mixture to cooled milk mixture.
Put flour in a large bowl; hollow out center and pour milk mixture in center of flour.
Add Herman and stir; do not knead.
Put dough in a greased pan or bowl; cover and let rise until double.
Divide into 2 loaves.
Roll into desired shape. Place in greased baking pans.
Let rise, uncovered, in a warm place until double.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°, then 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix the butter, peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Form into eggs or balls and refrigerate or freeze until firm.
Melt in top of double boiler the baking chips or chocolate chips and paraffin. Dip balls into chocolate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix in saucepan, broccoli, oil and onion.
Cook until broccoli is thawed, then 5 minutes longer.
Pour in chicken soup, sweet milk, Cheez Whiz and 1 teaspoon salt.
Cook until bubbly.
Pour over 1 cup rice that has been cooked and spread over bottom of casserole dish.
Bake 15 or 20 minutes in oven at 350°.

title: hershey's chewy chocolate and chip cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat butter and sugars until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Gradually add to butter mixture, beating until well blended.
Stir in chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.
Cool slightly; remove from baking sheet to wire rack.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: lemon fruit dip
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients together and stir in sour cream. Chill and serve with fruit (kiwi, apples, strawberries, grapes, bananas).
Quick and easy.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Chop and drain tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Add turmeric, mustard seed, sugar, vinegar and salt to tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Cook for 1 hour.
Seal in hot jars.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas (easy)
directions: In a large bowl, mix soup, sour cream and cheese.
Put aside at least one cupful (scoop it into the sour cream container).
Add in chicken and green chiles and any optional ingredients.
Roll this mixture up into the tortillas and line the tortillas up in baking dishes or pans.
Spread the extra stuff you set aside on the tops. Bake, covered, at 250° for 20 minutes.
Uncover, turn heat up to 375° for another 15 minutes.

title: spinach manicotti
directions: Saute onion and garlic until tender.
Combine all ingredients except noodles and sauce.
Fill noodles with spinach mixture. Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Heat sauce.
Pour over noodles.
Sprinkle with additional Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: crunchy jumble cookies
directions: Stir together flour, baking soda and salt.
Set aside.
Beat margarine and sugar until smooth.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix in flour mixture.
Stir in cereal and chocolate chips.

title: low-fat tapioca pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla.
Let stand 5 minutes. Bring to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla.
Serve warm or cold.
Recipe makes 5 (1/2-cup) servings, each with .5 g of fat.

title: extra easy, extra good potato soup
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes into small pieces.
Peel and cut up 1/2 onion (or more, if desired).
Place 2 cans of soup and 2 soup cans of water in sauce pan over low-medium heat.
Add veggies and butter, season to taste.
Put lid on pan and cook until potatoes are tender (30 to 40 minutes).
Stir to prevent sticking.

title: mock rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Cream butter; work into flour until mealy.
Beat egg yolks, sugar and vanilla until thick and fluffy.
Add first mixture, beating thoroughly.
Fold in egg whites.
Beat for 15 minutes. Bake at 325° for 1 hour in greased tin.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cook above ingredients until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix
all ingredients together.	Add enough salad dressing to make moist.
Chill and serve.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine potatoes, chicken broth and onion. Bring to a boil; reduce heat.
Cover and cook over medium heat for 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Pour potato mixture into blender and blend until smooth.
Measure and add enough milk to make 5 cups.
Return mixture to saucepan.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 12-cup Bundt pan.
In large bowl, combine sugar and margarine; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after addition. Gradually add 2 cups powdered sugar; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
By hand, stir in flour and remaining cake ingredients until well blended.
Spoon batter into greased and floured pan; spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 58 to 61 minutes.
Cool upright in pan on rack for one hour.
Invert onto serving plate.
Cool completely.
Top with your favorite glaze.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour in bowl.
In a saucepan bring the butter, cola and cocoa to a boil.
Add marshmallows, remove from heat and pour over dry ingredients, mix well.
Add buttermilk, soda and eggs.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with bugles, chips and vegetables.

title: sourdough starter
directions: In a large crock, at least 3 quarts, soften yeast in water. Add sugar and flour; beat to mix.
Cover; let rise until light and slightly aged, 24 to 48 hours.
Starter may be kept in refrigerator 7 to 10 days without attention, then it should be stirred and equal amounts of flour and water added.
To keep starter, pour off amount needed for recipe, then add flour and water to remaining amount. Do not use metal spoons, measuring cups, etc. that touch the starter before adding to the recipe.
May be fed by putting in a peeled, unsalted potato.

title: butter bean bake
directions: Heat olive oil in a large skillet.
Saute garlic and onion until tender.
Add butter beans, cut up tomatoes with liquid, oregano, basil, thyme, bay leaf, cumin, coriander, lemon juice and brown sugar.
Bring to boil.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 teaspoon parsley.
Pour
into casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until thickened. Serve in bowls sprinkled with cheese.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Preheat electric skillet to 300°.
Saute onions, celery, garlic and mushrooms until tender.
Sprinkle with flour and seasonings and blend in.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste and simmer 10 minutes.
Add green pepper and shrimp and simmer 8 to 10 minutes more.
Grated cheese is also added with green pepper. Heat and serve over hot rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, over low heat, melt together margarine
and
peanut butter; remove from heat.
Add sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla;
beat well.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake
for
to
minutes
or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth, 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Pour into greased (do not flour!!) pie plate.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes. Top with Cool Whip when served.

title: taco heap
directions: Spread beans on a 12-inch round platter; cover with sour cream. Brown ground beef and drain; then stir in taco seasoning.
While the beef is cooling, chop up the lettuce and drain very well.
Dice tomatoes and onions.
Spoon meat on top of the sour cream; then cover with lettuce, tomatoes and onions.
On top of that put the cheese and black olives.
It will be in layers.
Serve with large tortilla chips.
This is a great dip for parties!

title: summertime drink
directions: Combine sugar and water; heat until consistency of syrup. Stir in all remaining juice, except ginger ale.
Chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.

title: cabbage and bean soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together.
Pour in a big pot and add beans, cabbage and tomatoes.
Add sauce, salt and pepper to taste and mix all together.
Simmer for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
A great meal with crackers or corn bread.

title: stewed chicken zucchini
directions: Lightly brown chicken breasts in about 2 tablespoons oil in a medium saucepan.
Add 1/4 cup diced onions, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup water.
Continue to simmer, covered, on low for about 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and set aside.

title: raspberry slush(serves 1)
directions: Blend with ice cubes on medium speed until creamy.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples.
Place in a greased baking dish. Combine dry ingredients; add melted margarine, mixing until crumbly.
Sprinkle on top of apples.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm or cold with your favorite whipped topping.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Bone the cooked chicken and cut into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients except the chips.
Place the chips in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour chicken mixture over chips. Sprinkle the top with some extra cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Serve with avocado and salsa.

title: all-bran refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix shortening, boiling water, sugar, All-Bran and salt, stirring until shortening is melted.
Let stand until mixture is lukewarm.
Add eggs, then the yeast softened in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Add flour.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover bowl and place in refrigerator overnight or until ready to use.
Roll the dough out 1/4 inch thick and cut into 2 1/2-inch circles.
With the dull edge of a knife, make a crease just to one side of center.
Brush with melted butter and fold large side over.
Press edges securely and place on a greased baking sheet 1 inch apart.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: candy mints
directions: Mix like pie dough.
Add color and flavoring, as desired. Roll into small balls.
Roll each in granulated sugar.
Press balls into molds.
Pop out.
Keeps several weeks.

title: lime-pineapple salad
directions: Heat pineapple juice so it will dissolve jello.
Add
Cool Whip, buttermilk and pineapple.

title: cheddar cheese log
directions: Beat the cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in Cheddar cheese. Stir in olives, pimiento, green pepper and Worcestershire sauce; blend well.
Shape into roll on waxed paper.
Coat well with almonds.
Cover; chill several hours to allow flavors to blend. Allow to stand at room temperature about 30 minutes before serving with assorted crackers.
Decorate with apple fans.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Place sugar, syrup and milk in saucepan over medium heat, stirring occasionally.
Cook to 234° or until ball forms when a small amount is dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter, butter and vanilla.
Beat until thick.
Spread in buttered pan; cut into squares.

title: butterscotch cashew bars
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Combine flour and salt.
Add to creamed mixture just until combined.
Press into a greased 15x10x1 cookie sheet.

Bake at 350°for 10-12 minutes, until lightly browned. Spread topping (recipe to follow) over crust. Sprinkle with cashews, pressing down lightly. Bake 11-13 minutes or until topping is bubbly and lightly browned. Cool on wire rack. Cut into bars.

title: microwave sweet potato puffs
directions: Whip sweet potatoes with butter, brown sugar and salt.
Form into 1 1/2-inch balls around a marshmallow and roll in corn flakes.
Arrange on a baking dish with small place between each ball.
Cook, covered, on 80 percent power 1 1/2 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: country lima beans
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces.
Fry until crisp.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Add onions and cook until soft.
Sprinkle with flour.
Stir to make roux.
Cut tomatoes into small pieces. Add to roux.
Stir.
Add lima beans.
Heat and serve.
The gravy can be made ahead of time.
Serves 8 generously.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll in crushed nuts and serve with crackers.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Add lemon and vanilla.
Add flour to batter (reserving a little to coat fruits and nuts).
Mix well.
Add cherries, pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 250° in angel food pan or 2 loaf pans for 2 to 3 hours.
Decorate the top with some fruit and bake until light brown.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook and debone chicken; cut into bite size pieces.
Cook spaghetti; set aside.
Saute green pepper, onion, celery and both kinds of olives in butter.
Combine vegetables and chicken.
Mix the sherry, soup and broth.
Combine with chicken and vegetable mixture and cooked spaghetti.
Put in large baking dish; sprinkle with Parmesan.
Bake for 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: summer apple pudding-pie
directions: Beat the egg until light; add sugar and blend well.
Combine flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon; add to egg mixture, stirring well.
Add chopped apples and nuts.
Spoon into well-greased 8 or 9-inch pie pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cool, with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream or plain.
Although it bakes in a pie pan, this dessert is more like a cake, laced with lots of fresh apple and is quicker to make than a pie.
I almost always double the recipe and bake it in a 10-inch pan.

title: oatmeal crispies
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and soda; add to creamed mixture and mix.
Add the oatmeal and mix thoroughly.
Roll into one-inch balls and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: seafood chowder
directions: Fry bacon.
Add onion and butter; cook until onion is translucent.
Add bouillon, celery, salt, pepper, potatoes and enough water to cover all.
Add wine, if desired, and cook until potatoes are tender.
Add seafood and cook 15 minutes more.
Add light cream.
Cornstarch may be used to thicken, if desired.

title: easy chocolate mound cake
directions: Bake cake according to box in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Remove from oven and prick thoroughly with fork.
Drizzle one can Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Spread coconut over this.
Cool completely. Spread Cool Whip on top.

title: chilled fruit soup
directions: Soak prunes, apricots and raisins in 3 cups cold water.
Add cinnamon stick, apples and pears.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until tender.
Add undrained cherries, bring to boil.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir into fruit.
Chill overnight.

title: spicy cheese log
directions: Mix cream cheese and Ranch dressing mix in a bowl with fork or hands.
Mix until dressing is well into cream cheese.
Roll into a log.
Press seasoned pepper firmly into log until it is covered all over.
Serve with crackers or Melba toast.

title: "apricot bread"
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl until well blended and lumpy.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured loaf pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 65 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: battletown inn baked squash
directions: Wash and slice squash; boil in salted water until tender. Drain and mash.
Saute onion in butter.
Add cream and crackers, stirring and cooking for a few minutes.
Mix with squash and place in greased casserole. Cover with bread crumbs; dot with butter. Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in 2-quart casserole; cover.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until defrosted, stirring once to break apart; drain.
Stir in croutons, soup, cheeses and milk; mix well. Re-cover, microwave on High for 8 to 11 minutes or until heated through, stirring twice.
Let stand covered for 3 minutes before serving.

title: baked pork chops and stuffing
directions: In 13 x 9 x 2-inch oval baking dish or 2 1/2 to 3-quart shallow casserole, sprinkle dry mix on bottom.
If using 6 ounce package, toss stuffing with contents of seasoning packet.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain. Add taco seasoning. Line large casserole dish with tortillas. Layer beans, meat, salsa and cheese; repeat. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Serve with sour cream and tomatoes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: pizza popcorn
directions: Melt first 4 ingredients.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Pour over popped corn and heat in a 300° oven for 15 minutes.

title: crumb-topped parsnip and turnip puree casserole
