directions: This recipe takes 30 minutes to prepare and 1 hour and 10 minutes to boil and bake.

title: brownies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, egg, 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt, soda and rolled oats.
Place half of this mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sweet-sour baked beans
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet on medium heat until crisp.
Drain on paper towels and crumble.
Remove bacon drippings from skillet. Place onions in skillet and add sugar, mustard, garlic powder, salt and vinegar; toss with spoon to mix.
Cover and simmer on low heat setting for 20 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix well and put 1/2 mixture in greased skillet. Add 2 cups grated cheese and then pour in remaining mixture and bake for 1 hour at 350.

title: blender cake
directions: Mix margarine and brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir.
Add nuts and chocolate bits.
Spread onto greased 11 x 17-inch pan.
Bake at 315° for 25 minutes.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix and separate into 2 parts.
Roll out each between 2 sheets of waxed paper.

title: oven french fries
directions: Ask your assistant to help you here.
First, preheat your oven to 400°.
Then, you can peel the potatoes or not, it's up to you (although the skin is the healthiest part).
Cut each one into long wedges (about 8 per potato) and put them on a cookie sheet.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Add shortening, water, nuts, raisins and applesauce.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add egg and beat 2 minutes more.
Bake in greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: Bring pineapple and sugar to boil; boil 3 minutes. Add jello; stir until dissolved. Add cream cheese and stir.
Cool. Fold in rest of ingredients. Pour into 9-inch square dish. Chill until firm. Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: black walnut cookies
directions: Melt margarine.
Add white sugar and brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well.
Sift salt, soda and flour together.
Add half of dry ingredients and beat.
Stir in walnuts (or pecans).	Blend in rest of flour mixture.
Shape into two long, thin rolls and wrap each in plastic or waxed paper.
Refrigerate or freeze. Slice and bake as needed.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes depending on your oven and thickness of slices.

title: hot appetizer pie
directions: Blend cream cheese with milk.
Add dried beef, pepper and sour cream.
Pat into an 8-inch glass pie pan.
Spread chopped walnuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: black raspberry bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add flour, soda and salt sifted together; mix well.
Stir in rolled oats.
Press half of crumb mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with preserves; cover with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 400°
for 25 minutes. Cool 5 minutes; cut into bars.
Yields 2 dozen.
Can be made with other preserves; such as
apricot.

title: kiefles
directions: Place flour and cheese in a bowl.
Add butter; cut into small pieces.
Mix ingredients with pastry knife or your hands until the butter is thoroughly blended and the dough clings together in a ball.
Divide into 3 balls; chill 3 hours.

title: cranberry casserole
directions: Mix together first three ingredients (apples, cranberries and sugar) in casserole dish.
Combine rest of ingredients for topping. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown hamburger and onions in small amount of fat; pour off excess fat.
Add chopped green pepper, mushrooms plus liquid from can and remaining ingredients.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together in large bowl until well mixed the eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add and mix until well blended the flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Fold in chopped apples and walnuts.
Batter will be very thick like cookie dough.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Serve plain or with whipped cream or a scoop of vanilla ice cream or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: double deck cocktail
directions: Into each glass, pour 1/3 cup pineapple juice.
Tip glass and slowly pour 1/3 cup tomato juice down side of glass.
If desired, float thin lemon slices, halved on top.

title: cheese scalloped carrots
directions: Cook carrots in salted boiling water, cover, 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and set aside.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter in a saucepan over low heat.
Add onion and cook, stirring often, until tender.
Add flour and next three ingredients, stirring until blended.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Stir in cheese and then carrots.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle over carrot mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pineapple-nut coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, soda, pineapple and eggs.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine brown sugar and pecans; sprinkle over top of mixture.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool 5 minutes.
Pour topping over warm cake.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Mix together well.
Bake in cold oven at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: southern peanut butter pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients, mixing until thoroughly blended. Pour into prepared pastry shell.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes; reduce heat to moderate (350°).
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Filling should appear slightly less set in center.
Chill.
Top with whipped cream.

title: dixie's sweetened condensed milk substitute
directions: Take a bunch of patience,

title: dill carrots
directions: Place 1/2 teaspoon dill and 1/2 clove garlic in each pint jar. Fill each jar with carrot sticks. Boil water, vinegar and salt. Pour over carrots. Close jars and turn upside down for about 10 minutes or until sealed.

title: cherry-pineapple crumb cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan; spray with Pam.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: In a large bowl, combine oil, vinegar, lime juice, onion, garlic, pepper sauce, salt and pepper.
Add chicken; marinate at least 1 hour at room temperature or overnight in the refrigerator. Light charcoal grill or preheat broiler.
Remove chicken from marinade; reserve marinade.
Grill over medium-hot coals or broil, turning and basting with marinade several times, for 10 minutes, until chicken is opaque throughout but still juicy.
To serve, spread tortillas with salsa and sour cream.
Add chicken; top with lettuce.
Wrap up tortilla and pick up to eat.
Serves 8.

title: swedish heirloom cookies
directions: Beat shortening and butter at medium speed of an electric mixer until fluffy. Add 1 cup powdered sugar and salt. Mix well. Stir in flour. Add water, vanilla and almonds, stirring well. Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheets and flatten. Bake at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes or until firm and lightly browned. Dredge warm cookies in additional powdered sugar. Yield: 4 dozen.

title: jolly old st. nick cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Angel food cake mix and 2 2/3 cups water.
Add "A" mix and mix in large stainless steel bowl (Kitchen Aid).
Mix for 2 minutes on slow.
Whip until peaks don't fall. Put into large bowl.
Sprinkle 1/4 flour ("B" package) onto whipped eggs at a time, then fold.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread evenly.
Cook for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let cool 35 to 45 minutes. Marshmallows should be spread like a beard; gumdrops as eyes.
Ice cake with icing evenly, then chow.

title: church windows
directions: Melt butter and chocolate chips; cool.
Add nuts and marshmallows.
Spread coconut on 2 sheets of waxed paper and divide chocolate and marshmallows on each.
Roll in logs and refrigerate until firm.
These will keep a long time in refrigerator or freezer.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs with salt and pepper in bowl. Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Dip into egg mixture; roll in cracker crumbs, coating well.
Brown in hot oil in skillet; drain chicken and skillet well.
Arrange chicken in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bring tomato sauce, basil and garlic powder to a boil in skillet.
Simmer for 10 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in butter.
Pour over chicken; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake, covered, for 30 minutes.
Arrange Mozzarella slices over top.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pizza potatoes casserole
directions: Empty potato slices (and seasoned sauce packet) into an ungreased 2-quart casserole dish.
Heat tomatoes, water and oregano to a boil.
Stir into potatoes.
Arrange pepperoni on top and sprinkle with cheese.

title: 1930's old time fudge(in the days before marshmallow creme.)
directions: Line a 9 x 5 x 3 inch pan with foil, butter it.
Butter sides of heavy 2 quart saucepan.
In the saucepan, mix sugar, milk, chocolate, corn syrup
Cook and stir over medium high heat until mixture boils.
Reduce heat to medium low and boil at moderate, steady rate.
Stir frequently until soft ball stage (234 degrees) about 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from heat, add butter and vanilla, but do not stir.
Cook without stirring to 110 degrees (about 55 minutes). Beat mixture vigorously with wooden spoon until fudge begins to thicken.
Add nuts, continue beating until fudge becomes very thick and starts to loose gloss-about 10 minutes. Quickly spread fudge into prepared pan.
Score into squares while warm, when fudge is firm, use foil to lift out of pan.
Cut in squares, top each with a walnut half.
Makes about 32 pieces.

title: helen hofer's mixed pickle
directions: Dissolve sugar, cider vinegar, oil and salt; heat to boiling. Pour over vegetable mixture and let stand overnight in a crock. Stir occasionally.
Store in refrigerator.
Keeps well.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: spinach, mushroom and mozzarella wrap
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In large skillet over medium high heat, heat oil.
Add mushrooms and garlic.
Cook and stir until the mushroom liquid has evaporated (about 5 minutes).

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix the mustard and wine to a dipping consistency with a whip.
Combine bread crumbs with cheese in a large plastic baggie.
Dip chicken in mustard mixture, then shake in bread crumb mixture.
Bake on a greased foil, covered, baking sheet for 30 minutes or until coating is brown and crispy.
Best served hot.

title: mexican hat
directions: Brown meat.
Add chili mix.
Blend Ro-Tel tomatoes and cheese soup.
Mix well.
Place rice on plate.
Top with meat mixture, then Fritos, lettuce and then tomato.
Spoon on heated cheese sauce.

title: florentine spaghetti
directions: Prepare
spaghetti
per package directions.
Brown meat and drain.
Stir
in
herb spiced mix, tomato paste and water. Bring to boil and simmer 10 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put chopped lettuce in a bowl.
Add celery, pepper and onion on top.
Add peas, 2 cups Miracle Whip, 2 teaspoons sugar, crumbled bacon and top with shredded cheese.

title: one dish casserole
directions: Cook noodles in salt water 15 minutes.
Brown meat in butter, add onion and celery.
Cook 10 minutes.
Mix noodles, onions and celery.
Add cheese (cut fine), tomato soup and salt and pepper. Cover with bread crumbs and bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: aunt ann's shortbread cookies
directions: Work dough for 10 minutes.
Chill overnight.
Drop by spoonful.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Blend in all ingredients; beat 2 minutes or until smooth. Pour into 2 (9-inch) greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot ranch beans
directions: This is a recipe for dried string beans. Take fresh string beans and a needle with a
fish line and string beans on it like a necklace. Hang them in the attic to dry.
When you are ready to cook them, cook them like dry shell beans.
Soak them overnight in water.
Add a few pieces of bacon pieces, onion, salt and pepper. Simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Flavor is a combination of dry beans and string beans.
Very good!

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar and flour together in a pot.
Add 1/2 cup hot water to mix.
Then add milk and cream.
Bring to a boil over medium heat until thick and bubbly.
Serves 4.
Use on pancakes or biscuits.
Very delicious.

title: summer lime chicken
directions: Using kitchen mallet, pound chicken breasts to 1/2 inch thickness.
Combine olive oil, garlic and juice of limes. Marinate 2 hours.
Grill or broil chicken until done.
Stir-fry vegetables.
Squeeze a bit more lime juice on chicken.
Chicken tastes even better cold.

title: mother's frittle fruit cake
directions: Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Sift flour and cocoa together.
Alternate flour and milk to batter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans. Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in order in a 8 inch dish. Squash, onion, cheese then crackers make two layers. Beat eggs and mix with milk pour over crackers. Pour melted butter over top. bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease jelly roll pan.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape
into
1-inch balls.
Place about 2-inches apart in pan.
Bake
to 25 minutes or until brown. Serve warm.
Makes about 7 dozen appetizers.

title: chocolate and caramel cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make cake mix according to box.
Pour half batter into pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Make sauce in pan with butter, milk and caramels.
Remove cake from oven; pour on caramel mix.
Sprinkle chips and nuts over sauce.
Top with remaining cake mix and bake for 15 to 20 minutes more.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix all ingredients together in medium to large casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and broil 5 to 10 minutes or until top is golden.

title: amana sauerbraten
directions: Place roast in stock pot of roughly the same size.
In another pan, combine vinegar, 2 1/4 cups water, lemon, onion and spices. Bring to a boil.
Pour over roast, cool and refrigerate for 3 days, basting and turning often.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Mix Oreo cookies and margarine and press in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Slice ice cream and place on top.
Sprinkle with salted peanuts.
Put in freezer.
Combine powdered sugar, chocolate chips, 1/2 cup margarine and evaporated milk.
Bring to a boil for 10 minutes over medium heat.
Boil gently.
Cool.
Pour over ice cream.
Freeze.

title: swiss green beans
directions: Mix crumbs and butter; set aside for topping.
Melt 2 tablespoons of butter, in a large saucepan, over low heat.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper, onion and sugar.
Add sour cream.
Stir until smooth.
Increase heat to medium and cook until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except graham cracker crust. Pour mix into crust and chill.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine soup, water, rice 3/4 tsp. dill and pepper in a 13x9 inch baking dish;
Mix well.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook celery and onion in butter until clear.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.
(Can be topped with grated cheese.)

title: raspberry-orange sauce
directions: Place raspberries in container of an electric blender or food processor; process until smooth.
Add powdered sugar and remaining ingredients; process until blended.
Pour through a wire-mesh strainer; press mixture with back of a spoon against the sides of the strainer to squeeze out liquid.
Discard seeds.
Serve with pound cake and additional fruit.
Yields 1 cup.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and hot water; cool and salt.
Add cottage cheese and salad dressing.
Grind carrots, pepper and onion.
Add milk last.
Goes real well with turkey.

title: caramel dip
directions: Beat with mixer until creamy.
Serve with apple wedges. Tastes like caramel apples.

title: chicken primavera stir-fry
directions: Brown 2 cloves of chopped garlic in hot oil in wok.
Remove garlic.
Add chicken to hot oil and cook until browned.
Remove from oil.
Add vegetables to oil and stir-fry until tender.
Return chicken to wok.
Add 2 tablespoons soy sauce and 1/2 cup chicken broth.
Stir until heated.

title: layered mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain off grease.
Mix in soups, chilies and seasonings.
Place half of this mixture in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Next, lay taco shells over top of this.
Finally, place remaining hamburger mix on top of shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top and serve.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown with bacon.
Stir until crumbly.
Drain.
Add onion. Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Add beans and mix.
Spoon into large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 10 more minutes or until cheese melts.
Serves 10.

title: momma's chex party mix
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Melt butter in large roasting pan in oven.
Stir in seasonings and worcestershire sauce.
Gradually stir in remaining ingredients until evenly coated.
Bake 1 hour stirring every 15 minutes.
Spread on paper towels to cool.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix together. Cook 20 minutes at 350°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients, then add last four.
Chill dough. Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: orange apricot freeze
directions: Stir yogurt in carton to blend.
Drain apricots and cut up fruit.
Combine yogurt, apricots, sugar, and nuts.
Spoon into container and freeze.
Line a loaf pan with waxed paper and pour into pan and let freeze, then take out and wrap and leave in freezer for later use.

title: almond tokay pilaf
directions: Stir onion into water; let stand a few minutes.
Heat butter until bubbly; toss in rice, onion and celery.
Cook and stir 2 to 5 minutes until rice tuns pale wheat color.
Add broth; cover and simmer over low heat 25 minutes until all liquid is absorbed or use microwave.
Stir in herbs, salt, pepper, almonds and grapes. Mix lightly with fork.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add beaten eggs, beat until light and creamy.
Gradually mix in dry ingredients and vanilla.
Add oatmeal, raisins and nuts.
Mix well, drop by teaspoons onto greased baking sheet.
Cook at 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen or more.

title: non-fat caramel corn
directions: Boil last 3 ingredients until hard crack stage.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon soda.
It will foam up.
Pour over corn and stir.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: pamela's potato candy
directions: Add vanilla to mashed potato, mix well. Roll out on powdered sugar. Spread surface of potato with creamy peanut butter. Then roll up like a jelly roll, or cinnamon roll. Slice into 1/2 to 3/4 inch slices. Keep stretching the roll to give you the maximum amount of candy pieces. Refrigerate covered with wax paper and loose plastic. Remove when ready to eat, all at once or piece by piece.

title: double chocolate cream pie
directions: Combine pie filling, milk, butter and chocolate chips in pan. Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full bubbling boil.
Remove from heat.
Cool 5 minutes, stirring twice. Pour into shell.
Refrigerate 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped topping and grated chocolate chips.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and milk.
Blend well.
Sift dry ingredients and add slowly to creamy mixture.
Stir in grated zucchini.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch tin.
Sprinkle with chocolate bits and chopped walnuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Dissolve bouillon in hot water; stir into flour mixture.
Add milk.
Stir over medium heat until thickened.
Combine sauce with chicken and vegetables and heat through.
Pour into lightly greased casserole dish.
Arrange biscuits on top.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes or until biscuits brown.
Serve immediately.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Bring seafood seasoning, water, vinegar and salt to boil in large, shallow pan with a tight-fitting lid.
Add frozen fish. (Do not use breaded or thawed fish.)
Boil 7 1/2 minutes on each side for a total of 15 minutes.
Remove from pan and place on cookie sheet.
Stir lemon juice with margarine and drizzle part of mixture over fish.
Sprinkle with parsley and/or paprika.
Broil 2 or 3 minutes.
Serve with remaining melted margarine.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Roll biscuits in this mixture.
Place biscuits in Bundt pan, greased.
Melt sticks of butter and add white sugar, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Pour this mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion finely chopped in skillet; drain. Line baking dish with tortillas, bottom and sides, allowing to extend over top of the pan.
Pour hamburger mixture on top, then add Ranch Style beans.
Top these ingredients with grated cheese.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and put in 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Blend together topping and sprinkle on top.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Put 1 box washed, stemmed, whole berries in bottom of a baked pie shell.
Mash berries from the other box.
Add water and 1/2 cup of sugar and boil.
Add 1/2 cup of sugar and cornstarch, mixed together.
Boil until clear, stirring constantly.
Add lemon juice.
Cool and pour over berries in pie shell.
Top with whipped cream before serving.

title: cassandra's potatoes
directions: Cut new potatoes into bite-sized chunks and boil until tender.
Cook and crumble bacon.
Mix cheese, onion, mayonnaise and bacon.	Layer potatoes in 9 x 13 pan and pour mixture on top. Spread evenly over potatoes and bake for 30 minutes at 325°.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Chop vegetables and layer in order given.
Spread Miracle Whip on evenly, seal entire surface.

title: springtime skillet
directions: Brown ground beef.
Sprinkle garlic salt; add rice and water. Simmer, uncovered, for 40 minutes.
Next add carrots and potatoes. Cook 20 minutes.
Stir in soy sauce, salt and pepper to taste.

title: baked barbecue chicken
directions: First you parboil chicken (vinegar and water; clean it first), then put in large pan seasoning the chicken.
Put a little water in pan, then put in oven at 400°.
Put a small pot on with the barbecue.
First Lipton soup with a little water, then after the chicken has cooked a little, pour on barbecue sauce.
This is for a large pan of chicken.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with last 2 ingredients.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: coffee tortoni
directions: Whip the whipping cream with 1/4 cup sugar and both of the extracts.
Combine the egg white and the coffee and whip until the egg white is fluffy.
Gradually add the 2 teaspoons sugar.
Fold together the cream mixture, the whipped egg white, the toasted coconut and almonds.
Spoon the mixture into fluted paper cups. Sprinkle these with additional toasted coconut, if desired. Freeze at least 2 hours or until firm.

title: super chicken
directions: In a large covered nonstick skillet, heat oil, garlic and Italian seasoning over medium heat.
Add chicken.
Cook 10 minutes, turning to brown all sides.
Meanwhile, dice onion and cut broccoli.
Add seasonings, tomatoes and onion.
Bring to a boil over high heat, then reduce heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add broccoli, then cover and simmer 10 minutes longer. Serve with parboiled rice or noodles.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Put in a bowl, cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Mix with hand mixer until well blended.
Add orange Jell-O as is and beat until dissolved.
With a spatula fold in oranges and pineapple.
Put in a mold.
Refrigerate until set.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together and keep covered in a tightly sealed container. To serve, spoon 2 or 3 teaspoons of mix into a cup or mug and add freshly boiled water.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add next 4 ingredients, already mixed.
Mix lightly, then beat well.
In separate bowl, mix remaining ingredients.
Mix well, then add to egg mixture, 1 cup at a time.
Mix well.
Add 1/2 cup walnuts.
Divide batter into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Remove from pan at once.

title: ezekiel's bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the water and let sit for 10 minutes. Mix the other ingredients.
Blend lentils, oil and small amount of water in blender and place into large mixing bowl with remaining water.
Stir in two cups of mixed flour.
Add yeast mixture.
Then stir in remaining salt and flour.
Place on floured bread board and knead until smooth.
Put in oiled bowl.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Knead again, cut dough and shape into loaves.
Place in greased pans.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to one hour. Yields 4 loaves.
(Ezekiel 4:9)

title: buckeyes
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together with your hands.
If too crumbly, add a little peanut butter.
If too creamy, add powdered sugar.
Make into small balls.
Melt the chocolate and paraffin over hot water.
Turn heat low and dip peanut butter balls almost under in warm chocolate.
Cool on waxed paper.

title: cherry-apple jam
directions: Chop cherries fine, reserving juice.
This will make 3 cups chopped fruit.
Combine cherries, apple and lemon juice.
Add pectin and mix well.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Boil hard, uncovered, for 1 minute.
Remove from heat, quickly skim off foam with a metal spoon.
Put into hot clean half pint jars.
Process in boiling water bath for 15 minutes.
Start timing when water begins to boil.
Makes about 5 half pints.
Contains 36 calories per 2 teaspoons.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix all together and use with favorite fruit.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in fourths.
Mix cinnamon and sugar together. Roll biscuit pieces in mixture and drop into Bundt pan.
Melt butter and add vanilla.
Mix remaining sugar mixture into butter and vanilla.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Invert on platter and serve warm.

title: spicy dogs
directions: Mix ketchup and brown sugar together.
Bring to a boil. Simmer 20 minutes.
Add bourbon to ketchup.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onions and celery in water in covered pan for about 20 minutes or until tender.
Do not drain.
Add milk, bouillon and butter.
Mix sour cream with flour until smooth.
Add to soup.
Stirring, make sure bouillon cubes are dissolved; add pepper.

title: no fail chocolate chess pie
directions: In a large bowl, add sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Mix well. Add eggs, evaporated milk, melted margarine and vanilla.
Mix real good.
Pour mixture in a 9-inch pastry (uncooked). Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until center is done.

title: cherry carnival
directions: Beat with rotary beater or spoon until smooth, then stir in cherries. Pour into 9 inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 - 40 minutes.
Serve warm covered with Cherry Sauce.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Step 1:
Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar and put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Sift together first 3 ingredients.
Cut in margarine and shortening.
Add milk and beat 2 minutes.
Add eggs and pumpkin. Beat 1 minute.
Pour into greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn upside down for 10 minutes on cake rack.
Remove pan.

title: homemade wine
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into a 1-gallon jug.
Fill remainder of jug up with water.
Put a small balloon over the neck of the jug.
The balloon will blow up, then down in 3 to 4 weeks. When it deflates, the wine is ready.
Yuh-hoo!

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add soda, salt and cinnamon and mix well.
Mix in flour and blend thoroughly.
Stir in carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: citrus cooler
directions: Combine all in a blender and process until thick and foamy.

title: chocolate revel bars
directions: In large bowl, beat 1 cup margarine with mixer at medium speed for 30 seconds.
Add about 1/2 of flour, all of the brown sugar, eggs, 2 teaspoons vanilla and baking soda.
Beat on low speed until combined good.
Beat in remaining flour.
Stir in oats.

title: macaroni casserole
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix well and place in dish.
Chill.
Sets up in about 1/2 hour.

title: hot fruit compote
directions: Place all fruits in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Melt butter and in top of double boiler, put butter, sugar, flour (mixed in sugar) and juice.
Blend well and cook about 15 minutes or until slightly thick.
Pour over fruit.
Cook at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: cornflake cookies(from the parsonage kitchen)
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil in saucepan.
Remove from heat; add peanut butter.
Stir in cornflakes.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: calico salad
directions: Mix together and let stand overnight.

title: fat-free guilt free potato salad
directions: Add a little green pepper or pimento if desired.

title: swedish ginger cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in egg, syrup and water.
Stir in sifted dry ingredients.
Chill.
Roll to 1/8-inch thick and cut in desired shapes.
Bake in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: granola
directions: Combine oats, coconut, almonds, sesame seed, sunflower seeds and wheat germ in a large bowl. Combine honey and oil. Stir into oat mixture. Spread in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until golden brown. Stir with spatula every 15 minutes. Cool and store in tightly covered container. Serve as a snack or a topping for fruit.

title: canned ham
directions: Using key supplied, open canned ham but do not remove from can.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven; pour off juices and pour over the ham the barbecue sauce and maple syrup. Bake for another hour.
Remove from can and slice.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Place rhubarb in pie shell.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add syrup and butter.
Pur over rhubarb.
Place pastry on top.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° for 30 minutes or longer.

title: cowboy stew
directions: In Dutch oven, melt butter and brown meat.
Saute onion, celery, garlic and bell pepper with meat.
Add rest of ingredients and cook about 40 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Serve over rice.

title: grilled tuna crunch sandwich
directions: Put tuna salad on bread.
Add Swiss cheese.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Add crisp bacon.
Grill in usual manner.
Delicious!

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix cukes, onion and salt in large bowl.
Let stand two hours. Drain well. Pack in freezer containers, leaving one-inch headspace.
Mix oil, vinegar, sugar and dill.
Pour into each container to cover.
Seal and freeze or refrigerate.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: german sauerkraut
directions: Fry onion and apple until glossy and tender (about 2 minutes). Combine onion-apple mixture with spices and 1 cup water in good size cooking pot.
Add sauerkraut; simmer for at least 30 minutes. Flavor improves with extended cooking time.
Before serving, taste for need of optional salt, pepper and garlic powder.

title: lentil stew(low-fat)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large kettle or Dutch oven. Bring to boiling. Reduce heat.
Simmer, covered, for 35 to 40 minutes or until the lentils are tender.
Very low-fat.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix well. Chill for 1/2 hour.
Put on greased cookie sheet, about 1/2 teaspoon dough and press with juice glass dipped in water.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until edges turn brown.

title: spicy stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove the stems from mushrooms.
Chop the mushroom stems.
Set mushrooms and stems aside.
In large skillet over medium heat, thoroughly brown sausage.
With slotted spoon, place sausage on a plate lined with paper towels to drain.
Spoon off all but 4 tablespoons of sausage drippings from skillet.
Cook mushroom stems in drippings over medium heat (about 10 minutes).

Remove skillet from heat, and stir in the sausage, cheese, and bread crumbs. Preheat oven to 450 degrees F. Fill caps with sausage mixture. Place stuffed mushrooms in jellyroll pan and bake 15 minutes.

title: easy taco hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger; drain grease.
Add tomato juice and spaghetti sauce mix.
Simmer.
In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer crumbled Doritos, 1/2 package cheeses, meat, rest of cheese and top with Doritos.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: mary b's caramel pie
directions: Cook unopened can of milk in boiling water for 2 hours.
Keep can fully covered with water the full 2 hours.
Remove from heat and cool.
Pour into graham cracker crust.	Spread Cool Whip on top.
Crush candy bar and sprinkle on top of pie.
Enjoy!

title: pistachio salad
directions: Beat until thick.
Spread as 2nd layer; chill

title: pickled pigs feet(my brother, bud, can eat a whole jar of this recipe.)
directions: In a large pan, cook pigs feet with water and salt for 1 1/2 hours or until very tender.
Remove pigs feet from liquid and let liquid stand until cold.
Skim fat off top of cold liquid, then add vinegar and spices and bring to a boil.
Pour over pigs feet in a sterile glass jar, and let stand 2 days before eating.

title: laura's summer squash
directions: If using crookneck squash, cut off most of the narrow crookneck.
Slice squash in half lengthwise.
Boil until tender but still firm.
Drain water and place on towel to further drain. Grease baking dish large enough to accommodate the amount of squash you are cooking.
Place cooked squash in dish seed side up, one layer.
Score through seed several times with knife.
Drizzle melted butter on each squash.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, and sugar on each piece and top with Cheddar cheese.
Run in oven at 350°F and heat until cheese melts.

title: biscuits with master mix
directions: Roll out on flour, cut, bake on ungreased pan 10-15 minutes or until brown at 450°.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Drain chicken.
Combine all ingredients and spoon into tortilla shells.
Roll and place in 9 x 12-inch glass dish. Spoon excess over top of tortillas.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Serves four.

title: vegetable breakaway bread
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters.
Dip in margarine.
Layer 1/3 in buttered 10-inch Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with half of vegetable and repeat layers, ending with biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Yields one 10-inch loaf.

title: tomatoes stuffed with crab salad or lobster
directions: Wash desired amount of tomatoes; dry.
Mix remaining ingredients with enough mayonnaise for a good consistency.
Put on top of small tomatoes or stuff into a larger tomato.
Sprinkle with paprika or chopped parsley.

title: "sausage dip"
directions: Crumble, fry and drain the sausage.
Place sausage, salsa and cream cheese in a crock-pot.
Heat until melted.
Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: microwave pralines
directions: Mix sugar and milk in a 2-quart batter bowl. Use a wooden spoon to mash out all the lumps. Add pecans. Microwave on High for 6 minutes. Stir and continue cooking on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until reaches soft-boil stage. Beat with wooden spoon for about 3 minutes or until it starts to thicken slightly. Quickly drop by tablespoon on wax paper. Store in airtight container.

title: weight watchers strawberry pie
directions: Crush graham crackers and mix with margarine; press into 8 x 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
In saucepan, bring cornstarch and water to boil.
Dissolve jello and Equal.
Add strawberries to cooked mixture.
Pour into pie shell and chill. 1/4 pie=100 calories.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt oleo.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: jumbo chunk chocolate cookies(yields 5 dozen large cookies)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening on medium speed for 5 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Add chocolate and nuts.

title: portuguese soup
directions: Brown sausage, onion, garlic and celery.
Add all the other ingredients and simmer for 1 hour.
Cabbage should be cut into 1-inch squares.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch baking dish and spread the following in layers:
pineapple,
blueberries, 3/4 cup sugar sprinkled on berries,
dry
cake
mix,
melted butter or margarine, pecans and 1/4
cup
sugar sprinkled on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes
(maybe
longer)
until brown on top.
Serve warm or cold. Good with Cool Whip.

title: caraway rye bread
directions: Soften
yeast
in
warm
water (110°).
In
large
bowl combine sugar, molasses, salt and shortening.
Add
hot
water and stir until sugar dissolves.
Cool to lukewarm. Stir in rye flour; beat well.
Add softened yeast and
caraway
seed;
mix well. Stir in the all-purpose flour to make
a
soft
dough. Knead on a well floured surface for 8 minutes.
Place dough in lightly greased bowl, turning once to
grease surface.
Cover; let
rise in
warm place until double (1
hours).
Punch down. Turn out on lightly floured surface; divide
in
portions.
Shape into 2 loaves and place in greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x
1/2-inch loaf pans.
Cover and let rise
in
warm
place until double (1 hour). Bake at 350° about 25
to
30 minutes. Brush with melted butter, if desired.
Cool on
rack.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: garden spread or dip
directions: Cream all together; cover and refrigerate at least 1/2 hour before use.
Good with crackers or veggie dip.

title: tobey's brownies
directions: Prepare pudding according to package directions.
When ready to boil, add cake mix.
Mix together.
Smooth into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 325° until set.
Any flavor pudding and cake mix may be used.

title: peach trifle
directions: Bring pudding mix and milk to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove and let cool.
Fold in half of whipped topping.
Sprinkle sugar over fruit; toss gently.

title: owen brennan's creole pralines
directions: In heavy pan, combine sugars, milk and butter.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat until mixture boils and reaches 238° on candy thermometer or until a sample forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and stir in pecans.
Beat for about 3 minutes or until creamy and somewhat cooled.
Drop by tablespoon onto a double thickness of wax paper.
Pralines will harden in 15 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.
Very easy to make.

title: reese bars
directions: Combine margarine and peanut butter in medium bowl and mix well.
Stir in confectioners sugar.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch dish. Spread chocolate over top.
Let stand until firm.
Cut into bars.

title: three-potato gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
With the butter, grease 3-quart shallow baking dish.
In bowl, mix cream, mustard, cornstarch, salt and pepper.
Add yams and potatoes; toss.
Pour into prepared dish. Cover and bake 1 hour; uncovered, bake 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden.
Let sit 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with thyme. Makes 12 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease and flour an 8 x 4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Stir flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt together.
Set aside.

title: barbecue ribs in crock-pot
directions: Place ribs on broiler pan.
Sprinkle salt and pepper on ribs. Broil 5 to 7 minutes on both sides.
Remove ribs to crock-pot. Pour enough barbecue sauce over ribs just to cover ribs.
Cover; cook on low 6 to 8 hours.
Very tender.

title: southern-fried chicken with cream gravy
directions: Wash and dry chicken.
Roll in 1/2 cup flour seasoned with salt and pepper.
Melt butter and shortening in skillet.
Add chicken and brown quickly on all sides.
Reduce heat, cover and continue cooking for 25 minutes or until tender, turning occasionally.
Remove cover during last 10 minutes of cooking. Drain on absorbent paper and arrange on platter.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Boil chicken in salt
water
until done.
Take meat off of bones.
While the
noodles
are cooking, add chicken pieces to mushroom soup.
Mix all together and serve.
